<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/013a9706-3932-4ce5-8777-64aab321cc32> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/013a9706-3932-4ce5-8777-64aab321cc32> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Committed canonical kg.nq: write-through export + hash-stamp startup reconciliation" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/013a9706-3932-4ce5-8777-64aab321cc32> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/11e01ea2-f520-4f7c-a165-09532dacd43f> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/013a9706-3932-4ce5-8777-64aab321cc32> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/013a9706-3932-4ce5-8777-64aab321cc32> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Implements the deferred half of Requirement d459cac2: the project KG's committed source of truth is now .moosedev/kg.nq (canonical sorted N-Quads), maintained automatically; the RocksDB store + vector DBs are a derived, gitignored cache. Mechanism: (1) WRITE-THROUGH — AppState::note_project_write() (mark_inferred_stale + canonical re-export, best-effort/never fails the symbolic write) replaces mark_inferred_stale at all five project-graph write sites (record/supersede/retract/relate MCP tools + HTTP import); CLI import also syncs. ~2k quads exports in milliseconds, so it is synchronous. (2) STARTUP RECONCILIATION (src/canonical.rs, in AppState bootstrap right after the store opens) — a three-way SHA-256 compare of T=hash(kg.nq), S=hash(canonical export of store), P=stamp (.moosedev/kg.nq.stamp, gitignored) decides: in-sync → nothing; fresh clone/git pull (S==P, T moved) → replace-import from text; missed export (T==P, S moved) → re-export; both moved or no stamp → patch-union + loud warn; no file + non-empty store → adoption export. An unparseable kg.nq (e.g. merge-conflict markers) FAILS boot deliberately — continuing would let the next write-through clobber the file. (3) CANONICAL SCOPE — project graph only, MINUS reasoner-materialized quads (enumerated via the reification tags: new provenance::reasoner_inferred_data_quads, shared with clear_reasoner_inferences). This is a correctness requirement, not hygiene: inferred edges' reification tags live in the LOCAL provenance graph, so committing the edges would strand them untagged (= un-droppable pseudo-asserted) on every clone; lazy enrichment re-derives them locally instead (inferred_stale starts true at boot). Blank nodes in the export trigger a warning (they break patch idempotency; records use named UUID IRIs). Answers d459cac2's open sub-questions: serialization = sorted N-Quads (per Lesson f84b4b21); provenance graph stays LOCAL-ONLY (author-name privacy, worst merge behavior; revisit as an option); staleness = content hash (SHA-256), never mtime; conflict guidance = git merges append-only additions cleanly, divergence falls back to patch-union + warn. Gitignore uses /.moosedev/* + !/.moosedev/kg.nq (git cannot re-include a file beneath an excluded directory). Verified: 9 unit tests (decision table, inferred-quad exclusion) + end-to-end lifecycle integration test (write-through, adoption byte-identical re-export, fresh-clone hydration, git-pull replace, divergence union), full cargo test + clippy -D warnings green." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
