<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/03393c63-5351-4891-9b21-06752534c612> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Push/injection delivery is evidence-supported for local models" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/03393c63-5351-4891-9b21-06752534c612> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/03393c63-5351-4891-9b21-06752534c612> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Corrects AD 3e69bae9 (\"value unproven — execution ceiling\"). Updated status: BUILT + MECHANICALLY VALIDATED (the opencode plugin injects the rank-1 record into the system prompt) AND now EVIDENCE-SUPPORTED for local models. In the only genuine injection test (B2-oracle) on a local model, A3B (qwen3.6-35b-a3b MoE) scored 1.0 on the cache-gap coding task — the patch makes every cross-module edit (struct + both constructors + builder + sqlite/postgres INSERT + both migrations) — vs 0.4 in all five cold/pull/B1-md/B1-rag/B0-oracle runs of the same model. Push/injection is the ONLY condition that moved the local model off 0.4, exactly the plugin's thesis (the symbolic layer injects rather than relying on the LLM to pull; invariant #1). Caveats: n=1 for the treatment (needs N-trial replication — local runs are high-variance per Lesson 5ac2174a); the LIVE plugin (vs harness oracle-injection) still needs an end-to-end value run; and the win is task-shaped (it shows up where cold lacks non-obvious knowledge, and is overhead on default-correct tasks). Extends value-benchmark AD 47f3f038 / opencode-driver AD f45cf655." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/03393c63-5351-4891-9b21-06752534c612> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/03393c63-5351-4891-9b21-06752534c612> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasRationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/ccfac08f-0221-4a0b-b690-2dedc02be062> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/03393c63-5351-4891-9b21-06752534c612> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-19T05:24:22.905811Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/03393c63-5351-4891-9b21-06752534c612> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Push/injection delivery: built, mechanically validated, AND evidence-supported — injecting the record took a local model 0.4→1.0 on the multi-module cache-gap task (the only condition that worked)" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/03393c63-5351-4891-9b21-06752534c612> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#supersedes> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/3e69bae9-fe9c-44fd-8882-a4b1ae8c78ad> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/059b01b7-8d8b-493c-a3f1-ceb459eb2626> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/059b01b7-8d8b-493c-a3f1-ceb459eb2626> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Bootstrap skill rewritten to build a linked graph" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/059b01b7-8d8b-493c-a3f1-ceb459eb2626> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/059b01b7-8d8b-493c-a3f1-ceb459eb2626> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Realizes the rich-ADR capture model that Lessons 96456e40 (capture/tooling gap) and 3f807592 (ontology designed for rich ADRs, capture elicits none) identified as unbuilt. skills/bootstrap-existing-codebase.md now captures DECISION CLUSTERS — a decision plus its motivating Requirement, shaping Constraint, weighed Alternative, resulting Consequence, and concerned SystemComponent — and draws the typed edges with relate() per a predicate->endpoint map, which the write path now SHACL-validates (AD 73918962). Three new disciplines: (1) link-or-mint grounding for instance dedup (invariant #4) — recall same-kind, reuse the existing IRI or mint, biasing Requirement/Constraint toward reuse so they become multi-hop hubs; (2) anti-confabulation (evidence-or-skip per edge, prefer not-linking over guessing — invariant #6, since get_relevant_context tells agents to TRUST records); (3) verification that proves LINKAGE not mere validity — edge histogram, edge-type-matrix lint, orphan check, the 6 competency questions, and the MOOSEDEV_EXPAND_HOPS 2-vs-0 traversal A/B. Honesty point baked in: 0 SHACL violations does NOT prove a linked graph (the M3 validator never requires edges), so SPARQL/competency evidence is the acceptance bar. Next: pilot on burrow (separate store, fresh agent) to test that the skill alone produces structure on a repo we can validate." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/059b01b7-8d8b-493c-a3f1-ceb459eb2626> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/059b01b7-8d8b-493c-a3f1-ceb459eb2626> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-19T17:34:28.611853Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/059b01b7-8d8b-493c-a3f1-ceb459eb2626> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Bootstrap skill rewritten to build a LINKED graph (decision-cluster capture + relate() link phase + link-or-mint), with verification that proves linkage — not just 0 SHACL violations" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/07415633-e7f0-410b-9eec-2a7bf9fcff97> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/07415633-e7f0-410b-9eec-2a7bf9fcff97> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "In-anger trial: operational measurement protocol" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/07415633-e7f0-410b-9eec-2a7bf9fcff97> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/ce49a867-7ebc-41d5-879c-fa59eed3ae65> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/07415633-e7f0-410b-9eec-2a7bf9fcff97> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/07415633-e7f0-410b-9eec-2a7bf9fcff97> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Operational protocol (2026-06-24) that OPERATIONALIZES the in-anger trial AD d3d4d7b1 — the concrete HOW for measuring whether structured memory reduces comprehension debt over months on trivyn + moose.\n\nSTORES (per-project, isolated by MOOSEDEV_DATA_DIR): trivyn = ~/.moosedev-stores/trivyn-trial (the temporally-bootstrapped trivyn-temporal store, COPIED then CAUGHT UP to live HEAD via a --resume git-walk: +9 records over 6 new commits, validate Conforms:true); moose = ~/.moosedev-stores/moose-trial (bootstrapped FROM SCRATCH via temporal_bootstrap.py, codex/gpt-5.4-mini, ~55 decision-bearing episodes). From month-0 the graphs grow by LIVE in-anger capture during real work (the thesis under test) — NOT scheduled git-walks (which would confound the signal; an optional quarterly --resume reconciliation is kept distinct).\n\nHEADLINE METRIC: per context_recovery probe, per month, gap = judge(B2 with graph) − judge(B0 cold). B0 runs against the EVOLVING current-HEAD working tree (trial corpora pin NO sha; rationale-bearing docs excluded via agent_exclude so B0 cannot cheat); B2 runs against the GROWING current graph. PREDICTION: B0 decays as rationale recedes from the tree while B2 holds — the WIDENING gap is the comprehension-debt signal the frozen-snapshot benchmark structurally could not produce (Lesson 8a06ad1d). A probe whose why stays locally recoverable is a NULL for that probe (Lesson a80bbe88) — reported, never spun.\n\nPROBES: ~8-12 per project, type context_recovery, reusing the bench task-JSON schema; FROZEN before month 1, only ADDED never revised; gold answers authored from PRIMARY sources (git/PRs/maintainer knowledge), NEVER the in-graph record (no circularity — AD 47f3f038, Lesson 440abc78).\n\nGRADING: blind strict LLM-judge (bench/regrade_judge.py, 'same specific answer, not same topic'), judge BLIND to which arm produced the answer; VALIDATE the judge by requiring it to reproduce a known-good arm's score before trusting deltas (Lesson a6529240).\n\nFIRING TALLY: auto-captured into each project graph as bare InformationRecord events titled [trial-fire]/[trial-miss] — align_concepts found NO fitting class (telemetry is not architectural knowledge), so no new ontology class is coined (invariants #4/#11). Each fire MUST cite the recalled record IRI(s) and assert the answer was NOT in the already-open files (no citation ⇒ not a fire). MISSES logged too (recall unhelpful, or a re-derivation the graph should have carried but lacked). Tally = fires AND misses (invariant #6); counted monthly per project via SPARQL on the title prefix.\n\nBIAS GUARDS (chosen by maintainer): automated B0-vs-B2 probes + blind LLM-judge + frozen pre-registration. NO deliberate hold-out — the cold B0 arm is the standing 'without graph' control, so a hold-out would only handicap a real project for redundant evidence.\n\nKILL CONDITION: see companion frozen-threshold Constraint. VERIFICATION GUARD: a dead MCP masquerades as a memory miss (Lesson 0a890ea9) — every probe/fire run must confirm get_relevant_context actually fired (tool_counts), else the datum is void. CADENCE: monthly through ~Q3 2026. Plan file: bubbly-giggling-balloon." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/07415633-e7f0-410b-9eec-2a7bf9fcff97> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/07415633-e7f0-410b-9eec-2a7bf9fcff97> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-24T07:26:55.749875Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/07415633-e7f0-410b-9eec-2a7bf9fcff97> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "In-anger trial: operational measurement protocol" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/07415633-e7f0-410b-9eec-2a7bf9fcff97> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#isMotivatedBy> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/4ab93555-0d8d-4bb5-abf5-ce3241f2be90> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/0d81e237-be84-46e8-b6fd-3bf866d0d73f> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/0d81e237-be84-46e8-b6fd-3bf866d0d73f> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Shared backend over Unix-socket MCP" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/0d81e237-be84-46e8-b6fd-3bf866d0d73f> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/0d81e237-be84-46e8-b6fd-3bf866d0d73f> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Problem: the durable KG is RocksDB-backed (oxigraph Store), which is single-writer and takes an exclusive directory lock. With the per-client stdio-subprocess model, a second MCP client (e.g. Codex alongside Claude Code) fails at Store::open during bootstrap; main() returns Err and exits before serve(stdio()), so the client never gets an initialize response — observed as a \"handshake fail on startup\". open_read_only is documented as undefined behavior while another process writes and would not permit captures anyway; moose::initialize and load_ontologies both write on every startup, so sharing one RocksDB across processes is impossible.\n\nDecision: introduce a single shared backend process that owns the store; multiple MCP clients talk to it. Build the CORE first (manual lifecycle): one binary, three modes — default stdio (unchanged, backward compatible), --serve (backend owning the store, listening on a Unix domain socket, serving MCP per accepted connection over rmcp's async-rw transport on a shared Arc<AppState>), and --connect (a transparent bidirectional byte relay between stdin/stdout and the socket — no MCP parsing). Concurrency is type-safe: EntityIndexCache is Send+Sync and assert_instance writes through a RocksDB transaction.\n\nMulti-project isolation: the socket path is derived per data dir (default $MOOSEDEV_DATA_DIR/moosedev.sock, with a hashed-path fallback for the macOS ~104-char sun_path limit), so each project gets its own backend + store + socket with no cross-talk. A fixed/global socket or TCP port was rejected precisely because it would cross-wire projects.\n\nDeferred to a later infra pass (auto-spawn daemon): detached spawn so the backend outlives the spawning client, idle-shutdown by connected-client refcount, a version handshake to restart a stale/outdated daemon, --status/--stop, and a daemon log file. Rationale for core-first: prove the shared-backend design with minimal, low-risk code before investing in lifecycle automation." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/0d81e237-be84-46e8-b6fd-3bf866d0d73f> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/0d81e237-be84-46e8-b6fd-3bf866d0d73f> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-17T22:10:28.452807Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/0d81e237-be84-46e8-b6fd-3bf866d0d73f> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Shared backend over Unix-socket MCP for concurrent multi-client access" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/0dddde16-e3eb-4e5d-89b3-825f813b4361> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/0dddde16-e3eb-4e5d-89b3-825f813b4361> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Embedded frontend default with explicit headless override" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/0dddde16-e3eb-4e5d-89b3-825f813b4361> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/8d48edbd-7ee2-4a52-9eac-f2a09c858637> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/0dddde16-e3eb-4e5d-89b3-825f813b4361> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "codex" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/0dddde16-e3eb-4e5d-89b3-825f813b4361> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Default Cargo builds now embed the MOOSEDev web UI, and backend-only builds opt into an explicit headless feature. This removes the prior release-build footgun where a plain `cargo build --release` silently produced a UI-less binary. `embedded-frontend` is now in the default feature set; `headless` is an explicit override so `cargo build --features headless` and `cargo check --all-features` compile the non-embedded static fallback, while `cargo build --release --no-default-features --features headless` remains the lean backend-only path that does not require `ui/dist`. The release script still builds `ui/dist` first, then uses the default Cargo build." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/0dddde16-e3eb-4e5d-89b3-825f813b4361> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/0dddde16-e3eb-4e5d-89b3-825f813b4361> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-24T02:16:15.330789Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/0dddde16-e3eb-4e5d-89b3-825f813b4361> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Embedded frontend default with explicit headless override" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/12af039b-1e77-47ce-97d9-0880a38f9cb1> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/12af039b-1e77-47ce-97d9-0880a38f9cb1> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "PUSH memory delivery via opencode plugin" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/12af039b-1e77-47ce-97d9-0880a38f9cb1> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/12af039b-1e77-47ce-97d9-0880a38f9cb1> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "The value benchmark established that agent-initiated PULL of memory (the model choosing to call get_relevant_context / an MCP recall tool) is unreliable for the local/self-hosted models MOOSEDev targets, so the symbolic layer must PUSH relevant records into the agent's context rather than wait to be queried (invariant #1: the LLM is a sensor, not the controller of retrieval). Decision: build a PUSH mechanism that proactively injects the records relevant to the current work into the model's context each turn. First implementation = an opencode plugin (opencode is the harness where local models actually run; Claude Code / Codex users mostly run the providers' frontier models, which already pull). Design: hook tool.execute.after to track the working set (files/symbols the agent reads/edits) as a deterministic retrieval key, and experimental.chat.system.transform to PREPEND the relevant get_relevant_context records to the SYSTEM PROMPT (context head — survives LM Studio TruncateMiddle; no tool call required). Keyed by a SHORT focused topic (concise topics retrieve at rank 1; the verbose task prompt diluted the right record to rank 5), lean top-K, dedup injected IRIs across turns, graceful no-op if the store is unreachable. This is \"oracle mode as a product\": oracle (harness-injected context) scored 1.0 where pull scored 0.4 on the same weakest model. Extends the value-benchmark AD 47f3f038 and the opencode-driver AD f45cf655; serves invariants #1 and #9 (local-first)." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/12af039b-1e77-47ce-97d9-0880a38f9cb1> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "superseded" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/12af039b-1e77-47ce-97d9-0880a38f9cb1> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-19T02:48:51.21287Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/12af039b-1e77-47ce-97d9-0880a38f9cb1> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "MOOSEDev needs a PUSH delivery mechanism for memory; first implementation is an opencode plugin" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/136dbf24-e8aa-4dd3-9eac-9fc8ac03296b> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/136dbf24-e8aa-4dd3-9eac-9fc8ac03296b> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Code entity identity: continuants with commit-anchored snapshots" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/136dbf24-e8aa-4dd3-9eac-9fc8ac03296b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/136dbf24-e8aa-4dd3-9eac-9fc8ac03296b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Claim: a code entity is a CONTINUANT identified by symbol path + kind (SCIP's symbol grammar is the prior art to adopt), persisting through edits; volatile facts (content hash, line span, metrics) live on commit-anchored SNAPSHOTS. Judgments, contracts, and intent links attach to the continuant; observations attach to snapshots. Refactor continuity is typed edges — renamedFrom/movedFrom/splitInto/mergedInto — the code-level analogue of supersession, reusing the existing lifecycle machinery (deprecated ≈ superseded). NOTHING in the graph is anchored by line number. Why: every other axis of the code layer is worthless if entity IRIs die on rebase — rationale must follow code through renames or capture rots at exactly the rate the code evolves. Migration path: v1 records' prose file:line citations (70 of 674 records as of 2026-07-03) are parseable seeds the v2 bootstrap upgrades into entity links." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/136dbf24-e8aa-4dd3-9eac-9fc8ac03296b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/136dbf24-e8aa-4dd3-9eac-9fc8ac03296b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-07-03T22:18:00.58532Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/136dbf24-e8aa-4dd3-9eac-9fc8ac03296b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Code entity identity: continuants with commit-anchored snapshots" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/136dbf24-e8aa-4dd3-9eac-9fc8ac03296b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#isMotivatedBy> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/350c7f2e-61bd-49e4-b7cd-2fdd3f51f521> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/136dbf24-e8aa-4dd3-9eac-9fc8ac03296b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#resultsIn> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Consequence/3753bf09-cb61-4e57-b7d1-e15a70c3de01> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/136dbf24-e8aa-4dd3-9eac-9fc8ac03296b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#resultsIn> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Consequence/aed3015e-a52a-4bbc-815e-4c89ead81971> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/136dbf24-e8aa-4dd3-9eac-9fc8ac03296b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#weighs> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Alternative/789df212-e666-4eb5-8465-526a44a39e11> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/136dbf24-e8aa-4dd3-9eac-9fc8ac03296b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#weighs> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Alternative/c5fd1925-a8a9-4000-93e5-0cd0b02924d5> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/145af7e9-c8ad-40e1-91ab-e4442d861733> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/145af7e9-c8ad-40e1-91ab-e4442d861733> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Active memory participant, not passive tool" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/145af7e9-c8ad-40e1-91ab-e4442d861733> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/145af7e9-c8ad-40e1-91ab-e4442d861733> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Foundational integration-architecture decision. MCP is client-initiated (passive): the agent calls a tool and the server answers; the server cannot act on its own. This single property is the shared ROOT of the two failures the benchmark measured — PULL fails (a passive tool waits to be called; local models don't call it — Lesson 2dcca5ff) AND CAPTURE is flat (a passive tool can only validate what it is handed; it cannot ELICIT the rationale/motivation the rich-ADR ontology anticipates — Lessons 3f807592 / 96456e40). A passive tool can CHECK structure but cannot ASK FOR it. DECISION: MOOSEDev's center of gravity is an ACTIVE memory participant in the agent loop. Architecture split: (1) MCP remains the SYMBOLIC OPERATIONS API (get_relevant_context, record_important_decision, relate, supersede, retract, sparql, validate) — passive but correct; (2) an ACTIVE-AGENCY layer drives WHEN those operations fire — proactively PUSHING relevant context into the agent (already prototyped: the opencode push plugin, AD 03393c63, which observes tool.execute and injects) and driving CAPTURE at decision-points. CAPTURE MUST BE GROUNDED to avoid LLM confabulation (invariant #6): prefer EXTRACTING the decision + rationale from what the agent actually did (diff/transcript) over interrogating the LLM to justify itself; CONSTRAIN isMotivatedBy to link an EXISTING Requirement (the agent picks from recorded ones, cannot invent — invariant #1 fences the LLM); let the USER CONFIRM the captured ADR (invariant #9). ACP / agent-communication protocols are a FUTURE option for making the active layer portable/host-independent, NOT a prerequisite — the plugin gives proactivity today (opencode hooks; Claude Code has equivalents). MCP's own server-initiated features (sampling, elicitation) give only CONDITIONAL interrogation (bootstrapped by an agent-initiated tool call; thin/inconsistent client support), not genuine initiative — it cannot watch the agent and jump in. Through-line consistent with the evidence: push (active delivery) >> pull (passive) is proven; by the same logic active capture (observe + extract) >> passive capture (hope the agent volunteers structure). Extends push AD 03393c63 and relate() AD d542b826; motivated by Lessons 2dcca5ff, 3f807592, aaee7652." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/145af7e9-c8ad-40e1-91ab-e4442d861733> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/145af7e9-c8ad-40e1-91ab-e4442d861733> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-19T15:11:31.12331Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/145af7e9-c8ad-40e1-91ab-e4442d861733> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "MOOSEDev is an ACTIVE memory PARTICIPANT, not a passive MCP tool: split MCP (symbolic operations) from an active-agency layer (plugin now, ACP-style later) that pushes context and drives GROUNDED capture" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/145af7e9-c8ad-40e1-91ab-e4442d861733> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#isMotivatedBy> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/350c7f2e-61bd-49e4-b7cd-2fdd3f51f521> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/14f8fe4d-702f-4b14-8db0-592bb0deebe7> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/14f8fe4d-702f-4b14-8db0-592bb0deebe7> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "--connect auto-spawns the matching detached backend" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/14f8fe4d-702f-4b14-8db0-592bb0deebe7> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "codex-mcp-client" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/14f8fe4d-702f-4b14-8db0-592bb0deebe7> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Decision: `moosedev --connect` now auto-spawns the current executable as `--serve <resolved-socket>` when no backend is listening on the resolved per-data-dir Unix socket, unless `MOOSEDEV_NO_AUTOSPAWN` is set to a non-empty non-0 value. The detached backend inherits the caller environment and cwd, redirects stdin to null and stdout/stderr to `<data_dir>/moosedev-serve.log`, writes `<data_dir>/moosedev-serve.pid` from serve mode, and handles SIGTERM through the same socket cleanup path as ctrl-c. Rationale: the previous manual lifecycle let clients and manually started daemons disagree on `MOOSEDEV_DATA_DIR`, producing a false \"backend is running but connect fails\" outage. Spawning from the proxy with the already-resolved socket removes that mismatch while keeping the MCP stdout channel byte-clean and preserving an opt-out for explicit lifecycle control. Verification: `cargo test --test autospawn`, `cargo check`, `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features`, and full `cargo test` passed." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/14f8fe4d-702f-4b14-8db0-592bb0deebe7> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/14f8fe4d-702f-4b14-8db0-592bb0deebe7> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-18T02:43:05.713168Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/14f8fe4d-702f-4b14-8db0-592bb0deebe7> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "--connect auto-spawns the matching detached backend" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/14f8fe4d-702f-4b14-8db0-592bb0deebe7> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#isMotivatedBy> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/ea2a00f5-e654-4589-91df-40448b5d7bab> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/1a4983b8-f254-4e56-b674-4eaae9a83641> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/1a4983b8-f254-4e56-b674-4eaae9a83641> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Shared export core across CLI/MCP/HTTP/UI" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/1a4983b8-f254-4e56-b674-4eaae9a83641> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "codex-mcp-client" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/1a4983b8-f254-4e56-b674-4eaae9a83641> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Implemented the export half of Requirement d459cac2. A new shared export core bulk-reads only the project/provenance named graphs, sorts quads deterministically by graph/subject/predicate/object, and serializes N-Quads canonically while supporting N-Triples/Turtle as graph-format exports that intentionally strip named graph identity. Thin surfaces call the same core: `moosedev export`, MCP `export_graph`, GET `/api/v1/graph/export`, and a SPARQL-page UI download control. Import/load-from-text, RocksDB cache rebuild, committed kg.nq, and gitignore changes remain deferred." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/1a4983b8-f254-4e56-b674-4eaae9a83641> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/1a4983b8-f254-4e56-b674-4eaae9a83641> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-20T18:34:15.473103Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/1a4983b8-f254-4e56-b674-4eaae9a83641> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Implement graph export as shared core with CLI, MCP, HTTP, and UI surfaces" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/1a4983b8-f254-4e56-b674-4eaae9a83641> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#isMotivatedBy> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/d459cac2-09f6-4f7b-b959-0f5337d6c5f4> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/1b590815-c9ab-4fff-b2a6-69df3ba7c997> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
