<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/1b590815-c9ab-4fff-b2a6-69df3ba7c997> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/1b590815-c9ab-4fff-b2a6-69df3ba7c997> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Claim: the v2 code-layer vocabulary lives in a NEW ontology module — ontologies/software-code.ttl + software-code_shapes.ttl, namespace https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/code# — not in software-engineering.ttl. CodeEntity ⊑ se:Component preserves AD b0d3e4d9's ratified Component/Module lineage via cross-ontology subclassing (arch precedent: SystemComponent ⊑ se:Component); this refines b0d3e4d9's letter (\"mint in the software-engineering ontology\") while keeping its substance. Scope discipline: v2.0 loads CodeEntity fully modeled (five datatype properties: hasScipSymbol identity key with version descriptor elided per Constraint 00b3986e, hasEntityKind as a DATATYPE property — kind taxonomy belongs to the index producer, not a class hierarchy — hasCodeName label property, hasLogicalPath, definedInPath; one CodeEntityShape validating integrity not editorial completeness) PLUS the seven other stratum classes ratified in the 2026-07-03 alignment pass (CodeFile, CodeSnapshot, CodeRole, Criticality, AttentionPolicy, Observation, AuthorshipProvenance) PARKED as bare declarations — no properties, no shapes, hence no relation-catalogue write paths before their strata's machinery ships (judgments: v2.1 ratification inbox; observations: v2.2 instrumentation). Intent links realizes/satisfies/embodies (+ is-X-by inverses) are declared CODE-side: the dependent module links upward into architecture; software-architecture.ttl takes only in-place widenings of its own generic predicates (concerns/isConcernedBy, constrains/isConstrainedBy, violates/isViolatedBy via dcam includes + sh:or unions in its shapes — SHACL unions cannot be relaxed additively from another file, so this cross-reference is the unavoidable minimum). Path map: the align_concepts/property-inventory arbitration anticipated by Consequence 224af324 resolved to REUSING the existing coversPath (exact prefix semantics already recorded and seeded on 9 components); hasPathGlob was not minted. Curation provenance: hand-curated 2026-07-08 from a Trivyn v0.8.4 generation; overruled generator alignments recorded in the file's editorial note (CodeEntity ⊑ arch:SystemComponent, CodeFile ⊑ se:Module, AuthorshipProvenance ⊑ se:ExternalDependency, duplicate record-layer classes bridged by owl:equivalentClass which the relation machinery cannot reason over, CodeKind class, RefactorEvent class vs the ratified typed continuity edges)." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/1b590815-c9ab-4fff-b2a6-69df3ba7c997> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
