<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/1c331df7-b89e-499f-9bf1-9c562bfea13c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/1c331df7-b89e-499f-9bf1-9c562bfea13c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "The release workflow previously packaged ONLY the binary + LICENSE + README, so a downloaded build could not start: ontologies/ (4 .ttl domain+SHACL files) is read from disk at startup by ontology::load_ontologies, and the deployed binary's ontology_dir() fell back to env!(\"CARGO_MANIFEST_DIR\")/ontologies — the CI build path, which does not exist on a user's machine — so it only worked if the user manually set MOOSEDEV_ONTOLOGY_DIR. Fix has two halves: (1) .github/workflows/release.yml Package step now copies ontologies/ (REQUIRED runtime resource) plus skills/ and templates/ (agent-facing bootstrap workflows + the CLAUDE.md adoption template — companion resources, not read by the binary) into the dist dir. examples/ (internal .rs probes) and spec/ (design docs) are intentionally NOT shipped. (2) src/main.rs ontology_dir() now resolves in priority order: MOOSEDEV_ONTOLOGY_DIR override -> ontologies/ next to std::env::current_exe() (the tarball layout, zero-config) -> crate's ontologies/ (dev/cargo run, where the binary is under target/). The web UI needs no shipping — it is embedded at compile time via include_dir! under the default embedded-frontend feature (AD 0dddde16). Verified: cargo build/test green (new unit test ontology_dir_resolves covers all 3 branches incl. exe-relative), and an end-to-end boot from a simulated tarball with MOOSEDEV_ONTOLOGY_DIR UNSET loaded the ontologies (\"built ontology vector store: 36 vectors\") and served cleanly. README's MOOSEDEV_ONTOLOGY_DIR doc updated to describe the exe-relative default and to note the unpacked bundle must be kept together." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/1c331df7-b89e-499f-9bf1-9c562bfea13c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/1c331df7-b89e-499f-9bf1-9c562bfea13c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-25T04:37:10.503122Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/1c331df7-b89e-499f-9bf1-9c562bfea13c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Release tarball bundles ontologies/skills/templates; binary resolves ontologies next to itself" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/1f749613-6ec4-481f-8a43-2d1c050d89b8> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/1f749613-6ec4-481f-8a43-2d1c050d89b8> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Instrument per-query NLQ token usage" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/1f749613-6ec4-481f-8a43-2d1c050d89b8> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/f4d2f589-8f00-4640-ae16-fbb0184cb365> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/1f749613-6ec4-481f-8a43-2d1c050d89b8> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/1f749613-6ec4-481f-8a43-2d1c050d89b8> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Phase 1 of the value benchmark. MOOSE's LlmClient trait returns only the completion string, so OpenAiCompatClient (src/llm/mod.rs) now accumulates usage.prompt_tokens/completion_tokens via interior mutability (Arc<UsageCounters> of two AtomicU64), populated in chat_completion from the response body. Added with_fresh_usage() (a clone sharing the HTTP pool but with FRESH counters) and take_usage() (read + reset). graph::query() forks the client per call so token counts attribute to exactly one query even under concurrent shared-backend use, then appends a machine-parseable 'tokens: prompt=X completion=Y' line to the rendered trace. This lets the benchmark attribute B2's INTERNAL NLQ cost (which B1's embedding retrieval does not incur) for an honest total-cost comparison. No MOOSE change needed: the NLQ LLM calls route back through our chat_completion sensor (execute_graph_walk_nlq_with_context is passed &state.llm), so this stays within the open boundary (invariants #8, #11). Verified: 3 new unit tests (accumulate/reset, missing-fields→0, fork isolation), cargo clippy --all-targets clean, full cargo test suite green." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/1f749613-6ec4-481f-8a43-2d1c050d89b8> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/1f749613-6ec4-481f-8a43-2d1c050d89b8> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-18T15:19:32.540109Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/1f749613-6ec4-481f-8a43-2d1c050d89b8> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Instrument per-query NLQ token usage in the LLM client; surface in the query trace" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/228b272c-bd92-489c-9734-dcb95b060de2> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/228b272c-bd92-489c-9734-dcb95b060de2> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "v2 code ontology: separate software/code# module generated via Trivyn, brief as input-of-record" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/228b272c-bd92-489c-9734-dcb95b060de2> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/228b272c-bd92-489c-9734-dcb95b060de2> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Claim: the v2 code-layer ontology terms (the 8 alignment-cleared classes: CodeEntity, CodeSnapshot, CodeFile, CodeRole, Criticality, AttentionPolicy, Observation, AuthorshipProvenance) are minted as a SEPARATE module generated by Trivyn's ontology pipeline — hash-style namespace https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/code# with shapes at …/software/code/shapes# (per AD f68ef43e) — which IMPORTS and specializes the software-engineering module under its Component/Module lineage, rather than growing the shipped software-engineering TTL in place. This occupies the extension seam the v1 architecture-ontology brief reserved ('language-specific (deferred) — specializes SE'), generalized to language-AGNOSTIC: language specifics live in the SCIP substrate identity scheme, never in the ontology. The generation input-of-record is spec/code-ontology-brief.md (structure mirrors spec/architecture-ontology-brief.md): it fixes layering, the 8 classes by stratum, seed relations (playsRole/hasCriticality carrying status+provenance, declaredIn crossing the two containment hierarchies, refactor-continuity edges, hasSnapshot/observedIn, intent links realizes/satisfies/embodies, constrains/violates widened), per-stratum SHACL posture, and the paste-ready domain-hint prompt (§9) for the generator; it defers to the generator the BFO grounding of CodeEntity vs CodeSnapshot, reification vs RDF-star for status-carrying assertions, and kind/exposure as designators vs shallow subclasses. Encodes, does not re-litigate: ADs b0d3e4d9 (three strata), b5b4762b (role taxonomy, ratified 2026-07-06), 136dbf24 (entity identity), 7079634f (intent links), and the 2026-07-03 alignment pass (reuse Interface/InterfaceDefinition/Module/DataStore/Constraint and dependsOn/implements/uses/accesses/exposes; never re-mint)." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/228b272c-bd92-489c-9734-dcb95b060de2> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/228b272c-bd92-489c-9734-dcb95b060de2> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-07-08T04:22:28.201128Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
