<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/233f460f-4f5c-4ac2-9e28-1405b6acf1a2> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "ADR generation uses a checked-in script fast path" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/233f460f-4f5c-4ac2-9e28-1405b6acf1a2> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/402e5c0b-dc22-4063-84c6-6b9dd954d540> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/233f460f-4f5c-4ac2-9e28-1405b6acf1a2> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "codex" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/233f460f-4f5c-4ac2-9e28-1405b6acf1a2> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "ADR generation now uses `scripts/generate-adrs-from-graph.py` as the checked-in fast path, with `skills/generate-adrs-from-graph.md` retained as the behavioral contract and manual fallback. The script implements the skill's read-only COUNT -> enumerate -> batched cluster SPARQL workflow against the local HTTP backend, writes `docs/adr/`, and verifies coverage/lifecycle integrity. Rationale: renderer logic is nontrivial enough that one-off agent scripts would drift in status mapping, supersession handling, markdown shape, and verification; a shared generator keeps the regenerable ADR view deterministic while preserving the graph as the source of truth." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/233f460f-4f5c-4ac2-9e28-1405b6acf1a2> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
