<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/2501ffa4-42d9-4d23-9185-e191ca70ea63> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/2501ffa4-42d9-4d23-9185-e191ca70ea63> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Surface architecture: headless daemon, thin surfaces, no dedicated editor" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/2501ffa4-42d9-4d23-9185-e191ca70ea63> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/2501ffa4-42d9-4d23-9185-e191ca70ea63> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Claim: the harness is NOT a UI — it is the policy engine + graph running headless (the daemon already serves MCP and HTTP); every human surface is a thin projection scoped by altitude and frequency. (1) TUI agent harness — high-frequency / low-bandwidth: escalation prompts, quick cited queries, a pending-ratifications nudge. (2) Editors — the ambient layer via a KNOWLEDGE-LSP, not a language server: it annotates symbols and never parses (rust-analyzer keeps language intelligence; editors run multiple servers per buffer). hover = dossier; codeLens = role/criticality/debt badges; diagnostics = edit-time constraint + staleness checks; code actions = the write path, routed through the same ratification gate (no side door into the graph). (3) Workbench (the existing React UI) — low-frequency / high-bandwidth: ratification inbox, graph walking, debt heatmaps, trial dashboards; also the buyer-facing demo surface. (4) Per-editor extensions only as picture frames (VS Code webview embedding workbench views); Zed needs no bespoke extension — MCP covers its agent panel today, the LSP covers ambience. MCP and LSP are sibling JSON-RPC protocols served natively by the SAME daemon over the SAME queries — a correctness property: the human's hover and the agent's pushed dossier present the identical world model. Sequencing: read-only LSP slice (hover + diagnostics) first, code lens next, write-path code actions last." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/2501ffa4-42d9-4d23-9185-e191ca70ea63> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/2501ffa4-42d9-4d23-9185-e191ca70ea63> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-07-03T22:18:46.259879Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/2501ffa4-42d9-4d23-9185-e191ca70ea63> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Surface architecture: headless daemon, thin surfaces, no dedicated editor" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/2501ffa4-42d9-4d23-9185-e191ca70ea63> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#isMotivatedBy> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/350c7f2e-61bd-49e4-b7cd-2fdd3f51f521> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/2501ffa4-42d9-4d23-9185-e191ca70ea63> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#resultsIn> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Consequence/09ce698d-a82d-4347-b54e-f8c4656ec85c> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/2501ffa4-42d9-4d23-9185-e191ca70ea63> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#weighs> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Alternative/ad738979-2817-4101-9a9e-e877b16289cd> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/282378cd-4282-4ece-ae47-a391762f1c80> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/282378cd-4282-4ece-ae47-a391762f1c80> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Canonical write-through throttled: bursts coalesce to one trailing kg.nq export" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/282378cd-4282-4ece-ae47-a391762f1c80> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/282378cd-4282-4ece-ae47-a391762f1c80> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Refines the write policy of AD 013a9706 (committed canonical kg.nq), user-directed: bulk write flows must skip the per-write export until the very end. Mechanism (canonical::WriteThrottle, wired into AppState::note_project_write): a leading+trailing throttle with a 2s quiescence window. An ISOLATED write exports synchronously — kg.nq is commit-ready the moment the capture tool returns, preserving the interactive guarantee. Writes landing within the window of the previous one form a BURST (bootstrap replays of O(100-250) records, bulk captures): they skip the export entirely and set a single trailing tokio task that flushes once the burst goes quiet — O(1) exports per burst instead of O(N). The full-file re-export itself stays deliberately non-incremental (sorted deterministic snapshot; ~2k quads = milliseconds), so the throttle governs only WHEN it runs, not HOW. Contexts without a tokio runtime (CLI paths, sync tests) fall back to synchronous export per write. Failure/crash mid-burst is already covered: the stamp protocol's missed-export branch (store moved, text matches stamp) re-exports at the next boot — the reconciliation table was designed to make the write policy swappable without protocol change. Verified: 2 new unit tests (no-runtime sync fallback; burst defers mid-burst then one trailing flush lands everything), clippy -D warnings clean, full suite green." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/282378cd-4282-4ece-ae47-a391762f1c80> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/282378cd-4282-4ece-ae47-a391762f1c80> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-07-03T19:04:20.337722Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
