<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/282378cd-4282-4ece-ae47-a391762f1c80> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#weighs> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Alternative/ee8cb65e-143d-4293-baac-6f1dc96d27e9> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/2a778f74-725f-4cd7-a389-52f51888795e> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/2a778f74-725f-4cd7-a389-52f51888795e> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Default captures are accepted and requirements derive addressed state" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/2a778f74-725f-4cd7-a389-52f51888795e> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "codex" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/2a778f74-725f-4cd7-a389-52f51888795e> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "MOOSEDev now treats newly captured records without an explicit lifecycle status as accepted, not proposed, and requirements derive an addressed flag from live linked ADRs. The implementation keeps addressed as an API/rendering derivation instead of storing a new graph fact: a Requirement is addressed when at least one linked ArchitecturalDecision is not retired. Retired filtering is centralized through a shared retired-status helper used by relevant context, link warnings, and requirements rendering. A one-off migration normalizes legacy proposed ADR and Requirement defaults to accepted while leaving auxiliary nodes untouched." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/2a778f74-725f-4cd7-a389-52f51888795e> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/2a778f74-725f-4cd7-a389-52f51888795e> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-27T20:39:13.598439Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
