<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/30ec7728-73db-4483-a5e3-e2778fdd16df> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/30ec7728-73db-4483-a5e3-e2778fdd16df> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Atomic cluster capture and lossless artifact rendering" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/30ec7728-73db-4483-a5e3-e2778fdd16df> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "codex-mcp-client" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/30ec7728-73db-4483-a5e3-e2778fdd16df> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Cluster capture now commits the decision, inline relation edges, minted Alternative/Consequence nodes, and cluster edges in one transaction. ADR and Requirement artifact renderers now take AppState so queries resolve class and predicate IRIs from the loaded ontology/capture predicates, and they enumerate typed records even when display fields are missing rather than silently dropping incomplete records. ADR summaries use plain lifecycle labels while markdown detail pages may include successor links." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/30ec7728-73db-4483-a5e3-e2778fdd16df> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
