<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/346bb120-6855-421e-bb6b-1d778cfeb038> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/346bb120-6855-421e-bb6b-1d778cfeb038> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Optional LLM assistance; symbolic default without provider" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/346bb120-6855-421e-bb6b-1d778cfeb038> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "codex" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/346bb120-6855-421e-bb6b-1d778cfeb038> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "MOOSEDev's core memory server must be fully usable without an LLM provider; absent MOOSEDEV_LLM_BASE_URL pins assist level to PureSymbolic. The LLM remains an optional sensor for assisted NLQ/chat, not a runtime prerequisite for capture, get_relevant_context, sparql, validation, or symbolic query. Implementation: LlmConfig treats MOOSEDEV_LLM_BASE_URL as the opt-in flag, AppState records llm_configured and clamps the engine assist level to PureSymbolic when false, /health reports the effective LLM mode, and /chat returns 503 with an enablement message when no provider is configured. Verified with cargo check plus focused llm/query/API tests." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/346bb120-6855-421e-bb6b-1d778cfeb038> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/346bb120-6855-421e-bb6b-1d778cfeb038> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-23T20:16:48.444158Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
