<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/365adb90-86c1-4478-b06f-129ab628a407> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/365adb90-86c1-4478-b06f-129ab628a407> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Fire-event telemetry deferred to v2.2 (spec §4.4 amendment)" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/365adb90-86c1-4478-b06f-129ab628a407> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/6baa075c-db0d-48e0-800a-0cae86603b2a> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/365adb90-86c1-4478-b06f-129ab628a407> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/365adb90-86c1-4478-b06f-129ab628a407> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "The fires.jsonl append-only telemetry log (spec §4.4) is deferred from the v2.0 slice list to v2.2, where the events it records actually exist: push-fires and gate-fires are active-agency verbs, and v2.0 ships only read surfaces (hover, diagnostics). A writer with no writers would be dead scaffolding. When v2.2's policy engine lands, the log lands with its first caller. Decided by James 2026-07-09 during slice-3 planning; this record is the conscious amendment of the spec's letter." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/365adb90-86c1-4478-b06f-129ab628a407> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/365adb90-86c1-4478-b06f-129ab628a407> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-07-09T23:54:58.831873Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/365adb90-86c1-4478-b06f-129ab628a407> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Fire-event telemetry deferred to v2.2 (spec §4.4 amendment)" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/365adb90-86c1-4478-b06f-129ab628a407> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#resultsIn> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Consequence/6505ed72-0353-4b5b-9cc9-4039538f89e8> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/365adb90-86c1-4478-b06f-129ab628a407> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#weighs> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Alternative/5596d4f4-bbd6-42bd-8263-1b18e83de944> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/3b32fb25-1957-4f74-8d64-c70b250c8cae> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/3b32fb25-1957-4f74-8d64-c70b250c8cae> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Editor LSP surface is v2-gated; v1 capture becomes anchor-ready now" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/3b32fb25-1957-4f74-8d64-c70b250c8cae> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/3b32fb25-1957-4f74-8d64-c70b250c8cae> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Claim: do NOT ship the editor LSP on v1 capture; make v1 capture anchor-ready instead. Empirical basis (SPARQL, 2026-07-03): 674 records, of which 70 (~10%) cite any code path — as prose file:line that rots — and concerns → SystemComponent is effectively unused; a (file, position) → records resolver has nothing precise to resolve against, and the fallbacks (lexical/BM25 binding) are exactly the relevance-guessing the entity layer exists to eliminate. A sparse-and-fuzzy ambient surface triggers alarm fatigue: users disable it in week one and do not re-enable it when v2 makes it precise — shipping early spends the surface's one first impression on the weakest version of the product. Note: much of the store is legitimately code-locationless (trial protocols, benchmark designs) — not a capture failure; the code-locatable fraction grows only when capture is entity-anchored. V1 DISCIPLINES effective immediately: (a) mint concerns edges at capture time via a small path→SystemComponent map (~10 lines of config for this repo); (b) keep prose code citations as migration seeds for the v2 bootstrap's citation parser. In-editor PULL via Zed's MCP support is free and acceptable as a convenience, with pull's known limits. This is the month-0 lesson (56d142f9 — delivery value is capture-gated) recurring at the surface layer." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/3b32fb25-1957-4f74-8d64-c70b250c8cae> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/3b32fb25-1957-4f74-8d64-c70b250c8cae> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-07-03T22:19:07.680178Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/3b32fb25-1957-4f74-8d64-c70b250c8cae> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Editor LSP surface is v2-gated; v1 capture becomes anchor-ready now" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/3b32fb25-1957-4f74-8d64-c70b250c8cae> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#isMotivatedBy> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/350c7f2e-61bd-49e4-b7cd-2fdd3f51f521> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/3b32fb25-1957-4f74-8d64-c70b250c8cae> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#resultsIn> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Consequence/401c03d6-eb5a-4fcd-ab4b-3e8578089ffb> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
