<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/3b32fb25-1957-4f74-8d64-c70b250c8cae> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#weighs> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Alternative/272c2ce0-1715-42de-8450-9f78d021812d> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/3d091a06-a6d3-4ca8-9261-d8af349ed900> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/3d091a06-a6d3-4ca8-9261-d8af349ed900> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Graph import/export page with shared restore core" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/3d091a06-a6d3-4ca8-9261-d8af349ed900> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "codex-mcp-client" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/3d091a06-a6d3-4ca8-9261-d8af349ed900> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Graph import now uses a shared RDF import core exposed through UI, HTTP API, and CLI. The implementation keeps N-Quads as the dataset backup/restore format that preserves project/provenance named graphs, while TTL/N-Triples are single-target graph imports. PATCH inserts only missing quads, REPLACE removes the selected MOOSEDev-owned scope and inserts the parsed import in one transaction, and invalid project imports fail before mutation. The SPARQL UI is now query-only; graph transfer lives on a dedicated Import / Export page with typed RESTORE confirmation for replace mode." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/3d091a06-a6d3-4ca8-9261-d8af349ed900> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/3d091a06-a6d3-4ca8-9261-d8af349ed900> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-24T20:02:57.891258Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/3d091a06-a6d3-4ca8-9261-d8af349ed900> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Graph import/export page with shared restore core" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/3d091a06-a6d3-4ca8-9261-d8af349ed900> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#isMotivatedBy> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/d459cac2-09f6-4f7b-b959-0f5337d6c5f4> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/3e69bae9-fe9c-44fd-8882-a4b1ae8c78ad> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/3e69bae9-fe9c-44fd-8882-a4b1ae8c78ad> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Push delivery built and mechanically validated, value unproven" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/3e69bae9-fe9c-44fd-8882-a4b1ae8c78ad> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/3e69bae9-fe9c-44fd-8882-a4b1ae8c78ad> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Corrected status of the push mechanism. BUILT + MECHANICALLY VALIDATED: the opencode plugin (.opencode/plugins/moosedev-push.ts) loads in headless `opencode run` (from the project CWD, not --dir), all hooks fire (tool.execute.after, experimental.chat.system.transform/messages.transform), MOOSEDEV_DATA_DIR resolves, and after four fixes — symbol-keyed retrieval (records are indexed by symbol e.g. SchemaTriple, not file path), per-turn injection (cross-turn IRI dedup wrongly let an auxiliary hook call consume the record before the real turn), session-set aggregation (opencode passes a different sessionID than tool.execute.after sees), and noise-filter + round-robin per-symbol retrieval — it injects the correct rank-1 record into the model's system prompt (confirmed reaching the prompt 40–52x; offline-verified the cache-gap lesson lands rank-1). VALUE UNPROVEN: on the execution-heavy cache-gap task, delivery is irrelevant because local models hit an execution ceiling (Lesson 5a0e66fe) — they never make the cross-module edits even with the lesson in-prompt (oracle) and even dense-27b+thinking. Push/pull value for local models must therefore be tested on RECALL/Q&A + simple single-edit tasks within local execution capability (pending: whynot_tlo_merge). Push remains sound in principle per invariant #1 (the symbolic layer injects rather than relying on the LLM to pull), but is NOT yet shown to deliver measurable value. Extends value-benchmark AD 47f3f038 / opencode-driver AD f45cf655." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/3e69bae9-fe9c-44fd-8882-a4b1ae8c78ad> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "superseded" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/3e69bae9-fe9c-44fd-8882-a4b1ae8c78ad> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasRationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/7a911f2e-d44b-4ec3-92b6-6ee696119fac> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/3e69bae9-fe9c-44fd-8882-a4b1ae8c78ad> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-19T05:00:12.319849Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/3e69bae9-fe9c-44fd-8882-a4b1ae8c78ad> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Push delivery (opencode plugin) is built and MECHANICALLY validated; its VALUE for local models is unproven — execution ceiling on code tasks, pending on recall tasks" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/3e69bae9-fe9c-44fd-8882-a4b1ae8c78ad> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#supersedes> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/12af039b-1e77-47ce-97d9-0880a38f9cb1> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/43446e69-4b6c-4553-a478-8748a03da699> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/43446e69-4b6c-4553-a478-8748a03da699> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Cache ontology vector store across startups (fingerprint-gated rebuild)" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/43446e69-4b6c-4553-a478-8748a03da699> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/43446e69-4b6c-4553-a478-8748a03da699> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "vectors::build_and_open now reuses the persisted ontology-vectors.db instead of rebuilding it on every backend startup. Reuse requires (1) an ontology content fingerprint — a hash over every (iri, element_type, embed-text) tuple, stored in a sidecar file — matching the current ontology, AND (2) VecStore::open succeeding, which validates the embedding-model stamp against the compiled-in model_id::ACTIVE (so a model change forces a rebuild). Rationale: the shipped ontology only changes on a version bump, so the unconditional backbone load + re-embed was pure waste in steady state (~10s cold vs ~16ms warm, measured). Fingerprint is written only after a successful stamp so a crash mid-build can't leave a fresh-looking store. The embed inputs are collected once and used for both the fingerprint and the build, so the cache key can't drift from what is embedded." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/43446e69-4b6c-4553-a478-8748a03da699> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/43446e69-4b6c-4553-a478-8748a03da699> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-17T23:14:03.146902Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/43446e69-4b6c-4553-a478-8748a03da699> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Cache ontology vector store across startups (fingerprint-gated rebuild)" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/4569aede-d490-4998-b5f0-83d1e2f16445> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/4569aede-d490-4998-b5f0-83d1e2f16445> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Adopt Core label-designator contract" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/4569aede-d490-4998-b5f0-83d1e2f16445> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/11e01ea2-f520-4f7c-a165-09532dacd43f> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/4569aede-d490-4998-b5f0-83d1e2f16445> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/3193c9a7-8f50-4af0-b0b6-f05ebaa23393> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/4569aede-d490-4998-b5f0-83d1e2f16445> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "mcp" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/4569aede-d490-4998-b5f0-83d1e2f16445> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "MOOSEDev consumes MOOSE Core's deterministic label-shape verdict to fix the long-label retrieval pathology at runtime. EngineConfig.label_shape defaults to 80 chars / 8 words / sentence-break-on (src/graph/mod.rs); content-shaped labels forfeit the 2x BM25F title boost (de-saturation) and skip the fuzzy name-resolution tiers (no false-substring matches), while exact / case-insensitive match still resolves at any length. The EntityIndexCache self-defaults to the same thresholds, so the direct search_records_hybrid path (graph/mod.rs:1452) is correct without extra wiring at the default; tuning below 80/8 would need state.entity_index.set_label_shape(cfg) at bootstrap. Verified on the live dogfood store via examples/audit_labels.rs: 136 labels, 121 content-shaped (89%). This downgrades the bulk relabel from a retrieval fix to optional data hygiene." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/4569aede-d490-4998-b5f0-83d1e2f16445> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/4569aede-d490-4998-b5f0-83d1e2f16445> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-21T18:47:56.866226Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/4569aede-d490-4998-b5f0-83d1e2f16445> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Adopt Core label-designator contract" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/4729eb4f-c864-4c47-baaf-77bf52e7a602> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/4729eb4f-c864-4c47-baaf-77bf52e7a602> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "CodeEntity skeleton lives in the project graph, committed via canonical kg.nq" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/4729eb4f-c864-4c47-baaf-77bf52e7a602> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/11e01ea2-f520-4f7c-a165-09532dacd43f> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/4729eb4f-c864-4c47-baaf-77bf52e7a602> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "phase7-acceptance" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/4729eb4f-c864-4c47-baaf-77bf52e7a602> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Minted CodeEntity continuants are first-class members of kg/project and ride the canonical write-through export; RocksDB and vector stores remain derived, gitignored cache. Record-to-entity intent links must survive fresh clones with stable IRIs (re-minting per clone would sever every committed link), kg.nq diffs stay reviewable adds-only, and dossier/relation reads stay single-graph. Evidence from the 2026-07-08 acceptance run: mint --apply added 6995 canonical lines (905 entities) with zero deletions; re-run and re-index+re-run both produced an empty plan; a scratch rename produced exactly 1 create + 1 orphan report with the other 904 IRIs untouched." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/4729eb4f-c864-4c47-baaf-77bf52e7a602> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
