<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/4729eb4f-c864-4c47-baaf-77bf52e7a602> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#weighs> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Alternative/ea239aef-5711-487c-9d6e-c51f97ba15d9> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/47f3f038-8fd7-4a96-9c74-15a24bf8be17> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/47f3f038-8fd7-4a96-9c74-15a24bf8be17> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "B0/B1/B2 benchmark arms with content parity" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/47f3f038-8fd7-4a96-9c74-15a24bf8be17> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/ce49a867-7ebc-41d5-879c-fa59eed3ae65> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/47f3f038-8fd7-4a96-9c74-15a24bf8be17> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/47f3f038-8fd7-4a96-9c74-15a24bf8be17> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Design of record for the MOOSEDev value benchmark (bench/). Three arms differing ONLY in memory: B0 cold (working tree), B1 free-text RAG, B2 the live MOOSEDev graph (get_relevant_context/query/sparql). Headline metric is B2 − B1 (structured beats free-text); B2 − B0 is the trivial floor. Fairness rests on CONTENT PARITY — B1's text corpus is exported from the SAME graph B2 reads, so representation is the only difference. The agent-under-test (swept across model sizes, e.g. Qwen3.6 27B dense / A35B-A3B MoE on a 96GB M3 Ultra via LM Studio) is held distinct from MOOSEDev's internal NLQ model. Scale (KB size × hop count) is the variable that reveals the effect: expect a NULL (B2 ≈ B1) on the small MOOSEDev-on-itself corpus and the effect to appear on the larger multi-hop corpora (trivyn — private, code-bound; rust-lang/rfcs — public, decision-scale), both as pinned fresh clones under ~/code/moosedev_benches. Python harness talks to the real binary over MCP. Pre-registered hypotheses H1 completion / H2 tokens / H3 speed (moderated by model size), H4 currency-anti-staleness (structural kill-shot via supersede chains), H5 groundedness/anti-hallucination, H8 tool-calling tax (oracle − tooluse), H9 correction-memory persistence, H10 consistency; mechanism metrics: retrieval precision, KB-size sweep. Honesty guardrails: grade against primary-source ground truth (never the in-graph record); symmetric equal-effort usage guidance across B1/B2 (frozen pre-run; both an agents.md overlay and a system-prompt nudge), B0 cold; B1 must be a competent RAG; oracle vs tooluse modes; strong-model capture is the treatment (fair because of content parity + primary-source ground truth). Storage: append-only JSONL, one row per run. Phased delivery with a pause after each phase. Full design: tasks plan file (ok-what-s-next)." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/47f3f038-8fd7-4a96-9c74-15a24bf8be17> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/47f3f038-8fd7-4a96-9c74-15a24bf8be17> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-18T15:19:26.587442Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/47f3f038-8fd7-4a96-9c74-15a24bf8be17> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Benchmark MOOSEDev value via B0/B1/B2 arms (content parity), Python-over-MCP harness, pre-registered hypotheses" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/4a86aabc-bd7d-4587-adb2-a051f0386dc5> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/4a86aabc-bd7d-4587-adb2-a051f0386dc5> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Native temporal bootstrap subcommand + auto-installed agent skills" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/4a86aabc-bd7d-4587-adb2-a051f0386dc5> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/402e5c0b-dc22-4063-84c6-6b9dd954d540> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/4a86aabc-bd7d-4587-adb2-a051f0386dc5> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/6baa075c-db0d-48e0-800a-0cae86603b2a> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/4a86aabc-bd7d-4587-adb2-a051f0386dc5> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/4a86aabc-bd7d-4587-adb2-a051f0386dc5> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Claim: the temporal (git-walk) bootstrap ships as a NATIVE subcommand — `moosedev bootstrap --temporal` (src/temporal.rs, a Rust port of bench/temporal_bootstrap.py) — and `moosedev init` installs the workflow docs as auto-discoverable Agent Skills, so a fresh install can seed a real, backdated project graph with zero path-hunting. Shipped v0.6.0–0.6.3 (commits ce6a3c7, a9850ce, fee552b).\n\nTEMPORAL DRIVER: replays first-parent trunk history oldest→newest (git log --first-parent --reverse), deterministically triages non-decision commits (fmt/bump/wip/noise-paths), owns a dedicated --serve backend, and per decision-bearing commit rewrites the MOOSEDEV_CAPTURE_TS_FILE / MOOSEDEV_CAPTURE_AUTHOR_FILE capture-default files then spawns one coding agent (`claude -p` default; `--agent codex`) — the EXISTING resolve_when/resolve_author seam in src/mcp/mod.rs needed ZERO backend changes. Flags: --repo --data-dir --trunk --resume (temporal-applied.log cursor) --limit --dry-run. Verified end-to-end on slop-rdf: 2 commits captured, 16 records stamped with the REAL January commit dates (2026-01-20T17:26:41Z / 2026-01-23T07:28:17Z, timezone-correct) and real author — not wall-clock — proving the per-commit injection. Live-run fixes that review alone missed: claude 2.1 dropped --max-turns; --strict-mcp-config required so a project .mcp.json can't hijack captures into the wrong store; the agent needs the SKILL dir (--add-dir), not the target repo (diff is inlined).\n\nSKILLS AUTO-INSTALL: init synthesizes SKILL.md (name+description frontmatter + embedded doc body) into .claude/skills/<name>/ (Claude Code + opencode read it) and, with --codex, .agents/skills/ (Codex does NOT read .claude/skills/ — verified from primary docs). The flat skills/*.md stay canonical (bench harness + cross-references depend on those paths); SKILL.md is synthesized at init-time. `moosedev skills` lists the shipped docs. Snapshot bootstrap = the interactive skill; temporal = the command; both documented in README getting-started." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/4a86aabc-bd7d-4587-adb2-a051f0386dc5> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/4a86aabc-bd7d-4587-adb2-a051f0386dc5> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-07-07T03:28:02.148569Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
