<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/52554569-be1b-4ac0-ad84-0437a758a6b2> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/52554569-be1b-4ac0-ad84-0437a758a6b2> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Claim: spec/MOOSEDev_v2_spec.md (v0.1, 2026-07-06) is the spec of record for the full v2 scope — code layer, active-agency layer, and knowledge-LSP in ONE document — delivered in four phases with hard per-phase acceptance criteria: v2.0 read-only vertical slice (substrate + skeleton + resolver + dossier + LSP hover/diagnostics on Zed), v2.1 ambient layer + why-coverage debt metric + ratification inbox + citation-seed migration, v2.2 active agency (policy engine, entity-exact push, gate on two hosts, grounded capture), v2.3 write-path code actions + Neovim conformance. Client order: Zed first (extension-less per AD 2501ffa4), Neovim as scriptable conformance client at v2.3, VS Code picture-frame post-v2. LSP transport: a `moosedev lsp` stdio shim to the shared backend's Unix socket, reusing the proven --connect proxy pattern (src/runtime.rs). One dossier query function (get_entity_dossier) serves LSP hover, MCP push, and HTTP — the no-second-brain constraint (2ba76439) enforced by construction, not by synchronization. Delivery gate: role badges (v2.1) require the role-taxonomy AD b5b4762b ratified first. User-confirmed scope choice 2026-07-06." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/52554569-be1b-4ac0-ad84-0437a758a6b2> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/52554569-be1b-4ac0-ad84-0437a758a6b2> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-07-07T04:49:33.206505Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
