<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/603fe674-fb52-4bda-81f5-2c5f61b5247f> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#weighs> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Alternative/f58661a7-9f49-4b07-a9b8-82611f3b35e9> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/681698b3-bcb5-447f-b93a-600f94277e32> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/681698b3-bcb5-447f-b93a-600f94277e32> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "v2 active layer verbs: push, gate, capture over host adapters" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/681698b3-bcb5-447f-b93a-600f94277e32> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/681698b3-bcb5-447f-b93a-600f94277e32> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Claim: v2's active-agency layer (the AD 145af7e9 split; Requirement 350c7f2e's v2) decomposes into three escalating verbs whose policy vocabulary IS the code layer — the two halves of v2 are one design. (1) PUSH: exact entity dossiers on touch (role, criticality, contracts, defect/perf history) — extends proven push (AD 03393c63, 0.4→1.0) from topical relevance-guessing to entity-exact delivery. (2) GATE — the new verb: host hooks that BLOCK, enforcing differential process (deny / require-plan / require-ratification on hand-tuned or critical entities). This is the first time the symbolic-controller claim is literal inside a host harness: the LLM cannot talk its way past a hook the way it can past a system prompt. It turns validate_against_architecture operative (edit-time checks) rather than advisory. (3) CAPTURE: extract typed records from diff + transcript at decision points (grounded capture per 145af7e9 — never interrogate the LLM into confabulating), stamp authorship provenance for free, queue for human ratification. Architecture: ONE host-independent policy engine reading the graph, THIN per-host adapters (opencode plugin, Claude Code hooks — both precedented); policy degrades gracefully per host capability (gate where blocking exists, warn-and-inject where only observation exists). ACCEPTANCE TEST for v2: the same policy drives two hosts. The ClarificationCard flow (typed question → typed answer, durably recorded) generalizes from NLQ grounding to the ratification inbox." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/681698b3-bcb5-447f-b93a-600f94277e32> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/681698b3-bcb5-447f-b93a-600f94277e32> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-07-03T22:18:38.615883Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/681698b3-bcb5-447f-b93a-600f94277e32> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "v2 active layer verbs: push, gate, capture over host adapters" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/681698b3-bcb5-447f-b93a-600f94277e32> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#isMotivatedBy> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/350c7f2e-61bd-49e4-b7cd-2fdd3f51f521> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/681698b3-bcb5-447f-b93a-600f94277e32> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#resultsIn> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Consequence/0c447d67-2ce8-4470-8c69-742772a1391b> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/681698b3-bcb5-447f-b93a-600f94277e32> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#resultsIn> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Consequence/6505ed72-0353-4b5b-9cc9-4039538f89e8> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/6fd4f0e5-e5d1-4ebe-95d0-80efae74cfeb> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/6fd4f0e5-e5d1-4ebe-95d0-80efae74cfeb> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "get_relevant_context topic retrieval: search_records BM25, not gazetteer" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/6fd4f0e5-e5d1-4ebe-95d0-80efae74cfeb> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/11e01ea2-f520-4f7c-a165-09532dacd43f> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/6fd4f0e5-e5d1-4ebe-95d0-80efae74cfeb> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/6fd4f0e5-e5d1-4ebe-95d0-80efae74cfeb> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "relevant_context's topic path previously called moose's entity-index gazetteer (search_classes), which scores by strsim::levenshtein token edit-distance over LABEL_PREDICATES — that is named-entity LINKING, not relevance retrieval, and it never searched the description body. On any corpus with terse titles it whiffed: get_relevant_context('private fields') returned [] even though a record was titled 'RFC 1: private fields', and the benchmark's rust-rfcs (634 records) probes all returned empty (see Lesson 27a62901 on the small-corpus behavior; the large-corpus failure is what this fixes). A new moose primitive, search_records (BM25F over caller-supplied class IRIs + weighted text predicates; raw corpus-relative scores; zero-term-match records excluded), was added in moose (#40) on its own branch. This change wires moosedev's relevant_context (src/graph/mod.rs) to it: text_fields = [(rdfs:label, 2.0), (hasDescription, 1.0)] — rdfs:label (every record carries it as its title) rather than hasTitle so label-only records still match and title text isn't double-counted; predicates resolved from the loaded vocab (moose::RDFS_LABEL const + capture.description), not hardcoded namespaces. The gazetteer-era 0.45 TOPIC_RELEVANCE_FLOOR was removed (BM25 scores aren't normalized, so an absolute floor doesn't transfer); honest empty-state (invariant #6) is preserved because search_records excludes records sharing no query term. tests/context.rs updated: the noise assertion (single-incidental-token -> empty) was a gazetteer artifact incompatible with BM25 and with verbose NL topics, reframed to the preserved property (a topic sharing no term returns nothing). Done on branch search-records-integration, merged to benchmarks. Verified: cargo test + clippy green; on rust-rfcs get_relevant_context now returns RFC 1 for 'private fields', RFC 243 for the '?' operator, and BOTH RFC 212 + RFC 115 for the integer-fallback query. This makes B2's primary recall competent and fair vs B1-rag's BM25, isolating the representation comparison. The agent-facing 100-result cap (Lesson aec883f5) is unchanged and correct." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/6fd4f0e5-e5d1-4ebe-95d0-80efae74cfeb> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/6fd4f0e5-e5d1-4ebe-95d0-80efae74cfeb> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-18T18:47:08.348874Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/6fd4f0e5-e5d1-4ebe-95d0-80efae74cfeb> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "get_relevant_context topic retrieval uses moose search_records (BM25 over label+description), replacing the entity-index gazetteer" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/6fd4f0e5-e5d1-4ebe-95d0-80efae74cfeb> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#isMotivatedBy> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/b3ba8285-746d-4f3e-a092-b8e4fc324149> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/7079634f-057d-4738-b752-a9cf51f2cba0> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/7079634f-057d-4738-b752-a9cf51f2cba0> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Intent links join the code layer and record layer into one graph" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/7079634f-057d-4738-b752-a9cf51f2cba0> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/7079634f-057d-4738-b752-a9cf51f2cba0> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Claim: the code layer is not a second graph — code entities link into the existing record layer: realizes (CodeEntity → SystemComponent), so every record that concerns a component transitively concerns its realizing code; satisfies (→ Requirement); embodies (→ Pattern); constrains and violates widened to range over code entities. This closes two loops. (1) validate_against_architecture gains DENOTATION: a Constraint on a component becomes checkable against the actual entities realizing it — edit-time diagnostics and a no-LLM CI gate (capability axis B of Lesson 8a06ad1d). (2) Drift detection runs both directions: a decision whose realizing code was deleted flags stale; a core-role, high-criticality entity with NO linked rationale is a comprehension-debt hotspot with an address. \"Why-coverage\" (fraction of core entities with linked rationale) becomes a per-entity, per-component metric — the SPARQL-able comprehension-debt query is the product claim. The in-anger trial extends from decision-anchored probes (\"recover the why of decision X\") to entity-anchored probes (\"recover the invariants of function Y\") on the same instrument." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/7079634f-057d-4738-b752-a9cf51f2cba0> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/7079634f-057d-4738-b752-a9cf51f2cba0> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-07-03T22:18:06.328493Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/7079634f-057d-4738-b752-a9cf51f2cba0> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Intent links join the code layer and record layer into one graph" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/7079634f-057d-4738-b752-a9cf51f2cba0> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#isMotivatedBy> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/350c7f2e-61bd-49e4-b7cd-2fdd3f51f521> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/7079634f-057d-4738-b752-a9cf51f2cba0> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#resultsIn> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Consequence/843df861-f98a-431e-83f0-5b19dbe6fb5b> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/7079634f-057d-4738-b752-a9cf51f2cba0> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#resultsIn> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Consequence/f03b30ca-a159-4ea7-88c9-c0729413a3f4> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/717f60ed-631d-4e81-ab6d-e96818494590> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/717f60ed-631d-4e81-ab6d-e96818494590> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Guard MOOSEDev NLQ against schema-contract internal error leakage" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/717f60ed-631d-4e81-ab6d-e96818494590> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "codex-mcp-client" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/717f60ed-631d-4e81-ab6d-e96818494590> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "MOOSE can classify project-memory questions such as \"What are the current architectural decisions?\" as a coarse schema/meta intent. In the observed failure, the engine returned the contract violation text \"Schema query intent set but no SchemaQuerySpec was attached\" as the query answer. MOOSEDev now treats that exact internal error as an integration-boundary failure and retries the same NLQ in PureSymbolic mode, preserving normal Standard-assist behavior for all other results. Added a hermetic query integration test with a fake LLM that emits meta intent for architectural decisions and asserts the internal error does not leak and the retry trace is PureSymbolic. Verified with cargo check and full cargo test." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/717f60ed-631d-4e81-ab6d-e96818494590> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/717f60ed-631d-4e81-ab6d-e96818494590> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-18T14:03:07.717242Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/717f60ed-631d-4e81-ab6d-e96818494590> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Guard MOOSEDev NLQ against schema-contract internal error leakage" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/72dc4260-2f0c-47d3-967e-44a981e0c248> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/72dc4260-2f0c-47d3-967e-44a981e0c248> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Records are workbench-addressable from every read surface" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/72dc4260-2f0c-47d3-967e-44a981e0c248> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/6baa075c-db0d-48e0-800a-0cae86603b2a> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/72dc4260-2f0c-47d3-967e-44a981e0c248> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/8d48edbd-7ee2-4a52-9eac-f2a09c858637> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/72dc4260-2f0c-47d3-967e-44a981e0c248> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "phase7-acceptance" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/72dc4260-2f0c-47d3-967e-44a981e0c248> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Every record shown by hover, diagnostics, or the MCP dossier output links to a workbench page: render_markdown linkifies record titles to http://[http.addr]/#/record/[uuid], diagnostics carry the record short-id as code plus codeDescription.href (the LSP-native clickable field), and a new GET /api/v1/records/[uuid] endpoint serves any typed node - record, component, or code entity - with typed edges in both directions, rendered by a deep-link-only RecordPage in the SPA (hash routing, no router dependency). The workbench origin comes from the daemon-published http.addr file and links degrade to plain text when the HTTP UI is disabled. Diagnostic messages now lead with the record description first sentence (capped at 140 chars) instead of the bare title-handle. Motivated directly by James 2026-07-09 slice-3 acceptance feedback: the title+short-id form was cryptic and nothing was clickable - and it closes spec section 5.3 addressability line ('each addressable (workbench URL)'), which the phase prompts had missed. Also fixed in the same change: the record-page edge filter initially consulted only the architecture vocabulary, silently dropping code-namespace intent links (realizes/satisfies/embodies); the filter now spans both vocabularies." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/72dc4260-2f0c-47d3-967e-44a981e0c248> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "superseded" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/72dc4260-2f0c-47d3-967e-44a981e0c248> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-07-10T02:37:18.109207Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/72dc4260-2f0c-47d3-967e-44a981e0c248> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Records are workbench-addressable from every read surface" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/72dc4260-2f0c-47d3-967e-44a981e0c248> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#weighs> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Alternative/9c57f47e-4885-453a-93bc-5cb89969d4bb> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/72dc4260-2f0c-47d3-967e-44a981e0c248> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#weighs> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Alternative/eaa5a003-0cbe-45fc-825f-cccf17e237e1> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/72e9ca40-1310-4f13-a90d-bc87beaee200> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/72e9ca40-1310-4f13-a90d-bc87beaee200> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Two-tier granularity: substrate code index vs KG skeleton" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/72e9ca40-1310-4f13-a90d-bc87beaee200> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/CodeEntity/fad369c7-65e6-4997-8220-8cb51a758384> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/72e9ca40-1310-4f13-a90d-bc87beaee200> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/72e9ca40-1310-4f13-a90d-bc87beaee200> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Claim: the full AST/symbol graph lives in a SUBSTRATE index (rust-analyzer / tree-sitter / SCIP output; regenerated per commit; no IRI-stability promises), while the knowledge graph holds only the ADDRESSABLE SKELETON. Minting rule: modules and the exported surface always get IRIs; other entities earn one LAZILY on first attachment of a judgment, observation, or record link; statements and expressions never do. Why: MOOSE's retrieval precision comes from walk planning over a curated graph, not from indexing everything (Rationale 262a87b8 — the deliberate no-A-box-index design); pouring the AST into the KG would bloat walks and destroy precision. Structural queries needing full resolution run against the substrate; the KG references into it. The structural layer is commodity — consume SCIP/LSIF-style output rather than hand-rolling parsers." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/72e9ca40-1310-4f13-a90d-bc87beaee200> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/72e9ca40-1310-4f13-a90d-bc87beaee200> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-07-03T22:18:30.14322Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/72e9ca40-1310-4f13-a90d-bc87beaee200> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Two-tier granularity: substrate code index vs KG skeleton" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/72e9ca40-1310-4f13-a90d-bc87beaee200> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#isMotivatedBy> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/350c7f2e-61bd-49e4-b7cd-2fdd3f51f521> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/72e9ca40-1310-4f13-a90d-bc87beaee200> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#weighs> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Alternative/2b0b5cfd-bf58-464d-b983-83811556a37d> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/72e9ca40-1310-4f13-a90d-bc87beaee200> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#weighs> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Alternative/a5360220-1653-4410-b3aa-814335e19f98> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/73918962-4171-4a97-b666-ae51f7958f80> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/73918962-4171-4a97-b666-ae51f7958f80> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "relate() validates endpoints against SHACL shapes" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/73918962-4171-4a97-b666-ae51f7958f80> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "codex-mcp-client" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/73918962-4171-4a97-b666-ae51f7958f80> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Implemented the graph write-path decoupling in MOOSEDev-side code. relate(subject, predicate, object) still resolves predicate IRIs by local name from the loaded ontology, but now validates endpoint classes against loaded SHACL shape constraints before opening the transaction: direct sh:property/sh:path/sh:class constraints and sh:or RDF-list branches both contribute valid subject/object class pairs, with existing InformationRecord checks retained only as the fallback when no SHACL object constraint exists. Capture continues to write rdfs:label as the canonical instance label for retrieval/indexing, and mirrors that label into the class-specific datatype property indicated by the ontology's labelProperty annotation, falling back to hasTitle. This lets SystemComponent captures write hasComponentName and pass validation without hardcoding ontology namespaces or modifying MOOSE." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/73918962-4171-4a97-b666-ae51f7958f80> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/73918962-4171-4a97-b666-ae51f7958f80> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasRationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/fa5b6ae3-bab5-4afa-a21e-ac1f18e5467b> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/73918962-4171-4a97-b666-ae51f7958f80> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-19T17:07:19.956747Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/73918962-4171-4a97-b666-ae51f7958f80> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "relate() validates relationship endpoints against SHACL shapes; capture keeps rdfs:label canonical and mirrors it into class-specific typed properties" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
