<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/77b7f5f7-bab4-4bf6-9ca6-dc047e01112d> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/77b7f5f7-bab4-4bf6-9ca6-dc047e01112d> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Ignore rust-analyzer whole-file crate marker in SCIP resolution" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/77b7f5f7-bab4-4bf6-9ca6-dc047e01112d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/CodeEntity/f07f14b4-a2dd-4854-9e4f-25faaedaeeee> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/77b7f5f7-bab4-4bf6-9ca6-dc047e01112d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "codex-mcp-client" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/77b7f5f7-bab4-4bf6-9ca6-dc047e01112d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Claim: the SCIP resolver must ignore rust-analyzer's synthetic whole-file `crate/` Module occurrence when resolving a cursor position. Evidence: `moosedev resolve src/main.rs 1:1` initially returned the file-wide crate symbol because rust-analyzer emits a `... crate/` Module occurrence covering the entire document; that converts ordinary whitespace/comment misses into false hits and violates the v2 substrate rule that misses are silence. Real token occurrences still resolve by smallest enclosing range, e.g. `parse_mode()` at its function name position." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/77b7f5f7-bab4-4bf6-9ca6-dc047e01112d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/77b7f5f7-bab4-4bf6-9ca6-dc047e01112d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-07-07T15:11:08.639095Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/77b7f5f7-bab4-4bf6-9ca6-dc047e01112d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Ignore rust-analyzer whole-file crate marker in SCIP resolution" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/77b7f5f7-bab4-4bf6-9ca6-dc047e01112d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#isMotivatedBy> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/350c7f2e-61bd-49e4-b7cd-2fdd3f51f521> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/77b7f5f7-bab4-4bf6-9ca6-dc047e01112d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#resultsIn> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Consequence/a2dc37a7-3457-4ede-9e64-7f31f22c30a3> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/77b7f5f7-bab4-4bf6-9ca6-dc047e01112d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#weighs> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Alternative/969826b5-a020-480f-8506-74823f0ed933> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/7b824b26-36bb-47ce-a235-0a4fdf31a662> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/7b824b26-36bb-47ce-a235-0a4fdf31a662> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "v1 value: efficiency and weak-model accuracy" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/7b824b26-36bb-47ce-a235-0a4fdf31a662> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/7b824b26-36bb-47ce-a235-0a4fdf31a662> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Strategic reframe of what MOOSEDev v1 claims and the benchmark measures, articulated by the user and now evidence-backed (Lesson fa9170f6, the Q&A efficiency matrix). Trying to make local models BETTER CODERS is the wrong goal ('handing a goat a calculus proof'); the defensible, demonstrated wins are: (1) TOKEN EFFICIENCY — fewer tokens to reach the same answer (local cold→push 70×, frontier cold→push 8× fewer prompt tokens, at matched accuracy on the frontier); (2) THRASHING REDUCTION — far fewer tool calls / steps / wall-clock (both models ~24→0 tool calls under push); (3) ACCURACY only as a SECONDARY, regime-dependent effect — a large win for weak/local models when memory closes a knowledge gap (0.12→0.90), but a WASH for frontier models that already recover the knowledge by exploration. Delivery matters by regime: PUSH (symbolic-layer injection) is REQUIRED for local models (they don't pull, and given the tools they thrash — invariant #1); frontier models pull reliably so pull/push both work and the gap is small. Consequences for the headline: lead with efficiency/thrashing (universal, robust, model-comparable), not with accuracy (noisy under keyword grading) and not with 'memory makes weak models code like frontier' (false — execution capability is separate). The original B2−B1 structured-vs-free-text headline (AD 47f3f038) is refined: it is a single-hop NULL and requires a MULTI-HOP task to show structured's edge. Extends/refines benchmark-value AD 47f3f038; grounded in Lessons fa9170f6, f2f4cd99, 679a69af, 72cc1962, and the push AD 03393c63." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/7b824b26-36bb-47ce-a235-0a4fdf31a662> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/7b824b26-36bb-47ce-a235-0a4fdf31a662> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-19T06:22:08.983139Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/7b824b26-36bb-47ce-a235-0a4fdf31a662> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "v1 value proposition: memory's measurable value is token-efficiency + thrashing-reduction (universal) and accuracy-for-weak-models (closing a knowledge gap) — NOT raw coding ability, NOT frontier accuracy" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/81754f67-83f5-469a-8685-d6e3bdd7d66c> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/81754f67-83f5-469a-8685-d6e3bdd7d66c> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Code-task arm grades constraint-adherence on diff" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/81754f67-83f5-469a-8685-d6e3bdd7d66c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/ce49a867-7ebc-41d5-879c-fa59eed3ae65> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/81754f67-83f5-469a-8685-d6e3bdd7d66c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/81754f67-83f5-469a-8685-d6e3bdd7d66c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "The bench now measures CODING tasks that require retrieval, not just Q&A (the more tangible value story: a small model AVOIDS a known violation because memory carried the constraint). Mechanics (bench/run.py + grade_code.py): a task of type 'constraint_code' materializes the corpus's pinned tracked tree into the run workdir via `git archive <sha|HEAD> | tar -x` (excludes .git — enforcing the comprehension-debt premise of no history — plus gitignored target/.moosedev; .env is dropped); per-arm overlays (AGENTS.md, and docs/decisions for B1-md) are laid down and committed as a git baseline so they don't appear in the diff; opencode edits in place; after the run `git add -A && git diff --cached` yields the patch, saved as a referenced artifact (runs/<run_id>.patch). grade_code.grade_patch scores the diff on three axes — implemented / violated / complied — via regex over ADDED lines only (violation_patterns = the tempting wrong path, e.g. a hardcoded ontology namespace literal; compliance_patterns = the recorded-correct path, e.g. the iri_by_local_name resolver). Sandbox/test execution stays out of scope (patch-level grading only). Ground truth is the codebase's own canonical pattern, never the in-graph record (no circularity). Flagship public task: moosedev/no_hardcoded_ontology_iri, grading against Constraint 19bb4d8a. Validated end-to-end (2026-06-18) on moosedev-on-itself: B0 and B2 both produced a correct compliant patch (resolve_datatype_property delegating to datatype_property_iri); harness, materialization, diff capture, and grader all work, including the B2 code-task + memory-MCP path. Extends the value-benchmark AD 47f3f038." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/81754f67-83f5-469a-8685-d6e3bdd7d66c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/81754f67-83f5-469a-8685-d6e3bdd7d66c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-18T18:02:42.623477Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/81754f67-83f5-469a-8685-d6e3bdd7d66c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Benchmark code-task arm: constraint-adherence graded on the patch (git-archive tree → agent edits → git diff → pattern grader)" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/8353c51a-795a-414f-b978-4781647a1ffe> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/8353c51a-795a-414f-b978-4781647a1ffe> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Capture-gap fix: inline relations + link-suggester + under-linked advisory" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/8353c51a-795a-414f-b978-4781647a1ffe> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/11e01ea2-f520-4f7c-a165-09532dacd43f> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/8353c51a-795a-414f-b978-4781647a1ffe> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/8353c51a-795a-414f-b978-4781647a1ffe> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Built the tool-level capture-gap fix (Lesson 3f807592 parts a+b, previously unbuilt; part c was already done at the skill level by AD 059b01b7). Three pieces: (1) record_important_decision now accepts inline `relations` (predicate + target by IRI or exact title), wired through the previously-dead record_instance_with_relations with per-edge SHACL validation — an invalid edge fails the whole capture ATOMICALLY (no orphan record). (2) A symbolic link-suggester: hybrid retrieval generates candidates; a RelationCatalogue (built once at bootstrap, generalizing the per-predicate SHACL constraint query into a domain/range table that includes sh:or union ranges) gates legality; ranked by edge-priority. Surfaced at capture time and via a new suggest_links MCP tool (single-record, or scan-under-linked). (3) A non-blocking under-linked advisory in validate_against_architecture, driven by the shapes' existing sh:or branches. KEY CHOICES: (a) SUGGEST-ONLY — abductive (similarity/legality) edges are guesses; auto-writing them would pollute the get_relevant_context 'TRUST records' contract and spend the confabulation-resistance differentiator (Lesson 8a06ad1d), so the agent always asserts via the validated path; auto-apply stays limited to GROWL's deductive edges. (b) The LLM is at most a GATED tiebreaker (assist>=AssistedValidation, default OFF) that only reorders already-legal predicates — it can never coin one (invariant #1, symbolic-first). (c) The validate nudge is a Rust/SPARQL ADVISORY, not declarative sh:Warning, because MOOSE's M3 validator (src/validation.rs) has no sh:severity and skips sh:class/sh:or — declarative severity is a deferred MOOSE-core change the user owns. Reuse wins: validate now reads the in-memory catalogue (retired per-call SPARQL); edge_priority decoupled to a PRIORITY_EDGES const guarded by a catalogue-membership test. Verified: catalogue/legal_predicates/priority unit tests + inline_relations (atomic-fail + distinct errors) + suggest (suggest->confirm->idempotent) + validation-advisory tests green; clippy clean; dogfood probe on the live 154-record graph found 110 under-linked records (35 AD missing isMotivatedBy, 5 Constraint missing constrains, 70 Lesson missing learnedFrom) with Conforms:true, 0 violations." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/8353c51a-795a-414f-b978-4781647a1ffe> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/8353c51a-795a-414f-b978-4781647a1ffe> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-22T07:52:59.660262Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/8353c51a-795a-414f-b978-4781647a1ffe> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Capture-gap fix: inline relations + link-suggester + under-linked advisory" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/8353c51a-795a-414f-b978-4781647a1ffe> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#isMotivatedBy> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/b3ba8285-746d-4f3e-a092-b8e4fc324149> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/83ced254-437c-4dc2-b05f-12943c11661a> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/83ced254-437c-4dc2-b05f-12943c11661a> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Route NLQ by query class: content vs structure" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/83ced254-437c-4dc2-b05f-12943c11661a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/83ced254-437c-4dc2-b05f-12943c11661a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Content-recall NLQ should DEGRADE to hybrid BM25F⊕dense record search (a no-anchor fallback at the planner's fallback seam) instead of fail-to-anchor; reserve graph-walk for genuinely structural queries (list accepted decisions, what supersedes X, rationale for Y). Keeps the fuzziness in the sensor/boundary and the symbolic walk deterministic (invariant #1). Hold it to: an auditable trace (\"no anchor → content search over class X\") and a current-only lifecycle filter. Implemented in MOOSE Core, so it's a general MOOSE win, not just moosedev. The label-designator contract already de-saturated the content channel this routes into, so the two compose." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/83ced254-437c-4dc2-b05f-12943c11661a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/83ced254-437c-4dc2-b05f-12943c11661a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-21T23:48:22.889489Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/83ced254-437c-4dc2-b05f-12943c11661a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Route NLQ by query class: content vs structure" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/83ced254-437c-4dc2-b05f-12943c11661a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#isMotivatedBy> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/b3ba8285-746d-4f3e-a092-b8e4fc324149> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/83d0479e-40f7-46bb-880e-d2e49e49f2f9> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/83d0479e-40f7-46bb-880e-d2e49e49f2f9> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "MOOSEDev chat clarification dialog learns to the user overlay" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/83d0479e-40f7-46bb-880e-d2e49e49f2f9> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/19df26dc-076b-4339-bee6-bfdc602c13ff> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/83d0479e-40f7-46bb-880e-d2e49e49f2f9> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/8d48edbd-7ee2-4a52-9eac-f2a09c858637> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/83d0479e-40f7-46bb-880e-d2e49e49f2f9> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/83d0479e-40f7-46bb-880e-d2e49e49f2f9> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "The MOOSEDev web chat now handles MOOSE clarification turns end to end. The UI detects finish_reason==\"clarification\" + moose.clarification, renders an inline candidate-picker card (ported from Trivyn's ClarificationCard, minus the checkbox), locks free-text input while a card is open, and replies on the SAME session via a new clarification_reply field. Learned surface forms are ALWAYS remembered to the USER overlay (urn:moose:overlay:user:default), never promoted into the shipped ontology TTLs: MOOSEDev has no ontologist review queue, and the overlay is user-owned local memory that survives version updates because ontology::load_ontologies clears+reloads only the four shipped ontology graphs, not overlay graphs. To make \"remember\" work without per-user auth, the backend normalizes an anonymous Human{user_id:None} reply to a stable \"default\" id (src/api/handlers/chat.rs::normalize_clarification_reply); otherwise MOOSE's accept() rejects it with rule anonymous_cannot_remember and silently drops the pick. Files: ui/src/api/types.ts (wire types), ui/src/api/client.ts (clarification_reply payload), ui/src/components/chat/{ClarificationCard.tsx,clarification.ts,ChatMessage.tsx}, ui/src/pages/ChatPage.tsx (detect/reply/lock), src/api/handlers/chat.rs (agent normalization). Verified LIVE against the release binary with a local LLM: \"list all florbles\" -> UnknownEntity clarification, Decline resumed with \"Dismissed.\"; \"show decisions by importance\" -> 15-candidate UnresolvedModifier clarification; PickCandidate(remember=true) wrote \".../concerns skos:altLabel \\\"by importance\\\"\" with moose:overlayScope \"user\" into urn:moose:overlay:user:default. Also 6 ClarificationCard component tests (vitest/jsdom) and 2 backend normalization unit tests, tsc+clippy clean." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/83d0479e-40f7-46bb-880e-d2e49e49f2f9> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
