<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/87f558c6-e69b-41c7-9cfe-b000d6e1cc50> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/402e5c0b-dc22-4063-84c6-6b9dd954d540> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/87f558c6-e69b-41c7-9cfe-b000d6e1cc50> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/87f558c6-e69b-41c7-9cfe-b000d6e1cc50> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Added skills/generate-adrs-from-graph.md — a read-only workflow that renders each ArchitecturalDecision plus its 1-hop cluster as a standard docs/adr/ set (one NNNN-<slug>.md per decision + a 0000-index.md log). Mapping: isMotivatedBy + inbound constrains → Context; hasRationale → Decision; weighs → Considered Options; resultsIn → Consequences; concerns → Affects; supersedes/isSupersededBy chain → ADR Status. Rationale: the graph is the source of truth and the ADR files are a regenerable view (invariant #2) — the typed model maps ~1:1 onto the canonical ADR template, including the supersession lifecycle hand-written ADRs usually get wrong. It is the inverse of the bootstrap skill (which writes the graph; this only reads it). Scope decisions, pinned with the maintainer: pure ADR set, no diagrams; standalone Constraint/Pattern/AntiPattern/Lesson are omitted because this is the FIRST of a planned family of artifact-generating skills that will render those other kinds (decision-linked constraints/requirements still appear as ADR Context). Honesty discipline carried from bootstrap: render-or-mark — a section with no graph row reads \"not recorded\", never invented (invariant #6); enumerate ALL decisions regardless of lifecycle status (superseded/deprecated included) since the log's value is the evolution. Evidence: skills/generate-adrs-from-graph.md; the skill's SPARQL was verified runnable against the live store (47 ArchitecturalDecisions; Phase-2 cluster query resolves both outbound isMotivatedBy and inbound constrains for AD 07415633)." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/87f558c6-e69b-41c7-9cfe-b000d6e1cc50> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/87f558c6-e69b-41c7-9cfe-b000d6e1cc50> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-25T15:12:41.63104Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/87f558c6-e69b-41c7-9cfe-b000d6e1cc50> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Render ADRs from the graph as the first artifact-generating skill" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/899b9ab9-f670-4025-bb26-1c9d046fde01> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/899b9ab9-f670-4025-bb26-1c9d046fde01> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "First-class Requirements UI uses reusable artifact service" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/899b9ab9-f670-4025-bb26-1c9d046fde01> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "codex-mcp-client" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/899b9ab9-f670-4025-bb26-1c9d046fde01> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "First-class Requirements UI renders Requirement records through a reusable backend artifact service, following the established ADR artifact-service precedent. The implementation adds a read-only requirements renderer that counts and enumerates Requirement records, renders generated markdown detail pages, reports linkage warnings, and summarizes inbound ArchitecturalDecision isMotivatedBy links. Thin REST endpoints expose list, detail, and ZIP archive responses. The React UI adds a Requirements page and shared markdown IRI navigation so Requirement IRIs in ADRs open the corresponding requirement, and ArchitecturalDecision IRIs in requirement details open the corresponding ADR. The project graph remains the source of truth; the feature does not write generated docs." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/899b9ab9-f670-4025-bb26-1c9d046fde01> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/899b9ab9-f670-4025-bb26-1c9d046fde01> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-26T04:02:52.157996Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
