<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/8b48ab85-cf38-4925-a73a-ea3c21e23842> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/8b48ab85-cf38-4925-a73a-ea3c21e23842> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Benchmark model suite spans the capability spectrum" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/8b48ab85-cf38-4925-a73a-ea3c21e23842> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/8b48ab85-cf38-4925-a73a-ea3c21e23842> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Four models span the capability spectrum the value thesis lives on: (1) codex-spark (strong frontier, codex CLI) — efficiency regime; recovers code-rule knowledge by exploration. (2) Sonnet (claude-sonnet-4-6, claude -p) — second strong anchor in a different family/harness (generalization). (3) Haiku (claude-haiku-4-5, claude -p) — the TRANSITION PROBE: small but HOSTED, so an accuracy lift (not just efficiency) would be a reproducible capability win without local infra; and because it pulls reliably it isolates the capability axis from the delivery/pull-gap axis. (4) A3B (qwen3.6-35b-a3b, opencode + LM Studio) — the weak/self-hosted anchor where memory becomes a capability win AND the pull gap appears (won't call the tool, so push is necessary). Skipped: gemma (weaker 2nd local, can't co-load with A3B) and Opus (redundant strong anchor).\n\nHARNESS MAPPING (multi-harness): Claude models -> Claude Code headless (claude -p); codex-spark -> codex CLI; A3B -> opencode + LM Studio. claude -p is a complete harness for Claude models: --mcp-config attaches the moosedev MCP (B2) and the free-text recall MCP (B1-rag); --output-format json yields per-run input/output/CACHE tokens, total_cost_usd, num_turns, duration, and the resolved model id (cleaner than parsing opencode logs); --append-system-prompt carries arm guidance and the push/oracle injection. Retained from the superseded decision: memory is injected as an MCP server so B1/B2 differ only in representation.\n\nACCOUNTING RULE (caching): claude -p uses prompt caching, so its raw token totals are NOT comparable to the no-cache local (opencode/LM Studio) runs (cf. the token-fingerprint gap). Headline efficiency metric = the WITHIN-model cold-vs-push token RATIO (cache/harness-robust); keep absolute counts harness-tagged.\n\nCOMPARISON NOTE: pull-reliability is harness-dependent (Lesson 094087c7 — pull fails for local across opencode AND codex), so the cross-model comparison leans on the harness-independent push/oracle arm; tooluse/pull shows the per-harness pull gap (esp. A3B). Iterate task design on cheap/fast Haiku+Sonnet, add slow local A3B for the final capability runs." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/8b48ab85-cf38-4925-a73a-ea3c21e23842> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/8b48ab85-cf38-4925-a73a-ea3c21e23842> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasRationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/280c1722-9f41-4488-954c-333bec2c56ca> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/8b48ab85-cf38-4925-a73a-ea3c21e23842> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-19T18:00:02.317673Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/8b48ab85-cf38-4925-a73a-ea3c21e23842> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Benchmark model suite spans the capability spectrum (codex-spark / Sonnet / Haiku / A3B), run per-harness; within-model token-ratio is the efficiency metric" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
