<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/91ceb155-4f64-486b-8387-6001daa30a0e> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/91ceb155-4f64-486b-8387-6001daa30a0e> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-18T19:03:38.298959Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/91ceb155-4f64-486b-8387-6001daa30a0e> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Trivyn constraint-code task suite spans the non-locality spectrum (strong→null) to disconfirmably isolate memory's value" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/97671bfa-f13c-4588-a0fd-f1a3e5c540a1> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/97671bfa-f13c-4588-a0fd-f1a3e5c540a1> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Shared --serve backend, thin --connect proxies" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/97671bfa-f13c-4588-a0fd-f1a3e5c540a1> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/97671bfa-f13c-4588-a0fd-f1a3e5c540a1> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "The durable KG is RocksDB-backed and single-writer (exclusive lock), so the default per-client stdio model fails when a second MCP client (e.g. Codex beside Claude Code) opens the same project. Decision: one shared backend process (moosedev --serve) owns the store and clients attach as thin --connect proxies over a per-data-dir Unix socket, giving multi-project isolation by construction. Rejected alternatives: per-client stdio servers (cannot share a single locked store); an N-Quads file fallback (loses transactional cache-coherence). Evidence: tasks/todo.md M5." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/97671bfa-f13c-4588-a0fd-f1a3e5c540a1> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "deprecated" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/97671bfa-f13c-4588-a0fd-f1a3e5c540a1> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasRationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/8423e995-ce75-41c8-889c-2fb550708ea2> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/97671bfa-f13c-4588-a0fd-f1a3e5c540a1> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-18T05:48:08.53293Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/97671bfa-f13c-4588-a0fd-f1a3e5c540a1> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Shared --serve backend with thin --connect proxies for concurrent multi-client access" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/992f3f10-b1ec-408f-b0c1-8c46cf441657> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/992f3f10-b1ec-408f-b0c1-8c46cf441657> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Dual substrate: SCIP canonical, tree-sitter honest-degradation fallback" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/992f3f10-b1ec-408f-b0c1-8c46cf441657> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/CodeEntity/3560f0a4-30c4-451e-93b6-2fa2fe451281> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/992f3f10-b1ec-408f-b0c1-8c46cf441657> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/992f3f10-b1ec-408f-b0c1-8c46cf441657> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Claim: the v2 substrate index treats SCIP as the canonical format (first producer: rust-analyzer, dogfooding on moosedev/moose; later languages = more SCIP producers, zero resolver changes) with tree-sitter as the fallback resolver for languages lacking a SCIP producer — both shipping in the first slice (user-confirmed 2026-07-06). Normative degradation semantics: fallback entities get syntactic identity (ts:<lang>:<path>:<kind>:<qualified-name>), position resolution to the enclosing declaration only; topology (calls/uses/implements), fan-in/out, and blast radius are ABSENT in fallback mode — never approximated from lexical evidence (extends AD 3b32fb25's rejection of relevance-guessing to the resolver); renames orphan the continuant with a stale flag rather than guess. Every resolution result carries its mode; surfaces may mark syntactic anchors but never present a lexical guess as precise. Index runtime: `moosedev index` on demand plus an optional git post-commit hook; no file watcher in v2.0. Refines AD 72e9ca40 (substrate tier) and AD 136dbf24 (SCIP symbol grammar as identity)." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/992f3f10-b1ec-408f-b0c1-8c46cf441657> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/992f3f10-b1ec-408f-b0c1-8c46cf441657> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-07-07T04:49:41.610697Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
