<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/9e7e8da1-e361-454f-988d-35dfc0c43d6f> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/9e7e8da1-e361-454f-988d-35dfc0c43d6f> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Keep MOOSEDev MCP client wiring repository-local" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/9e7e8da1-e361-454f-988d-35dfc0c43d6f> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "codex-mcp-client" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/9e7e8da1-e361-454f-988d-35dfc0c43d6f> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Codex and Claude should load the MOOSEDev MCP server from repo-scoped configuration for this repository, not from global user config. Codex uses .codex/config.toml and Claude uses .mcp.json, both pointing at ./target/release/moosedev --connect with MOOSEDEV_DATA_DIR=./.moosedev. User-level/global configs should not define a MOOSEDev MCP server; they may still contain unrelated global servers such as omni." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/9e7e8da1-e361-454f-988d-35dfc0c43d6f> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/9e7e8da1-e361-454f-988d-35dfc0c43d6f> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-18T01:15:14.831391Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/9e7e8da1-e361-454f-988d-35dfc0c43d6f> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Keep MOOSEDev MCP client wiring repository-local" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/9edda690-2ac1-494b-bd07-04a92cc4f787> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/9edda690-2ac1-494b-bd07-04a92cc4f787> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Web UI binds ephemeral loopback port" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/9edda690-2ac1-494b-bd07-04a92cc4f787> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/9edda690-2ac1-494b-bd07-04a92cc4f787> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Refines the web-UI binding sub-decision of AD d8a5cff1 (which defaulted the UI to a FIXED 127.0.0.1:7474). A fixed port collides across the per-data-dir backends this design runs in parallel (one `--serve` per project, AD 0d81e237), so only the first backend could bind 7474. Change: MOOSEDEV_HTTP_ADDR now defaults to 127.0.0.1:0 — the OS assigns a free ephemeral loopback port.\n\nThe backend publishes the resolved address to `<data_dir>/http.addr` (written on successful bind, removed on clean shutdown). New discovery/UX surfaces in the CLI: `moosedev --status` reports backend liveness (via a socket connect that NEVER opens RocksDB — Lesson c33ec85f) plus the web UI URL (read from http.addr, trusted only while the backend is live, so a stale file from a crash is ignored); `moosedev ui` opens the UI in a browser, auto-spawning a backend if none is live (reusing connect_or_spawn from AD 14f8fe4d); `moosedev --serve --open` opens the browser once the UI is up. A dependency-free, non-fatal open_browser (open/xdg-open/cmd start) handles the launch.\n\nspawn_http_if_enabled is now INFALLIBLE: a UI bind failure (port in use, unparseable MOOSEDEV_HTTP_ADDR, headless box) logs a warning and returns None so the MCP backend — the actual reason the process exists — keeps running, instead of aborting startup with `?`. The bind/publish path is split into a private bind_http_listener so it is unit-testable without building an AppState.\n\nConservative localhost-only default preserved (Lesson 237dd9e8); set MOOSEDEV_HTTP_ADDR for a stable port or network exposure, MOOSEDEV_NO_HTTP=1 to disable. Verified: cargo fmt, clippy -D warnings, full cargo test (all suites green), and a real-binary smoke — `--status` down→up→down, http.addr written/parseable, health 200 on the ephemeral port, a bad MOOSEDEV_HTTP_ADDR does not kill the backend, and http.addr is removed on SIGTERM." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/9edda690-2ac1-494b-bd07-04a92cc4f787> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/9edda690-2ac1-494b-bd07-04a92cc4f787> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-20T19:46:05.657631Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/9edda690-2ac1-494b-bd07-04a92cc4f787> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Web UI defaults to an ephemeral loopback port, discovered via http.addr + --status/ui" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/a7fc1353-2b7a-42c9-ab64-bd0043e412f6> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/a7fc1353-2b7a-42c9-ab64-bd0043e412f6> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Zed onboarding requires a thin dev extension (spec §5.7 amendment)" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/a7fc1353-2b7a-42c9-ab64-bd0043e412f6> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/6baa075c-db0d-48e0-800a-0cae86603b2a> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/a7fc1353-2b7a-42c9-ab64-bd0043e412f6> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/a7fc1353-2b7a-42c9-ab64-bd0043e412f6> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Zed cannot register a new language server via settings alone - maintainer-confirmed in zed-industries/zed discussion #24092 (still true as of 2026-07-09), which amends spec §5.7's \"settings-based LSP registration, no extension\" line. The clients/zed extension is the thinnest possible artifact: extension.toml declaring language_servers.moosedev for Rust plus a ~40-line wasm shim resolving the binary (settings override, then PATH) and passing [\"lsp\"] - a picture frame consistent with the headless-daemon/thin-surfaces architecture. It lives outside the cargo workspace (wasm32-wasip1 target), installs locally as a Zed dev extension for v2.0 dogfooding, and settings still carry initialization_options (the diagnostics toggles), which moosedev init --zed writes into project-local .zed/settings.json. Registry publication is a later, optional step." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/a7fc1353-2b7a-42c9-ab64-bd0043e412f6> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/a7fc1353-2b7a-42c9-ab64-bd0043e412f6> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-07-09T23:55:23.461944Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/a7fc1353-2b7a-42c9-ab64-bd0043e412f6> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Zed onboarding requires a thin dev extension (spec §5.7 amendment)" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/a7fc1353-2b7a-42c9-ab64-bd0043e412f6> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#isMotivatedBy> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/08b807a4-d7fa-4b0a-ad84-78158a4a8088> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/a7fc1353-2b7a-42c9-ab64-bd0043e412f6> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#weighs> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Alternative/6ea1d3d9-9eea-410f-813e-86d5dcc39c0b> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
