<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/ab379ef4-e43c-457b-ab4b-e51fe68a450d> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/ab379ef4-e43c-457b-ab4b-e51fe68a450d> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Whole-file module occurrences are not position hits" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/ab379ef4-e43c-457b-ab4b-e51fe68a450d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/CodeEntity/889e6b24-de43-4786-b592-ae057aad54f1> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/ab379ef4-e43c-457b-ab4b-e51fe68a450d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/accf4f9f-6309-4d3f-8705-26e551824eb0> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/ab379ef4-e43c-457b-ab4b-e51fe68a450d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "phase7-acceptance" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/ab379ef4-e43c-457b-ab4b-e51fe68a450d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Substrate::resolve skips any Module-kind occurrence that starts at 0:0 and spans multiple lines (is_synthetic_whole_file_marker) - rust-analyzer emits these as whole-file containers for every file, not as tokens. Token-less positions (comments, blank lines) therefore miss honestly instead of resolving to the enclosing module; modules stay reachable via their mod declaration name token, SCIP symbol, or entity IRI. Generalizes AD 77b7f5f7 (which filtered only the crate/ marker) to all per-file module symbols; resolves the 2026-07-08 slice-2 acceptance finding where a comment line in a module-linked file surfaced the module dossier and a mistyped link_code position could silently link the whole module. The multi-line requirement is what keeps real module name tokens (always single-line) resolvable; ingestion and definitions() are untouched, so module entities remain mintable." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/ab379ef4-e43c-457b-ab4b-e51fe68a450d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/ab379ef4-e43c-457b-ab4b-e51fe68a450d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-07-09T14:40:20.782062Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/ab379ef4-e43c-457b-ab4b-e51fe68a450d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Whole-file module occurrences are not position hits" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/ab379ef4-e43c-457b-ab4b-e51fe68a450d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#weighs> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Alternative/17b33064-170f-4838-a351-811aa7b143e6> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/ab379ef4-e43c-457b-ab4b-e51fe68a450d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#weighs> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Alternative/ff00bb2d-ef36-4797-ac7a-7feaa594e13e> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b0d3e4d9-873c-4b5b-bff1-0403c6ab1724> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b0d3e4d9-873c-4b5b-bff1-0403c6ab1724> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Code-layer ontology: three strata with distinct change-semantics" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b0d3e4d9-873c-4b5b-bff1-0403c6ab1724> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b0d3e4d9-873c-4b5b-bff1-0403c6ab1724> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Claim: the v2 code layer is organized as three ontological strata with different authorities and lifecycles. (1) STRUCTURE — rigid, derived deterministically from source at every commit, never hand-asserted: containment as TWO hierarchies kept distinct (logical crate/module/item AND physical directory/file, crossed by declaredIn); kind (function/method/type/trait/macro/const/test/migration/config); topology (calls/uses/implements/accesses/testedBy, with derived fan-in/out and blast radius); exposure (public API, FFI, network entry points). (2) JUDGMENTS — anti-rigid, proposed from evidence, human-ratified, lifecycle-managed: role (per AD b5b4762b: core-algorithm/domain-logic/boundary/glue/boilerplate/generated); CRITICALITY as an axis ORTHOGONAL to role (a payments CRUD handler is boilerplate by role, critical by cost-of-being-wrong); attention policy = f(role, criticality, observations), never f(role) alone; domain-concept links; contracts, which REUSE the existing Constraint class with constrains widened to code entities. (3) OBSERVATIONS — measured occurrents, append-only, instrument-provenanced, commit-anchored: performance, change dynamics (churn/age/authorship concentration → per-region bus factor), defect attribution, verification state, and authorship provenance (human vs which agent/session — first-class in the agent era; likely reuses the existing provenance named-graph machinery). Ontological discipline (OntoClean): rigid kind vs anti-rigid role — an entity IS a Function and PLAYS CoreAlgorithm via a playsRole relation carrying status + provenance, never a subclass. Mixing strata in one categorization destroys knowing which facts are re-derivable vs ratified (e.g. \"interface\" is largely structural/derivable via the existing Interface/exposes; \"core algorithm\" is a judgment). ALIGNMENT PASS (2026-07-03): all 8 candidate terms (CodeEntity, CodeSnapshot, CodeRole, Criticality, AttentionPolicy, Observation, AuthorshipProvenance, CodeFile) returned ambiguous below thresholds (top cosines 0.46–0.54 vs 0.55 bar) — genuinely new vocabulary, no false merges; mint in the software-engineering ontology under the Component/Module lineage (CodeEntity's top candidate: SystemComponent 0.488). Confirmed REUSES, not re-mints: Interface, InterfaceDefinition, Module, DataStore, Constraint, the supersession/lifecycle machinery, dependsOn/implements/uses/accesses/exposes." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b0d3e4d9-873c-4b5b-bff1-0403c6ab1724> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b0d3e4d9-873c-4b5b-bff1-0403c6ab1724> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-07-03T22:17:54.01551Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
