<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b2770b75-87a5-44fc-a341-9d8d83e346f7> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b2770b75-87a5-44fc-a341-9d8d83e346f7> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Defer get_focus_stack; ship the bootstrap skill for M4" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b2770b75-87a5-44fc-a341-9d8d83e346f7> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/402e5c0b-dc22-4063-84c6-6b9dd954d540> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b2770b75-87a5-44fc-a341-9d8d83e346f7> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b2770b75-87a5-44fc-a341-9d8d83e346f7> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "MOOSE's focus stack is conversational state written by chat_pipeline (per-turn salience decay for coreference). MOOSEDev's query is a one-shot symbolic graph walk (execute_graph_walk_nlq_with_context with session_prior/session_memory = None) that keeps no SessionContext and never calls save_context, so get_focus_stack would always read empty unless query is made session-aware. A coding agent issues discrete, fully-specified queries — it is its own multi-turn/coreference layer — so an ephemeral within-session focus stack is low value and cuts against invariant #5 (memory should be external and durable, not within-session). Decision: defer get_focus_stack (not build it hollow) and invest M4 in the bootstrap workflow, which populates the empty graph (invariants #3, #10). Evidence: spec/MOOSEDev_design.md frames focus as an optional within-session continuity layer; tasks/todo.md M4." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b2770b75-87a5-44fc-a341-9d8d83e346f7> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b2770b75-87a5-44fc-a341-9d8d83e346f7> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-18T05:47:54.353147Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b2770b75-87a5-44fc-a341-9d8d83e346f7> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Defer get_focus_stack; ship the bootstrap skill for M4" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b3205dcb-2639-46f0-9b06-96414de81502> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b3205dcb-2639-46f0-9b06-96414de81502> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Benchmark adds ecological free-text arms: B1-notes and B1-rag" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b3205dcb-2639-46f0-9b06-96414de81502> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b3205dcb-2639-46f0-9b06-96414de81502> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "The content-parity design (AD 47f3f038) exports the SAME graph B2 reads into B1's free-text corpus to isolate REPRESENTATION as the only variable. That is a valid CONTROL but ecologically INVALID as the headline baseline: it hands the free-text arm a clean, complete, self-announcing, per-decision export — the fruits of MOOSEDev's structured CAPTURE+CURATION for free — which is exactly the value MOOSEDev claims free-text lacks. This is why the currency A/B tied (self-announcing exported records double-cover the current answer, Lesson 9e7ebeb6) and efficiency washed: B2 was compared against an upper-bound baseline that is 'the graph wearing a markdown hat'. DECISION (user-driven): add ECOLOGICAL free-text arms sourced from the project's REAL human-maintained docs, modeling how knowledge is actually accumulated, and retain a content-parity arm as the control. ARMS: (1) B1-notes — the team's actual accumulated notes (trivyn: tasks/lessons.md, 2263 lines/131KB of Pattern/Invariant/Anti-pattern, + topical *.md + CONVENTIONS.md), agent-grep — the realistic low-effort default; (2) B1-rag (ecological upgrade, later) — a COMPETENT RAG (section-chunked + EMBEDDING retrieval, not BM25) over those same real docs — the strong free-text system (design always flagged BM25 as a placeholder, 'B1 must be a competent RAG'); (3) B1-export (the current graph-export B1-md/B1-rag) — kept as the REPRESENTATION-ONLY control (proves a B2 win is not just 'more/cleaner data'); (4) B2 unchanged. Headline value claim becomes B2 vs B1-notes/B1-rag (whole-system: capture+curation+currency+efficiency vs real practice); B1-export remains the honest control. GROUND TRUTH stays the primary source (trivyn CODE/commits), never the graph or lessons.md (no circularity; note B2's graph was bootstrapped from git commits while lessons.md was dev-written — independent sources). FAIRNESS SUBTLETIES: (a) NOT content-parity — frame B2 wins as whole-system, not representation-only; (b) coverage differs (lessons.md = bug/invariant lessons; graph = decisions/reversals) so pick tasks whose answer plausibly lives in BOTH, or label completeness gaps explicitly; (c) if B1-rag uses EMBEDDINGS while B2's get_relevant_context uses BM25 (lexical), B1 gets the BETTER retriever, so a B2 win proves the SYMBOLIC layer (currency filter + typed edges + expansion) beats a stronger retriever — the honest framing (B2's value was never its retriever). CONSEQUENCE: the prior currency/efficiency NULLS (Rationale 952b72d1, Lesson fa9170f6 wash, 9e7ebeb6) are artifacts of the content-parity baseline and must be RE-TESTED against the ecological arms. MINIMAL FIRST STEP: wire B1-notes (grep trivyn's real docs) and re-run currency + why tasks vs B2 vs B0. Extends/refines AD 47f3f038; relates to 8a06ad1d, 9e7ebeb6." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b3205dcb-2639-46f0-9b06-96414de81502> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b3205dcb-2639-46f0-9b06-96414de81502> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-20T15:33:56.003996Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b3205dcb-2639-46f0-9b06-96414de81502> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Benchmark adds ECOLOGICAL free-text arms (B1-notes = the team's real lessons.md/docs; later B1-rag = competent embedding-RAG over them) alongside the content-parity arm kept as a control; prior currency/efficiency nulls are baseline artifacts to re-test" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b3b84af1-ab05-4ef1-9ece-7eb5bed6f925> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b3b84af1-ab05-4ef1-9ece-7eb5bed6f925> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Commercial wedge hypothesis: MOOSEDev sells before the platform" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b3b84af1-ab05-4ef1-9ece-7eb5bed6f925> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b3b84af1-ab05-4ef1-9ece-7eb5bed6f925> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Claim: MOOSEDev, built as a proof-of-concept of MOOSE, may be the commercially leading product — the domain-specific application sells before the horizontal platform. STRUCTURAL ARGUMENT (not accident): the founding observation (LLMs cannot design ontologies from scratch; ontology design is rare, taste-bound skill) cuts against the horizontal platform sale too — every horizontal deployment needs per-customer ontology work the customer cannot do and consulting cannot scale. MOOSEDev inverts the cost: the vendor authors the software-architecture ontology ONCE and ships it in the box; the customer never sees an ontology, they just work while grounded capture happens. Invariant #7 (domain-specific > general-purpose) was a product strategy disguised as an engineering principle; the long-term Trivyn play may be a PORTFOLIO of domain apps (each = a shipped ontology), with MOOSEDev the template. TIMING: agentic coding manufactures comprehension debt at machine speed — the target problem grows at the rate the agent market grows; competing agent-memory products are free-text/embedding, and the benchmark program already mapped where typed-symbolic categorically wins (set-completeness/negation, currency/supersession, gated multi-hop, delivery-robust push — Lessons 8a06ad1d, bd96a65f). WHAT SELLS given the invariants: open MCP server (invariant #11) = distribution/funnel; closed MOOSE engine = the licensed artifact; local-first (invariant #9) = the enterprise wedge (code + rationale never leave the building; on-prem/air-gapped buyers underserved by cloud memory vendors); the accumulated graph (invariant #10) = the moat — honestly a VALUE moat not captivity (user-owned, export_graph exists). BUYER: EM/CTO buying comprehension-debt insurance (onboarding, bus-factor, agent-fleet grounding, audit trail for agent-written changes — invariant #6 as compliance feature), not the IC dev. EVIDENCE GATE: this hypothesis is strictly downstream of the in-anger trial (AD d3d4d7b1) and its frozen kill Constraint 75b0cf14 — commercial hope adds financial motive to the confirmation-bias risk the trial AD pre-registered against; thresholds must not be re-anchored. KNOWN GAPS: value is capture-gated (month-0 Lesson 56d142f9 — customer bootstrap inherits their commit quality; the enrichment loop UX is the product); current design is solo-operator while the paying unit is a team (shared/merged graphs, permissions, concurrent capture are unbuilt — that is the real commercialization engineering); platform risk from harness-native free-text memory (defenses: the categorical capability axis, cross-harness portability of the graph, and the v2/v3 path incl. role-typed attention routing AD b5b4762b). Origin: user speculation 2026-07-02." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b3b84af1-ab05-4ef1-9ece-7eb5bed6f925> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "proposed" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
