<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b3b84af1-ab05-4ef1-9ece-7eb5bed6f925> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#resultsIn> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Consequence/649894cc-47ed-4311-a8ff-17cb9417f45b> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b3b84af1-ab05-4ef1-9ece-7eb5bed6f925> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#resultsIn> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Consequence/924e6b59-6eb7-44fd-86fe-3feba23b471b> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b3b84af1-ab05-4ef1-9ece-7eb5bed6f925> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#resultsIn> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Consequence/9a13de67-119f-4834-b842-bb4444bbcf84> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b3b84af1-ab05-4ef1-9ece-7eb5bed6f925> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#weighs> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Alternative/e14d4cc0-0ed5-4a95-971a-c1006d2b279a> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b5b4762b-baae-495d-95e8-366f15602b5e> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b5b4762b-baae-495d-95e8-366f15602b5e> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Role-typed code + instrumented observations as the v3 attention router" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b5b4762b-baae-495d-95e8-366f15602b5e> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b5b4762b-baae-495d-95e8-366f15602b5e> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Claim: the v3 harness's world model should classify code by ROLE (core-algorithm / domain-logic / glue / boilerplate, each with an attention policy) and ground those classifications in deterministic OBSERVATIONS (profiler hot-paths, memory pressure, git churn, per-region defect attribution), so the harness routes human and LLM attention differentially instead of treating the codebase as an undifferentiated text corpus (the \"LLM writes ALL the code\" chat-harness model). Why: generation is cheap; trustworthy attention is scarce, and code is anisotropic in required taste, empirical risk, and cost-of-misunderstanding. Role classification has the same epistemics as ontology design (taste-laden, underdetermined — LLM-from-scratch fails the same way), so it follows the Trivyn pattern: proposed from evidence, human-ratified, held stable symbolically. Uniquely, it is continuously falsifiable: churn/defect/profile observations test each role hypothesis — a \"boilerplate\" region accumulating defect-fixes and conditional churn gets flagged for promotion; the taxonomy audits itself. Keep JUDGMENTS (proposed roles, ratified) typed apart from OBSERVATIONS (measured facts; profiler/git/CI are better sensors than the LLM for these — no hallucination possible, provenance for free). Differential PROCESS per role, not just visibility: core = focused snippet editing served with attached Constraints/invariants/benchmark+defect history, human-owned, LLM-assists; boilerplate = LLM-generated, machine-audited, escalate-on-anomaly (hidden ≠ unaudited). Comprehension-debt tie: debt is not uniform — losing the why of a CRUD handler costs nothing, losing the why of a core algorithm is catastrophic — so the role taxonomy is the targeting function for where capture/curation effort goes. Origin: user speculation 2026-07-02, generalizing Trivyn's founding observation (LLMs cannot design ontologies from scratch) to code. New ontology terms this implies (CodeRole, AttentionPolicy, Observation subtypes) must go through align_concepts before being minted." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b5b4762b-baae-495d-95e8-366f15602b5e> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b5b4762b-baae-495d-95e8-366f15602b5e> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-07-02T18:19:12.330972Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
