<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b68b8df1-4671-4667-968c-3085b8599137> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "SNARL-backed validate_against_architecture" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b68b8df1-4671-4667-968c-3085b8599137> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "codex-mcp-client" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b68b8df1-4671-4667-968c-3085b8599137> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "validate_against_architecture now delegates SHACL checking to MOOSE's SNARL-backed SHACL Core validator, with severity-filtered conformance in MOOSEDev. Blocking findings are ShaclSeverity::Violation results; under-linked SHOULD-link nudges are declarative sh:Warning property constraints in the architecture shapes and feed both validate advisories and suggest_links scans. The old M3 SPARQL subset and skipped-count caveat are retired. The architecture shapes use property-level sh:or for union range checks so missing links remain warnings while mistyped link targets remain blocking violations. Ontology and shape graphs are cleared before reload so existing stores do not retain stale shape triples across ontology upgrades." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
