<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b72be9f8-c11c-4b80-89ad-375a559a9c1c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Claim: the path→SystemComponent map (the v1 deliverable from Consequence 54937887, needed by capture-time concerns minting and the v2 resolver's realizes inference) is stored IN the project graph as path-glob literals on SystemComponent records — via a new datatype property (working name hasPathGlob) minted through align_concepts at implementation — not as a config file under .moosedev/. Why: the map IS project knowledge (invariant #2 — structured knowledge over free text); in-graph it is captured, superseded, and audited with the existing tools, travels in kg.nq with the code, and is readable by every surface through the one query layer (Constraint 2ba76439 — no second brain). Repo exploration 2026-07-06 confirmed .moosedev/ is a pure runtime data dir (kg.nq + derived caches + socket/pid files) with no config machinery to extend; config today is env-var driven. Spec: spec/MOOSEDev_v2_spec.md §3.6." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
