<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b933bd10-de56-4481-91dd-397a192a8022> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "get_relevant_context seeds with hybrid BM25F⊕dense retrieval" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b933bd10-de56-4481-91dd-397a192a8022> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/11e01ea2-f520-4f7c-a165-09532dacd43f> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b933bd10-de56-4481-91dd-397a192a8022> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b933bd10-de56-4481-91dd-397a192a8022> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Evolves the BM25-only seed (AD 6fd4f0e5) into core's search_records_hybrid: BM25F (rdfs:label 2x + hasDescription) fused with dense cosine over the instance vector store via Reciprocal Rank Fusion (RECORD_RRF_K=60). The seed gates the whole typed expansion, so improving seed recall is the highest-leverage fix for comprehension debt — a concept named differently than the query (\"flaky tests\" vs a query for \"intermittent CI failures\") was previously unreachable along with its entire linked neighborhood. Pipeline in relevant_context (src/graph/mod.rs): (1) symbolic-first anchoring — an exact normalized rdfs:label/hasTitle match seeds the named record first (invariant #1); (2) the hybrid seed recovers paraphrases BM25 misses; (3) the bounded typed expansion (Constraint aa8b3fa3) keeps its budgets, but candidate neighbors are now RANKED by typed-edge priority (isMotivatedBy/violates/supersedes/constrains/dependsOn over generic edges) then dense topic-similarity before the EXPAND_MAX cap, so the surviving links are answer-completing rather than store-iteration order; (4) the dense channel's confidence floor (DEFAULT_DENSE_FLOOR=0.5; MOOSEDEV_DENSE_FLOOR) preserves honest-empty-state (#6); (5) write-time index_record plus a durable, incrementally-reconciled instance index (instance-vectors.db) keep dense coherent, with warm-restart embedding cost ~0. Soft-fails to pure BM25 when no embedding backbone is present or the index is empty. Core consumed: search_records_hybrid, InstanceVecStore (+ new contains), embed_and_index_instance, retrieval_embed_query/_document, HybridMatch diagnostics. Validated: a \"how do we ship updates without taking the service offline\" query recovered the blue-green record PURELY via dense (BM25 returned nothing; cosine 0.575, above the 0.5 floor); in-domain paraphrases scored 0.575–0.730 vs an unrelated query < 0.5 (returns empty); MOOSEDEV_DENSE_FLOOR=0.99 collapses output to BM25-only (dense adds, never distorts); warm restart re-embeds 0; full cargo test suite + clippy green. Governed by the narrowed A-box-seed Constraint (which supersedes 71637748); respects bounded expansion (aa8b3fa3). Evolves AD 6fd4f0e5, left standing as BM25-seed history." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
