<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/bf838e2e-5320-4df7-8469-883e5b0155d6> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "The Knowledge-LSP uses lsp-server 0.8 + lsp-types 0.97 (the rust-analyzer projects own minimal scaffold: Content-Length framing, message loop, protocol types - no framework) with each editor session on a plain std thread over a blocking UnixStream accepted by the daemon listener. The daemon owns a second Unix socket (.moosedev/moosedev-lsp.sock) beside the MCP socket; moosedev lsp is a protocol-agnostic stdio byte relay reusing the --connect auto-spawn machinery. Three requests and one notification family do not justify an async LSP framework, and the thread-per-session model has zero impedance with lsp-server's synchronous transport while the daemon core stays tokio." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/bf838e2e-5320-4df7-8469-883e5b0155d6> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
