<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/ca1e5be2-308b-40ca-a928-dc286a20695b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "onboarding-capture" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/ca1e5be2-308b-40ca-a928-dc286a20695b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Productization onboarding: adds `moosedev init [DIR]` (new CLI Mode in main.rs + a testable src/init.rs) that NON-DESTRUCTIVELY and idempotently generates a project's `.mcp.json` (shared `--connect` mode by default so Claude Code + Codex + web UI share one single-writer store), the `.gitignore` memory rule (`/.moosedev/*` + `!/.moosedev/kg.nq`), and the CLAUDE.md adoption template. `.mcp.json` is MERGED (other MCP servers preserved); an existing CLAUDE.md is never overwritten; the MCP `command` prefers a bare `moosedev` on PATH (upgrade-stable), falling back to the absolute current_exe path with a warning. Two install channels, both BINARY-BASED (closed MOOSE forbids source builds; releases ship a self-contained binary bundled with ontologies/skills/templates, resolved exe-relative): (1) scripts/install.sh curl|sh — detect os/arch, download + SHA-256-verify the release tarball, install to ~/.local/share/moosedev/<ver> and symlink onto PATH; (2) a Homebrew CUSTOM TAP Trivyn/homebrew-moosedev (a formula, not a Cask, so on_macos+on_linux both work) whose text is generated by packaging/homebrew/render-formula.sh and pushed by a token-gated release.yml job. macOS needs NO Developer ID signing/notarization: curl/brew don't set the com.apple.quarantine xattr so Gatekeeper's notarization gate never fires, and the arm64 binary is already ad-hoc signed by the Rust toolchain (verified empirically: curl-installed v0.3.0 runs, Signature=adhoc, not quarantined). Docs: docs/quickstart.md, docs/install.md, .env.example. ALTERNATIVES: bare-stdio default config (rejected — shared --connect is what the repo dogfoods and unlocks the web UI + multi-client; --stdio stays a flag); homebrew/core submission (rejected — it rejects closed/binary formulae; a custom tap supports them); baking the absolute install path into .mcp.json (rejected — breaks on upgrade; bare PATH command is upgrade-stable). CONSEQUENCES: outside adoption is unblocked; the tap needs one-time maintainer setup (repo + HOMEBREW_TAP_TOKEN secret); extra release targets (Windows, Linux-arm64, macOS-x86_64) are follow-ups the installer errors cleanly on. Verified: 9 init unit tests + a live installer run against the real v0.3.0 release + brew style/audit clean in-tap + shellcheck/actionlint clean + full cargo test + clippy -D warnings green." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
