<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/cb68b4de-5e9c-468c-b7d1-4f143c24c7cd> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/11e01ea2-f520-4f7c-a165-09532dacd43f> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/cb68b4de-5e9c-468c-b7d1-4f143c24c7cd> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "phase7-acceptance" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/cb68b4de-5e9c-468c-b7d1-4f143c24c7cd> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "moosedev mint creates CodeEntity nodes for modules and items whose rendered signature starts with pub (including pub(crate)/pub(super)), skipping files under tests/; private items enter the graph only when link_code attaches knowledge to them. This bounds the committed skeleton while lazy minting covers the private tail on demand. Evidence from the 2026-07-08 acceptance run: 905 entities minted (skipped-scope=792, skipped-tests=207, collisions=0, orphans=0); two private functions (is_synthetic_crate_marker, definition_entry) lazy-minted during link acceptance exactly as designed." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
