<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d13be5bb-55b0-4ecc-a2c2-78f0ede8f502> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#weighs> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Alternative/cbb7c36a-bfb4-4a55-80da-b765e0a3d16c> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d146ae24-1f0b-4ae7-a3e6-9bfef97d98e1> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d146ae24-1f0b-4ae7-a3e6-9bfef97d98e1> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Retract as in-place deprecate plus rationale" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d146ae24-1f0b-4ae7-a3e6-9bfef97d98e1> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d146ae24-1f0b-4ae7-a3e6-9bfef97d98e1> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Satisfies Requirement/1ae3b79a (add an in-place status/retract transition for knowledge records). graph::retract_decision atomically mints a Rationale (the why), links the target hasRationale→rationale, and flips the target's hasLifecycleStatus to 'deprecated', then invalidates the entity index. Chose status 'deprecated' because the read path already hides superseded/deprecated by default and surfaces them under include_history — so no read-path change was needed. Distinct from supersede_decision: retract records NO replacement; it is the 'this entry no longer applies' transition (e.g. a duplicate, or a decision abandoned with no successor). The InformationRecord precondition is now a shared require_information_record helper used by both supersede and retract. New MCP tool retract_decision(iri, rationale). Verified by tests/retract.rs (3 tests); clippy clean. Motivated concretely by two duplicate records mistakenly captured during the M4 bootstrap dry-run (a recall-first slip; see tasks/lessons.md)." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d146ae24-1f0b-4ae7-a3e6-9bfef97d98e1> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d146ae24-1f0b-4ae7-a3e6-9bfef97d98e1> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-18T06:05:08.946014Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d146ae24-1f0b-4ae7-a3e6-9bfef97d98e1> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Implement retract as in-place deprecate + rationale (no replacement)" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d146ae24-1f0b-4ae7-a3e6-9bfef97d98e1> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#isMotivatedBy> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/1ae3b79a-f2c5-41ba-a221-cc79bfe9edc2> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d3d4d7b1-a904-4519-98d8-31a24bffa125> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d3d4d7b1-a904-4519-98d8-31a24bffa125> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Validate MOOSEDev via a longitudinal in-anger trial on trivyn + moose" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d3d4d7b1-a904-4519-98d8-31a24bffa125> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d3d4d7b1-a904-4519-98d8-31a24bffa125> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Decision (2026-06-23): validate MOOSEDev's core thesis — reducing comprehension debt — by USING it in anger on trivyn and moose, the maintainer's actively-developed projects, over ~the next few months (through ~Q3 2026). RATIONALE: the multi-corpus benchmark phase established TWO demonstrable structural wins — (1) capability: completeness/negation/supersession/multi-hop over large typed sets, structured graph (B2) categorically beats flat RAG (B1), reproduced on private trivyn AND public codegraph; (2) currency/anti-staleness (graph serves the current decision; free-text is currency-blind) — plus a pile of HONEST NULLS (retrieval ≈ parity with good RAG; no scale-compounding; decomposition saturates on clean corpora; efficiency modest, not the pre-registered <20%). The ACTUAL motivating thesis — that structured memory reduces the slow loss of *why* a codebase is shaped as it is, over months — remains UNMEASURED; only a longitudinal in-anger trial can earn it. RISK to guard: a self-run trial is prone to confirmation bias (the builder will 'see it working'). To yield EVIDENCE not anecdote it must be instrumented UP FRONT: (a) a pre-registered comprehension-debt signal — a fixed set of 'recover the why of decision X' probes re-scored monthly, with vs without the graph; (b) a running tally of when the graph actually saved a re-derivation in real work (or was bypassed); (c) a pre-registered kill/abandon condition (e.g., 'if I'm not reaching for it unprompted by month 2'); optionally (d) a hold-out (keep moose's graph deliberately behind, or leave some decisions uncaptured, for contrast). Side benefit: dogfooding hardens the capture + bootstrap workflow on real projects. Outward claims (blog/social) must stay scoped to what's demonstrated — this trial is the path to claiming more, not a claim itself." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d3d4d7b1-a904-4519-98d8-31a24bffa125> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d3d4d7b1-a904-4519-98d8-31a24bffa125> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-23T08:02:29.719041Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d3d4d7b1-a904-4519-98d8-31a24bffa125> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Validate MOOSEDev via a longitudinal in-anger trial on trivyn + moose" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d542b826-9c7d-4fea-a3ba-75067c459b54> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d542b826-9c7d-4fea-a3ba-75067c459b54> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Added a relate(subject, predicate, object) MCP primitive" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d542b826-9c7d-4fea-a3ba-75067c459b54> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d542b826-9c7d-4fea-a3ba-75067c459b54> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Implements the fix for the capture-tooling gap (Lesson 96456e40): MOOSEDev now exposes a `relate` MCP tool + `graph::relate()` that asserts a typed relationship edge between two existing recorded knowledge items. Design (all open-side in moosedev/src, ZERO MOOSE changes — the engine already writes edges, supersede proved it): resolve the predicate from the loaded architecture ontology BY LOCAL NAME via state.resolve_object_property (so the namespace stays out of the code, and only DECLARED object properties are allowed — ad-hoc/untyped edges are rejected); require BOTH endpoints to be InformationRecords (or subclasses) via require_information_record; insert one quad into the project graph in a transaction; idempotent (re-asserting dedups); invalidate the entity index. Validated end-to-end on the trivyn store: valid edge written + visible in sparql (ASK true); bad predicate 'frobnicates' rejected; non-record subject rejected; re-relate is a no-op. The ontology already DECLARED the relationship vocabulary (supersedes, violates, concerns, constrains, isMotivatedBy, learnedFrom, resultsIn, weighs, + engineering dependsOn/contains/...); only supersede_decision ever wrote one — relate() unlocks the rest. ALSO changed in this phase: get_relevant_context's tool description is now directive + authoritative ('the maintainers' recorded source of truth, kept current; TRUST it; prefer it over re-deriving from code; do not re-verify unless asked') — to stop the verify-against-code flail observed in the currency test (gpt-5.5 push went 0/0/0 hunting for absent code), which is only SAFE because the structure (supersession currency + typed records) backs the claim. This is Phase 1 of the build-real-structure plan (relate → rebuild trivyn linked → relational expansion in get_relevant_context → multi-hop test) motivated by the structure-untested finding (Lesson aaee7652) and the v1 thesis (AD 7b824b26). Edge to the motivating gap (96456e40) to be asserted via relate() once the dogfood serve runs the new binary." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d542b826-9c7d-4fea-a3ba-75067c459b54> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "superseded" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d542b826-9c7d-4fea-a3ba-75067c459b54> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-19T14:36:48.413379Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d542b826-9c7d-4fea-a3ba-75067c459b54> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Added a relate(subject, predicate, object) MCP primitive — writes the ontology's existing relationship edges, closing the capture-tooling gap so capture builds a GRAPH, not a flat list" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d8a5cff1-95a7-4814-9bfb-e3754318a419> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d8a5cff1-95a7-4814-9bfb-e3754318a419> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "MOOSEDev web UI from shared backend" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d8a5cff1-95a7-4814-9bfb-e3754318a419> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "codex-mcp-client" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d8a5cff1-95a7-4814-9bfb-e3754318a419> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "When moosedev runs in --serve mode, it will expose a loopback HTTP UI by default at 127.0.0.1:7474 (override MOOSEDEV_HTTP_ADDR, disable with MOOSEDEV_NO_HTTP=1). The HTTP API is embedded in the same backend process that owns AppState and the Oxigraph store, so MCP clients and humans share one project graph without violating RocksDB single-writer constraints. The first UI ships real MOOSE chat sessions backed by moose::chat::SessionDb in <MOOSEDEV_DATA_DIR>/moose_sessions.db, read-only project-graph SPARQL, and Cytoscape graph views. Typed project-memory writes remain through existing MCP tools for v1." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d8a5cff1-95a7-4814-9bfb-e3754318a419> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d8a5cff1-95a7-4814-9bfb-e3754318a419> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-20T00:31:34.946675Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d8a5cff1-95a7-4814-9bfb-e3754318a419> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Expose a local human-facing MOOSEDev web UI from the shared backend" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d91288c9-5d4a-494f-95b5-5d5a26383b0a> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d91288c9-5d4a-494f-95b5-5d5a26383b0a> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Resolver acceptance fixtures use suffix-stable SCIP samples" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d91288c9-5d4a-494f-95b5-5d5a26383b0a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/CodeEntity/0c042477-d0d6-4a04-8072-e0f7f1c53b36> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d91288c9-5d4a-494f-95b5-5d5a26383b0a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "codex-mcp-client" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d91288c9-5d4a-494f-95b5-5d5a26383b0a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Claim: resolver acceptance samples live under `tests/fixtures/` as 1-based source positions whose expected symbol is a suffix of the SCIP symbol, not the full rust-analyzer cargo prefix. This keeps the v2.0 40-position gate stable across crate-version bumps while still proving exact symbol resolution, definition/reference role detection, and coverage across source, tests, and examples. The fixture must be repaired only by re-verifying changed positions with `moosedev resolve`, not by guessing line/column updates." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d91288c9-5d4a-494f-95b5-5d5a26383b0a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d91288c9-5d4a-494f-95b5-5d5a26383b0a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-07-07T15:49:12.788107Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d91288c9-5d4a-494f-95b5-5d5a26383b0a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Resolver acceptance fixtures use suffix-stable SCIP samples" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d91288c9-5d4a-494f-95b5-5d5a26383b0a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#isMotivatedBy> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/350c7f2e-61bd-49e4-b7cd-2fdd3f51f521> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d91288c9-5d4a-494f-95b5-5d5a26383b0a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#resultsIn> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Consequence/6e1c25e8-0ec3-42ea-ba6e-29275b6e0327> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d91288c9-5d4a-494f-95b5-5d5a26383b0a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#resultsIn> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Consequence/c2d83825-adeb-4174-9af6-7d92502fd8a0> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
