<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/dddeed22-985a-4c12-873a-142f2923a115> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/dddeed22-985a-4c12-873a-142f2923a115> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Path coverage is a first-class MCP write: declare_component_paths" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/dddeed22-985a-4c12-873a-142f2923a115> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/CodeEntity/3dd4e492-6488-49f0-8aa0-6188ab8112f1> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/dddeed22-985a-4c12-873a-142f2923a115> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/6baa075c-db0d-48e0-800a-0cae86603b2a> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/dddeed22-985a-4c12-873a-142f2923a115> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "phase7-acceptance" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/dddeed22-985a-4c12-873a-142f2923a115> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "SystemComponent coversPath coverage is declarable over the MCP surface (declare_component_paths: exact name or IRI, repo-relative paths, add-only and idempotent, SHACL-typed target check) instead of only via the hardcoded seed table in examples/backfill_concerns.rs. Coverage is what moosedev mint uses to derive realizes edges (path to owning component, longest match wins), so without an agent-reachable write, bootstrapped projects inevitably end up with covered-nothing components - exactly the hole MOOSEDev's own repo fell into (the code layer substrate component sat coverage-less from slice 1 until 2026-07-09, leaving 12 paths unmapped and substrate entities without realizes edges). First real use: declaring src/code/ on that component, then an idempotent re-mint added the 106 missing realizes edges as an adds-only update. Both bootstrap skills (bootstrap-existing-codebase, temporal-episode-capture) now include the code-entity phase: declare coverage, index + mint, link_code the strongest records. Deferred: an in-process MCP mint tool so re-mint does not require stopping the daemon (the CLI holds the store lock)." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/dddeed22-985a-4c12-873a-142f2923a115> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/dddeed22-985a-4c12-873a-142f2923a115> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-07-09T14:41:07.029518Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/dddeed22-985a-4c12-873a-142f2923a115> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Path coverage is a first-class MCP write: declare_component_paths" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
