<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/e0b7b528-58f9-4638-a0d8-ef4cc6063c6b> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/e0b7b528-58f9-4638-a0d8-ef4cc6063c6b> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "GROWL enrich co-locates inferred edges in kg/project" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/e0b7b528-58f9-4638-a0d8-ef4cc6063c6b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/11e01ea2-f520-4f7c-a165-09532dacd43f> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/e0b7b528-58f9-4638-a0d8-ef4cc6063c6b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/e0b7b528-58f9-4638-a0d8-ef4cc6063c6b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Co-locate GROWL-materialized inferred A-box edges IN the project graph (kg/project), each tagged with RDF-star << s p o >> prov:wasGeneratedBy <reasoner-activity> in the sibling kg/provenance graph — the per-triple tag IS the drop-and-rerun mechanism (distinguishes an inferred isConcernedBy from an asserted one once co-located). The densify-by-reasoning thesis from the superseded record stands: run GROWL 0.5.1 in enrich mode (ReasonerConfig::new().enrich(true) — skips sameAs/class-exprs) over kg/project + the domain-ontology T-box (the newly-declared inverse object properties) to materialize prp-inv/spo/dom-rng/cax-sco edges deterministically, not by capture-agent hand-drawing. What changes vs the superseded record is PLACEMENT: NOT a separate kg/inferred named graph.\n\nWHY co-locate: every get_relevant_context expansion/walk read is graph-scoped to PROJECT_KG_GRAPH_IRI — record_neighbors (src/graph/mod.rs:1585), build_context_item (1760, 1810), list_instances (1728), require_information_record (764) — so inferred edges in kg/project are first-class in the existing reads with ZERO hot-path change, whereas a separate graph needs unioning into all 5-8. build_context_item already hand-rolls an inverse-supersedes reverse lookup (1799-1824) that a materialized isSupersededBy obviates — proof the win lands in moosedev's own retrieval code.\n\nPORT (mirror Trivyn): lift BlankNodeMapper + the four oxigraph<->growl marshalling fns + the reasoner-drive + the input-set (s,p,o) delta-dedup ~verbatim (swap TrivynError->anyhow, drop AppState/sandbox/batching — moosedev's graph is hundreds of triples, single batch); reuse moosedev's existing kg/provenance PROV-O graph (src/provenance/mod.rs) + rdf-12/RDF-star oxigraph fork for the annotation. growl 0.5.1 is a plain crates.io dep (Trivyn builds against it — vendored C core, no system lib). Dense index untouched (inferred edges carry no rdfs:label/hasDescription, so index_record has nothing to embed; the f1f86296 footgun does not apply). GROWL is an app-layer dep of MOOSEDEV, NOT moose (Trivyn wires it at the app layer too) — respects invariant #11. Drop-and-rerun = delete the kg/project triples the prov graph attributes to a reasoner activity, then re-enrich + re-tag. Trigger: lazy-on-read dirty flag (set by record/relate/supersede/retract, drained by the first edge-traversing read so a capture burst enriches once before recall) + an explicit enrich entry-point for bootstrap bulk-load. Validate after wiring: co-located prp-dom/rng type triples change SHACL targeting — confirm 0 new violations." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/e0b7b528-58f9-4638-a0d8-ef4cc6063c6b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
