<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/e383ce9c-160f-4fca-95c2-5d3ce3ea0b61> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#weighs> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Alternative/b7ebb145-fbc5-4d04-94f2-17ba6486f0fc> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/e54cff16-96e0-4f3e-beaf-74e6180bb6bb> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/e54cff16-96e0-4f3e-beaf-74e6180bb6bb> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Graph-first workflow with CLAUDE.md adopter template" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/e54cff16-96e0-4f3e-beaf-74e6180bb6bb> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/e54cff16-96e0-4f3e-beaf-74e6180bb6bb> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "The durable project knowledge graph is the source of truth for decisions/lessons/constraints/requirements/patterns (invariant #2); tasks/lessons.md and tasks/todo.md are optional human-readable mirrors, not canonical. Retargeted this repo's CLAUDE.md Self-improvement Loop and Task management sections to be graph-first (recall-first = a list-all get_relevant_context; capture typed records; align before coining; correct via supersede_decision/retract_decision not duplication; validate after capture; record lessons as typed Lesson records). Added a reusable, project-agnostic templates/CLAUDE.md encoding the same workflow plus the tool-selection ladder (get_relevant_context → query → sparql) for any project adopting MOOSEDev as memory. Prompted by recording a session lesson only into lessons.md and not the graph — a gap that revealed CLAUDE.md's old 'update tasks/lessons.md' guidance contradicted invariant #2." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/e54cff16-96e0-4f3e-beaf-74e6180bb6bb> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/e54cff16-96e0-4f3e-beaf-74e6180bb6bb> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-18T06:55:13.331779Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/e54cff16-96e0-4f3e-beaf-74e6180bb6bb> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Graph-first knowledge workflow; ship a CLAUDE.md template for MOOSEDev adopters" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/f45cf655-2dc7-4b29-b93d-b3c62c8517d0> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/f45cf655-2dc7-4b29-b93d-b3c62c8517d0> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Drive model-under-test via opencode headless" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/f45cf655-2dc7-4b29-b93d-b3c62c8517d0> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/f45cf655-2dc7-4b29-b93d-b3c62c8517d0> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "For the value benchmark, the agent-under-test is driven by opencode (a real terminal coding agent) in headless mode (`opencode run`), not a hand-rolled ReAct loop. Rationale: (1) credibility — a real, battle-tested coding agent, not a toy loop; (2) opencode supplies the common tools (file read/edit, search, shell) so the harness doesn't build them; (3) opencode is held CONSTANT across arms (pinned version, same base config + system prompt), so its internals are a confound that CANCELS in the within-corpus B2 − B1 comparison; (4) native support for local OpenAI-compatible models (LM Studio / Qwen3.x), MCP servers, AGENTS.md, and session-JSON token/cost telemetry. KEY UNLOCK: memory is injected as an MCP server for BOTH memory arms, making them maximally symmetric — B0 = no memory MCP (neutral AGENTS.md); B1 = a small freetext-recall MCP we build (recall(query) over the exported-graph-as-text + embeddings); B2 = the moosedev MCP (get_relevant_context/query/sparql). Arms differ ONLY in the memory MCP + symmetric AGENTS.md/nudge. Telemetry: agent tokens/steps/cost from opencode session JSON; MOOSEDev internal NLQ tokens from the Phase-1 'tokens:' trace line per query call; wall-clock by timing the run. Oracle mode = disable the memory MCP and prepend harness-retrieved context. Each run uses a throwaway copy of the pinned clone; code tasks graded by diff, Q&A by the final assistant message from the session JSON. De-risk in Phase 2: confirm opencode headless + session-JSON telemetry extraction on one task before scaling; fall back to a custom loop only if telemetry is insufficient. Refines (does not replace) the benchmark design decision 47f3f038." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/f45cf655-2dc7-4b29-b93d-b3c62c8517d0> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "superseded" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/f45cf655-2dc7-4b29-b93d-b3c62c8517d0> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-18T15:25:16.020137Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/f45cf655-2dc7-4b29-b93d-b3c62c8517d0> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Drive the model-under-test via opencode (headless); inject memory as an MCP server for symmetric B1/B2 arms" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/f4978d8a-6361-4628-bf7b-6b297de73c48> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/f4978d8a-6361-4628-bf7b-6b297de73c48> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Graph viewer legend and trace visibility control" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/f4978d8a-6361-4628-bf7b-6b297de73c48> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "codex" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/f4978d8a-6361-4628-bf7b-6b297de73c48> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "The web UI graph viewers now keep node-type meaning visible through a compact legend shared by Chat and SPARQL graph views. MOOSE pipeline trace nodes remain visible by default to preserve auditability, while the Chat graph adds a user-controlled Pipeline traces switch that filters mooseTrace nodes and their connected edges from the rendered graph without changing backend graph data or SPARQL result fidelity." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/f4978d8a-6361-4628-bf7b-6b297de73c48> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/f4978d8a-6361-4628-bf7b-6b297de73c48> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-21T04:02:18.51562Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/f4978d8a-6361-4628-bf7b-6b297de73c48> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Graph viewers expose node-type legend and Chat trace visibility control" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/f68ef43e-7bec-4616-8e0d-e9c0cbb9cc55> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/f68ef43e-7bec-4616-8e0d-e9c0cbb9cc55> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Ontology namespaces: path-style /domain/ IRIs replaced by hash-style #" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/f68ef43e-7bec-4616-8e0d-e9c0cbb9cc55> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/8bb903fd-faba-42af-98d1-a953373ef23b> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/f68ef43e-7bec-4616-8e0d-e9c0cbb9cc55> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "James" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/f68ef43e-7bec-4616-8e0d-e9c0cbb9cc55> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Claim: the ontology term namespaces move from path-style (…/software/architecture/domain/, …/software/engineering/domain/, …/SoftwareArchitectureOntology/shapes#) to hash-style (…/software/architecture#, …/software/engineering#, …/software/architecture/shapes#), fixing the inconsistent IRI pathing across the four shipped TTLs (domain vs shapes paths disagreed; ontology nodes, imports, and bridges now align; the dangling engineering mapping import removed, architecture's removed for symmetry). Instance data in all three live stores was migrated SYNTACTICALLY (prefix swap, local names unchanged) via examples/migrate_namespace.rs — two-stage: raw-store rewrite recursing into RDF-1.2 quoted-triple provenance tags, canonical-divergence preflight gate, write-through, then bootstrap + SHACL + zero-residual scan. Applied: repo store 2250 quads; trivyn-trial 4104; moose-trial 1415 — all conform, all 0-residual, all now carry canonical kg.nq+stamp. Trial stores carry [trial-maintenance] events with A/A retrieval-neutrality evidence (BENCH_HOME/<corpus>/aa-namespace-2026-07): content-neutral modulo iteration-order artifacts and two corrective rank-6 tail swaps from the dense-index rebuild closing incremental gaps. Rationale for hash namespaces: publishable, consistent ontology IRIs (user decision 2026-07-03/04)." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/f68ef43e-7bec-4616-8e0d-e9c0cbb9cc55> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/f68ef43e-7bec-4616-8e0d-e9c0cbb9cc55> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-07-04T06:17:35.602022Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/f68ef43e-7bec-4616-8e0d-e9c0cbb9cc55> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Ontology namespaces: path-style /domain/ IRIs replaced by hash-style #" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/f6ac8e23-f7a2-496f-a81c-9c38796b0d7d> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#ArchitecturalDecision> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/f6ac8e23-f7a2-496f-a81c-9c38796b0d7d> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Implement supersede-with-rationale: atomic txn, non-breaking relation layer" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/f6ac8e23-f7a2-496f-a81c-9c38796b0d7d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/f6ac8e23-f7a2-496f-a81c-9c38796b0d7d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Implemented Requirement/b2f8240c. Key choices: (1) Generic object-property capture added via a NON-breaking record_instance_with_relations(state, input, object_props, ...) rather than a new RecordInput field, so the 8 existing literal construction sites stay untouched. (2) A SEPARATE supersede_decision MCP tool (not overloading record_important_decision), since supersede mutates an existing record and that side effect should be explicit. (3) The supersede is ONE atomic oxigraph transaction: insert the new decision + a Rationale node + the supersedes/hasRationale edges, remove the old decision's lifecycle-status quads, insert hasLifecycleStatus 'superseded', then invalidate_graph (confirmed the oxigraph-trivyn Transaction supports insert+remove). (4) The WHY is a first-class Rationale node (hasRationale range) carrying the reason as hasDescription, stamped with author/timestamp/status to satisfy InformationRecordShape (minCount-1 author/status/timestamp are the only enforced constraints). (5) The old decision is preserved; only its status flips to superseded. (6) Read path: relevant_context defaults to the current working set (hides superseded/deprecated) with an include_history flag; items surface the supersedes link, the dereferenced rationale text, and a supersededBy back-link. No ontology changes were needed — supersedes, hasRationale, the Rationale class, and the lifecycle statuses already existed. Verified by tests/supersede.rs (4 tests: links+preserve+conforms, precondition rejects+no-write, read-path filtering+chain, record_instance_with_relations writes edges)." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/f6ac8e23-f7a2-496f-a81c-9c38796b0d7d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/f6ac8e23-f7a2-496f-a81c-9c38796b0d7d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-18T00:16:10.136876Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
