<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/faba413e-6180-455c-a26a-8c3db9850adc> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/11e01ea2-f520-4f7c-a165-09532dacd43f> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/faba413e-6180-455c-a26a-8c3db9850adc> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/6baa075c-db0d-48e0-800a-0cae86603b2a> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/faba413e-6180-455c-a26a-8c3db9850adc> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/faba413e-6180-455c-a26a-8c3db9850adc> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Added optional FLAT string-list fields `alternatives_considered` and `consequences` to record_important_decision; each string mints the typed node (Alternative/Consequence) and links it (weighs/resultsIn) in ONE call (new graph::record_decision_with_cluster in capture.rs, reusing record_instance + the SHACL-validated relate, with an up-front catalogue legality check so nothing illegal/orphaned is minted). WHY: rendering the ADR set exposed that of 49 live-captured decisions, 0 carried any Alternative or Consequence (weighs/resultsIn = 0; node census Alternative=0, Consequence=0). This graph is LIVE-captured (not temporal-bootstrapped), so it indicts capture friction, not git archaeology: the prior capture-gap fix (AD 8353c51a) only SUGGESTS links to records that already EXIST, and Alternatives/Consequences never exist, while minting one was a 3-call dance small models won't do (the pull-gap, Lesson 2dcca5ff). Flat fields were chosen for LEAST confusion to SMALL models — one call, no multi-turn follow-up, no arrays-of-objects to mis-shape; the field names are the elicitation. isMotivatedBy stays link-to-existing (Requirements are reusable hubs; don't let the model invent them — AD 145af7e9). This is the MCP-tool-layer slice of active capture (AD 145af7e9); transcript-grounded extraction (the plugin layer) remains the stronger future grounding. Evidence: src/graph/capture.rs, src/mcp/mod.rs, tests/cluster_capture.rs (green); full suite + clippy green. Follows AD 8353c51a. This very record was captured using the new fields (dogfood)." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
