<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Consequence/8de42bb0-bba8-4991-ba58-7e949c240c9a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "MOOSE's test_data/software_arch_shapes.ttl still uses the OLD node-level sh:or (no sh:severity), while MOOSEDev's ontologies/software-architecture_shapes.ttl now ships property-level sh:or for union ranges PLUS sh:minCount 1 + sh:severity sh:Warning advisory constraints (AD b68b8df1, SNARL-backed validate). Consequence: MOOSE's own integration test moosedev_project_conforms_to_arch_shapes_with_ontology validates an OLDER shape structure and no longer corroborates MOOSEDev's actual shipped shapes — so the live validate_against_architecture run is the real conformance proof. Independently verified on the live ~150-record graph (2026-06-26, copy of the durable store, freshly-built binary): Conforms: true, 0 violations, 98 non-blocking advisories (33 AD missing isMotivatedBy, 3 Constraint missing constrains, 62 Lesson missing learnedFrom); validate's advisory count equals under_linked_records (single declarative source); full cargo test suite + clippy green. Maintenance gotcha: the two shape copies can silently drift — edit one and the other is unaffected; do not treat MOOSE's fixture test as coverage of MOOSEDev's shapes." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Consequence/8de42bb0-bba8-4991-ba58-7e949c240c9a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
