<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/00b3986e-a443-4a6f-abdb-97c2161def16> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Normalize crate-version descriptor in SCIP symbols at KG minting" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/00b3986e-a443-4a6f-abdb-97c2161def16> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/accf4f9f-6309-4d3f-8705-26e551824eb0> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/00b3986e-a443-4a6f-abdb-97c2161def16> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#constrains> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/136dbf24-e8aa-4dd3-9eac-9fc8ac03296b> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/00b3986e-a443-4a6f-abdb-97c2161def16> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#constrains> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/CodeEntity/99ce662a-5e4b-42f7-bb72-e89b335d117f> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/00b3986e-a443-4a6f-abdb-97c2161def16> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/00b3986e-a443-4a6f-abdb-97c2161def16> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "rust-analyzer SCIP symbol strings embed the crate version (e.g. `rust-analyzer cargo moosedev 0.6.3 src/main.rs/parse_mode().`) — Spike A finding, 2026-07-06. Raw symbols are therefore NOT stable continuant identity across releases: every version bump would re-mint every continuant IRI and orphan all attached knowledge. The KG-skeleton minting slice MUST normalize the version descriptor out of the symbol (or key continuants on a version-stripped form) before minting IRIs (AD 136dbf24: SCIP symbol grammar as identity — the grammar, not the raw string). Within one index the raw string remains the resolver's exact key; the tests already shield themselves via suffix matching (see the suffix-stable fixtures decision). Binds the KG-skeleton minting slice." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/00b3986e-a443-4a6f-abdb-97c2161def16> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/00b3986e-a443-4a6f-abdb-97c2161def16> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-07-07T19:19:49.490287Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/00b3986e-a443-4a6f-abdb-97c2161def16> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Normalize crate-version descriptor in SCIP symbols at KG minting" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/0c2106ab-710d-4435-9413-67f6152d0e83> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Constraint> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/0c2106ab-710d-4435-9413-67f6152d0e83> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "MOOSE embeddings bound to T-box alignment, not A-box" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/0c2106ab-710d-4435-9413-67f6152d0e83> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/0c2106ab-710d-4435-9413-67f6152d0e83> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Core MOOSE capability gap surfaced while designing semantic recall and instance dedup. MOOSE exposes its embedding capability through alignment::suggest_parent (LeafClassInput -> AlignmentOutcome), i.e. matching a new concept to ontology *classes* (T-box). The A-box retrieval path, EntityIndexCache::search_classes, is purely lexical (label-token scoring, IndexMatch.score), with no embedding/semantic option. There is no MOOSE primitive for \"find recorded *instances* semantically similar to this candidate instance\" — the exact operation both embedding-ranked recall and instance dedup/contradiction detection require. Workaround needing no MOOSE change: moosedev already builds an ontology vector store via moose::embeddings::default_backbone(), and the same backbone can embed instance text for cosine similarity inside moosedev. But a first-class MOOSE A-box similarity/retrieval API is the clean home for it (invariant #8: prefer composing MOOSE over reimplementing core neurosymbolic logic). No custom pipeline required for this — distinct from the forthcoming Generate workflow, which will need one." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/0c2106ab-710d-4435-9413-67f6152d0e83> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "superseded" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/0c2106ab-710d-4435-9413-67f6152d0e83> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-18T03:48:48.303192Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/0c2106ab-710d-4435-9413-67f6152d0e83> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "MOOSE embedding similarity is bound to T-box term alignment, not A-box retrieval" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/19bb4d8a-9da8-4aba-97c1-73e5ed9aa41f> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Constraint> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/19bb4d8a-9da8-4aba-97c1-73e5ed9aa41f> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Resolve ontology IRIs by local-name, never hardcode" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/19bb4d8a-9da8-4aba-97c1-73e5ed9aa41f> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/11e01ea2-f520-4f7c-a165-09532dacd43f> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
