<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/19bb4d8a-9da8-4aba-97c1-73e5ed9aa41f> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#constrains> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/f68ef43e-7bec-4616-8e0d-e9c0cbb9cc55> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/19bb4d8a-9da8-4aba-97c1-73e5ed9aa41f> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#constrains> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/CodeEntity/ed273588-ce6e-4719-b973-764fe82ca2f8> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/19bb4d8a-9da8-4aba-97c1-73e5ed9aa41f> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/19bb4d8a-9da8-4aba-97c1-73e5ed9aa41f> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Code that needs an ontology class or property IRI MUST resolve it by local-name from the loaded vocabulary at runtime — never embed a namespace or full IRI string literal. The single lookup point is `iri_by_local_name(entries, local)` (src/graph/mod.rs:79), wrapped by `datatype_property_iri(vocab, local)` (:87), `object_property_iri(vocab, local)` (:96), and the AppState methods `resolve_class(kind)` (:197) and `resolve_object_property(local)` (:205), all reading from `self.arch_vocab` (CompactVocabulary loaded by ontology::load_ontologies). The code's own doc comments state the intent: 'keeping the volatile namespace out of the code' and 'the full IRI (and namespace) comes from the ontology, not from code.' Rationale: the ontology namespace is volatile and the T-box can be regenerated/renamed; hardcoded namespaces silently rot and orphan data on a breaking ontology change (this is the coding-side counterpart to Requirement 74423463, 'Migrate existing A-box instances on breaking ontology change', which likewise says 're-type via a mapping — never hardcode old namespaces'). The same discipline appears in the bench tooling, which matches predicates by STRENDS(local-name) rather than hardcoding the namespace. Violation pattern: a string literal containing an ontology base URL (e.g. https://trivyn.io/ontologies/... or a moosedev ontology IRI) used to construct a class/property IRI. Compliant pattern: call one of the resolvers above with just the local name." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/19bb4d8a-9da8-4aba-97c1-73e5ed9aa41f> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/19bb4d8a-9da8-4aba-97c1-73e5ed9aa41f> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-18T17:56:59.003929Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/19bb4d8a-9da8-4aba-97c1-73e5ed9aa41f> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Resolve ontology class/property IRIs by local-name from the loaded vocab; never hardcode namespaces or full IRIs in code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/2ba76439-e146-425d-b18a-4d46f7418cb8> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Constraint> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/2ba76439-e146-425d-b18a-4d46f7418cb8> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Every surface is a thin client of the one policy engine" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/2ba76439-e146-425d-b18a-4d46f7418cb8> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#constrains> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/2501ffa4-42d9-4d23-9185-e191ca70ea63> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/2ba76439-e146-425d-b18a-4d46f7418cb8> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#constrains> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/4db59805-ebd6-4209-a564-de6a2656c354> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/2ba76439-e146-425d-b18a-4d46f7418cb8> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#constrains> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/681698b3-bcb5-447f-b93a-600f94277e32> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/2ba76439-e146-425d-b18a-4d46f7418cb8> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#constrains> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/72dc4260-2f0c-47d3-967e-44a981e0c248> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/2ba76439-e146-425d-b18a-4d46f7418cb8> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/2ba76439-e146-425d-b18a-4d46f7418cb8> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Constraint: no surface — LSP server, editor extension, host-harness adapter, workbench — may build its own index, cache logic, or policy; all reads and writes go through the daemon's queries, and all writes route through the ratification gate. Why: the human-view/agent-view identity guarantee (the editor hover and the agent's pushed dossier are the SAME query) holds only while there is exactly one brain; the moment a surface grows its own index the views drift and the shared-world-model claim is false. Also prevents write-path side doors into the graph. \"No second brain.\"" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/2ba76439-e146-425d-b18a-4d46f7418cb8> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/2ba76439-e146-425d-b18a-4d46f7418cb8> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-07-03T22:19:10.51288Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/2ba76439-e146-425d-b18a-4d46f7418cb8> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Every surface is a thin client of the one policy engine" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/71637748-2eb5-4231-839e-e4718f74387f> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Constraint> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/71637748-2eb5-4231-839e-e4718f74387f> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "MOOSE doesn't index A-box; walk planning for precision" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/71637748-2eb5-4231-839e-e4718f74387f> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#constrains> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/72e9ca40-1310-4f13-a90d-bc87beaee200> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/71637748-2eb5-4231-839e-e4718f74387f> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/71637748-2eb5-4231-839e-e4718f74387f> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Design boundary to respect: MOOSE indexes instance *labels* lexically only for entity *resolution* (anchoring a walk), and never builds a semantic/vector index over instance *content* for retrieval. Retrieval precision is delivered by symbolic walk planning from resolved anchors over typed relationships (with a reasoning trace), not by nearest-neighbor over instance embeddings. Therefore: do NOT reintroduce instance vector indexing in moosedev to \"improve\" recall or dedup. Use query (walk planning) and sparql for precision; keep get_relevant_context a shallow lexical anchor/browse tool. Embedding use stays confined to T-box term alignment (suggest_parent), where the corpus is static and the operation is class placement, not instance retrieval." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/71637748-2eb5-4231-839e-e4718f74387f> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "superseded" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/71637748-2eb5-4231-839e-e4718f74387f> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasRationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/262a87b8-8a96-49be-bb11-4fdcbe22fb1a> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/71637748-2eb5-4231-839e-e4718f74387f> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-18T04:57:07.675692Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/71637748-2eb5-4231-839e-e4718f74387f> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "MOOSE deliberately does not index instance (A-box) data; precision comes from walk planning" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/71637748-2eb5-4231-839e-e4718f74387f> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#supersedes> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/0c2106ab-710d-4435-9413-67f6152d0e83> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/720dcd1c-26cc-43cb-b437-ee28a2f6a475> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Constraint> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/720dcd1c-26cc-43cb-b437-ee28a2f6a475> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Topology must derive from SCIP reference occurrences" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/720dcd1c-26cc-43cb-b437-ee28a2f6a475> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/accf4f9f-6309-4d3f-8705-26e551824eb0> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/720dcd1c-26cc-43cb-b437-ee28a2f6a475> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#constrains> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/992f3f10-b1ec-408f-b0c1-8c46cf441657> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/720dcd1c-26cc-43cb-b437-ee28a2f6a475> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#constrains> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/CodeEntity/0862dfd3-173f-45c3-8c4d-cc5ef6a401e7> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/720dcd1c-26cc-43cb-b437-ee28a2f6a475> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/720dcd1c-26cc-43cb-b437-ee28a2f6a475> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "rust-analyzer's SCIP emitter produces ZERO `relationships` and an empty `external_symbols` list (measured empirically in Spike A, 2026-07-06, on the moosedev repo: 78 documents / 39,896 occurrences, and re-confirmed at slice-1 index time). Consequence: stratum-1 topology (calls/uses/implements, fan-in/out, blast radius — spec §3.4) CANNOT be read from SCIP relationship edges; it must be derived by joining reference occurrences to definition sites (a reference to symbol S inside the range of entity E's definition ⇒ E uses S). Binds the KG-skeleton/topology slice: budget for this derivation pass, and do not design queries assuming producer-supplied relationship edges." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/720dcd1c-26cc-43cb-b437-ee28a2f6a475> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/720dcd1c-26cc-43cb-b437-ee28a2f6a475> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-07-07T19:19:36.975724Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/720dcd1c-26cc-43cb-b437-ee28a2f6a475> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Topology must derive from SCIP reference occurrences" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/72d7a908-30da-431f-b914-731b77996666> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Constraint> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/72d7a908-30da-431f-b914-731b77996666> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "GROWL enrichment needs reasoning axioms in the ontology" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/72d7a908-30da-431f-b914-731b77996666> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/72d7a908-30da-431f-b914-731b77996666> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "GROWL's --enrich materializes only what the ontology DECLARES as OWL 2 RL axioms: owl:inverseOf, TransitiveProperty, propertyChainAxiom, subPropertyOf, domain/range. Lesson 96456e40 established the relationship PROPERTIES are defined (so the flat graph is a capture-tooling gap, not a vocabulary gap) — this adds a DISTINCT gap: the ontology lacks the reasoning AXIOMS that gate materialization. software-architecture.ttl currently declares no inverse object properties (user-confirmed; likely no transitivity/chains either) — an UPSTREAM, Trivyn-owned fix, since the ontology is the shared semantic contract (don't fork it in moosedev). Inverses buy bidirectional walk; transitivity buys supersede-closure; property chains mint genuinely-new edges — worth declaring all three in one pass. Enrichment can't outrun the axioms." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/72d7a908-30da-431f-b914-731b77996666> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/72d7a908-30da-431f-b914-731b77996666> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-21T23:49:01.805337Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/72d7a908-30da-431f-b914-731b77996666> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "GROWL enrichment needs reasoning axioms in the ontology" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/75b0cf14-3722-47af-95f1-c6d9ac65ea43> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Constraint> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/75b0cf14-3722-47af-95f1-c6d9ac65ea43> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "In-anger trial: kill/abandon condition (frozen thresholds)" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/75b0cf14-3722-47af-95f1-c6d9ac65ea43> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#constrains> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/07415633-e7f0-410b-9eec-2a7bf9fcff97> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/75b0cf14-3722-47af-95f1-c6d9ac65ea43> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#constrains> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d3d4d7b1-a904-4519-98d8-31a24bffa125> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/75b0cf14-3722-47af-95f1-c6d9ac65ea43> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/75b0cf14-3722-47af-95f1-c6d9ac65ea43> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Frozen pre-registered kill/abandon condition for the in-anger trial (companion to operational-protocol AD 07415633; operationalizes d3d4d7b1). Set ONCE before month 1; NOT revised mid-trial.\n\nPRIMARY (engagement): if by END OF MONTH 2 sustained unprompted graph-assist fires are < 4 per project per month AND not trending up, the graph is not earning its place in the workflow -> ABANDON (the trial AD's own 'not reaching for it unprompted by month 2' criterion).\n\nSECONDARY (signal): if by END OF MONTH 3 the probe gap (judge(B2) - judge(B0)) is NOT widening beyond the month-0 baseline gap (within LLM-judge noise) on BOTH projects, the comprehension-debt thesis is not manifesting in the measurement -> DOWNGRADE/ABANDON.\n\nTRIPWIRE (cost/trust): if capture+recall overhead becomes net-negative — latency or friction makes the maintainer stop reaching for the graph unprompted — -> ABANDON.\n\nCrossing PRIMARY, or persistent SECONDARY, triggers an explicit go/no-go writeup recorded as a Lesson — never silent drift (invariant #6). These thresholds are deliberately conservative: the trial should be cheap to keep and easy to honestly kill." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/75b0cf14-3722-47af-95f1-c6d9ac65ea43> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/75b0cf14-3722-47af-95f1-c6d9ac65ea43> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-24T07:28:13.989063Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/75b0cf14-3722-47af-95f1-c6d9ac65ea43> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "In-anger trial: kill/abandon condition (frozen thresholds)" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/aa8b3fa3-6432-48da-8d1b-07fdb395f7f0> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Constraint> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/aa8b3fa3-6432-48da-8d1b-07fdb395f7f0> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Relational expansion in get_relevant_context must be bounded" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/aa8b3fa3-6432-48da-8d1b-07fdb395f7f0> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#constrains> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b933bd10-de56-4481-91dd-397a192a8022> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/aa8b3fa3-6432-48da-8d1b-07fdb395f7f0> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/aa8b3fa3-6432-48da-8d1b-07fdb395f7f0> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Design constraint for Phase 3 (relational expansion). Because MOOSEDev's demonstrated value is EFFICIENCY (fewer tokens + less thrashing — AD 7b824b26) and local models have tight context windows with silent LM Studio middle-truncation (Lesson 5ac2174a), get_relevant_context's edge-following expansion must be surgical, not exhaustive. Hard bounds: (1) expand only from the TOP few BM25 seed hits, not all `limit`; (2) follow only record→record edges (object is an InformationRecord) — this excludes the prov:* metadata firehose while keeping violates/isMotivatedBy/supersedes/hasRationale; (3) at most ~2 hops with a HARD GLOBAL CAP on total appended records (~5) so 2-hop reach doesn't blow up combinatorially; (4) dedup against seeds + already-expanded; (5) respect currency — do not expand into superseded/deprecated records unless include_history; (6) render appended records tersely (labeled 'via <relation>'), keeping |seeds| + |expanded| bounded. The goal is to reach the few linked records that COMPLETE an answer (e.g. the lexically-distant AD that holds the deep 'why'), not to dump the neighborhood. Caps should be constants/params so the benchmark can tune them. Governs the implementation of the relate()-enabled traversal (AD d542b826)." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/aa8b3fa3-6432-48da-8d1b-07fdb395f7f0> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "proposed" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/aa8b3fa3-6432-48da-8d1b-07fdb395f7f0> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-19T14:39:50.65501Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/aa8b3fa3-6432-48da-8d1b-07fdb395f7f0> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Relational expansion in get_relevant_context must be BOUNDED and net-efficient — a budgeted reach to answer-bearing records, never a neighborhood dump" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/af5ebd6d-e7de-49ef-ac64-f891252e86a8> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Constraint> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/af5ebd6d-e7de-49ef-ac64-f891252e86a8> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "A-box dense allowed only as a bounded seed" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/af5ebd6d-e7de-49ef-ac64-f891252e86a8> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#constrains> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b933bd10-de56-4481-91dd-397a192a8022> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/af5ebd6d-e7de-49ef-ac64-f891252e86a8> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/af5ebd6d-e7de-49ef-ac64-f891252e86a8> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Narrows (supersedes) the outright ban in 71637748. MOOSE core now ships a coherent, model-stamped instance vector store (InstanceVecStore) with a matched query/document embedding pair (retrieval_embed_query/_document) and a raw-cosine confidence floor (DEFAULT_DENSE_FLOOR). Given that, A-box dense retrieval is permitted — but ONLY as a SEED channel for get_relevant_context, under these rules: (1) Dense only SEEDS; it feeds the bounded typed expansion (Constraint aa8b3fa3) and never replaces walk planning — query (graph-walk NLQ) and sparql remain the precision, dedup, and complete-read tools. (2) Symbolic-first anchoring: an exact (normalized) rdfs:label/hasTitle match resolves the named record and seeds it FIRST, ahead of lexical+dense (invariant #1 — symbolic layer primary; dense is the open-vocabulary fallback sensor). (3) The dense channel is gated by a confidence floor on the RAW cosine (DEFAULT_DENSE_FLOOR=0.5; MOOSEDEV_DENSE_FLOOR override), preserving the honest empty state (invariant #6): cosine has no natural zero, so without the floor RRF would manufacture a nearest neighbor for an irrelevant query. (4) Retrieval stays auditable: HybridMatch exposes per-channel diagnostics (bm25f, dense_cosine, ranks). (5) The index is DURABLE (instance-vectors.db) and reconciled INCREMENTALLY at startup (only records not already embedded; batched), and kept coherent on write (index_record), so startup cost is proportional to churn, not graph size. Embeddings stay confined to: T-box term alignment (unchanged) + this bounded A-box seed channel. NOT permitted: dense instance retrieval as a substitute for walk-planning precision, or an unfiltered dense channel (no floor)." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/af5ebd6d-e7de-49ef-ac64-f891252e86a8> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/af5ebd6d-e7de-49ef-ac64-f891252e86a8> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasRationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/5e8e2a69-a7af-41df-a8bf-23ead1ecb62f> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/af5ebd6d-e7de-49ef-ac64-f891252e86a8> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-21T07:23:17.439642Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/af5ebd6d-e7de-49ef-ac64-f891252e86a8> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Instance (A-box) dense retrieval is permitted only as a bounded SEED for get_relevant_context; walk planning remains the precision engine" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/af5ebd6d-e7de-49ef-ac64-f891252e86a8> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#supersedes> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/71637748-2eb5-4231-839e-e4718f74387f> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/ea2a00f5-e654-4589-91df-40448b5d7bab> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Constraint> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/ea2a00f5-e654-4589-91df-40448b5d7bab> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "--serve and --connect must share MOOSEDEV_DATA_DIR" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/ea2a00f5-e654-4589-91df-40448b5d7bab> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#constrains> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/bf838e2e-5320-4df7-8469-883e5b0155d6> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/ea2a00f5-e654-4589-91df-40448b5d7bab> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#constrains> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/ca1e5be2-308b-40ca-a928-dc286a20695b> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/ea2a00f5-e654-4589-91df-40448b5d7bab> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/ea2a00f5-e654-4589-91df-40448b5d7bab> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "The Unix-socket rendezvous path is derived per data dir by socket_path_for(data_dir): <canonicalized data_dir>/moosedev.sock. The data dir comes from MOOSEDEV_DATA_DIR (default \"data\", which is relative and canonicalized against the process cwd). Therefore the --serve backend and every --connect client MUST be launched with the same MOOSEDEV_DATA_DIR (and compatible cwd) or they compute different socket paths and the client reports \"Failed to connect\" even though a daemon is running.\n\nObserved 2026-06-17: Claude Code and Codex MCP configs both set MOOSEDEV_DATA_DIR=/Users/jcadam/code/moosedev/.moosedev (the real accumulated graph, ~3400 triples), but a manually-started `--serve` with the env unset defaulted to data/, listened on data/moosedev.sock, and the clients looking for .moosedev/moosedev.sock could not connect. Fix: start the daemon with the matching data dir: MOOSEDEV_DATA_DIR=.../.moosedev moosedev --serve.\n\nMitigations to consider (runtime.rs already flags auto-spawn as a later pass): log the resolved data dir + socket path at --serve startup so a mismatch is obvious; have --connect auto-spawn the backend when none is listening so the two can never disagree on the path." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/ea2a00f5-e654-4589-91df-40448b5d7bab> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/ea2a00f5-e654-4589-91df-40448b5d7bab> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-18T01:01:33.668619Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Constraint/ea2a00f5-e654-4589-91df-40448b5d7bab> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "--serve and --connect must share MOOSEDEV_DATA_DIR or they pick different sockets" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/02147e6d-5359-4f9a-b82a-9a5fce8580c3> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/02147e6d-5359-4f9a-b82a-9a5fce8580c3> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Currency A/B, 4 reversal pairs: structured guarantees current" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/02147e6d-5359-4f9a-b82a-9a5fce8580c3> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/02147e6d-5359-4f9a-b82a-9a5fce8580c3> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Extends the single-pair clean currency win with 3 more reversal pairs from the temporal graph (oracle push, codex-spark N=5): ontology stub->production, --connect manual->auto-spawn, supersede_decision AD-only->all-InformationRecord-kinds (plus the original get_relevant_context pure-symbolic->BM25).\n\nRESULT. B2 (current-only graph) = 100% current on ALL 4 pairs — guaranteed currency, content-independent. B1-rag (currency-blind free-text) = 0% current on get_relevant_context (served the superseded answer) but ~100% current on the other 3.\n\nMECHANISM (why free-text fails on only 1 of 4): free-text serves stale iff the SUPERSEDED record is the top BM25 hit for the query AND the current record doesn't lexically announce the change. get_relevant_context hits both conditions — the stale record's title ('get_relevant_context: pure-symbolic context retrieval') is the dominant lexical match, so the push leads with it and the agent answers from #1, even though the current record is also in the top-k. The other 3 pairs DON'T: the current record ranks competitively and SELF-ANNOUNCES ('stub retired', '--connect auto-spawns', 'generalized to InformationRecord'), so the agent reasons to current. The graph excludes superseded by construction -> current regardless of phrasing or rank.\n\nREFRAMED CLAIM (honest, invariant #6): the robust, generalizable structured win is the GUARANTEE of currency (B2 100% across all 4 pairs, all models codex-spark/gpt-5.4-mini/gpt-5.5); free-text currency-correctness is a content-and-ranking GAMBLE that fails silently + catastrophically on the unlucky reversals (1/4 here) with no way to predict which. Lifecycle curation removes the gamble — that is the value, NOT a universal 0%-vs-100%. Efficiency finding stands (B2 oracle ~13K tokens, cheapest correct path; B1 tooluse 113-187K; gpt-5.4-mini is the tool-use sweet spot at 29K vs spark's 187K).\n\nCAVEATS: oracle/push mode is the clean isolation; the stale-marker diagnostic is NOISY (fires when an agent merely EXPLAINS the change, e.g. 'no longer temporary', while answering current), so current%/coverage is the cleaner signal; keyword grading; one repo's graph. Still overturns the earlier 'structured representation never wins' (aaee7652) -> structured wins on currency, conditionally and with a guarantee free-text cannot match." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/02147e6d-5359-4f9a-b82a-9a5fce8580c3> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/02147e6d-5359-4f9a-b82a-9a5fce8580c3> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasRationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/abe11031-8ec9-4ac4-bf3e-49bbb5884e87> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/02147e6d-5359-4f9a-b82a-9a5fce8580c3> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-19T23:50:30.250542Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/02147e6d-5359-4f9a-b82a-9a5fce8580c3> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Currency A/B across 4 reversal pairs: structured memory GUARANTEES current (B2 100%/pair, all models); free-text currency is a RANK-dependent gamble — catastrophic (0%) only when the superseded record outranks the current in BM25, else it recovers (~100%)" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/02147e6d-5359-4f9a-b82a-9a5fce8580c3> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#supersedes> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/d967f228-1b55-465d-845f-20d484a19880> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/0293c375-cc58-43d8-99fc-5dfe5d47088d> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/0293c375-cc58-43d8-99fc-5dfe5d47088d> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Lifecycle tests must cross the process-group boundary" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/0293c375-cc58-43d8-99fc-5dfe5d47088d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "codex-mcp-client" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/0293c375-cc58-43d8-99fc-5dfe5d47088d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Pattern: The initial `--connect` auto-spawn test killed only the proxy PID and asserted the daemon survived. That proves ordinary child reparenting, but it does not exercise the load-bearing `process_group(0)` isolation that protects the daemon when an MCP-client shell tears down the proxy process group. Rule: tests for process-group/session isolation must send a signal to the parent/proxy process group and assert the detached child still serves; killing one PID is insufficient because it passes even if the isolation call is removed." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/0293c375-cc58-43d8-99fc-5dfe5d47088d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/0293c375-cc58-43d8-99fc-5dfe5d47088d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-18T03:14:32.495364Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/0293c375-cc58-43d8-99fc-5dfe5d47088d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Lifecycle tests must signal the actual process group boundary" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/046bc2d8-18cc-4ddd-8c2a-a5200fc3647e> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/046bc2d8-18cc-4ddd-8c2a-a5200fc3647e> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Ecological currency: B2 beats real notes, cheaper" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/046bc2d8-18cc-4ddd-8c2a-a5200fc3647e> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/046bc2d8-18cc-4ddd-8c2a-a5200fc3647e> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "First ecological free-text run (AD b3205dcb): B1-notes = agent greps trivyn's REAL accumulated docs (lessons.md + topical guides + CONVENTIONS, 287KB) vs B2 = MOOSEDev temporal graph vs B0 = cold; gpt-5.4-mini via codex, tooluse, N=3, 4 currency tasks. RESULTS: (1) EFFICIENCY (clean, NOT prompt-contaminated): B2 is 1.3-2.6x CHEAPER than B1-notes on EVERY task and faster (local_embeddings 56k vs 143k tok, 15s vs 28s; nlq 125k vs 276k; geospatial 47k vs 78k; owl 79k vs 100k) — B1-notes pays to grep/read 287KB, B2 does ONE query. This is the H2/H3 token+speed win at realistic scale that the small corpora + content-parity baseline could never surface. (2) CURRENCY: B2 DECISIVELY beats B1-notes on local_embeddings — all 3 B1-notes trials confidently served the STALE answer ('Trivyn produces local embeddings via its Candle-backed CUDA/Metal path with CPU fallback, NOT routing through MOOSE'), actively DENYING the current answer, because the team's notes still describe the old Candle path and were never updated after embeddings were rerouted through MOOSE; B2 (supersession-aware, current-only) served current ('routed through MOOSE's default backbone') 3/3. nlq_filter + geospatial TIED (the notes happened to be current there; both arms correct). owl_reasoner contaminated (prompt names 'growl' -> even B0 echoes it). SIGNIFICANCE: FIRST demonstration of free-text currency FAILURE against a REALISTIC baseline; VINDICATES the ecological-baseline decision (b3205dcb) and the user's construct-validity critique. The content-parity baseline (graph export, self-announcing records) HID the currency advantage ('free-text recovers by construction', Lesson 9e7ebeb6); REAL notes reveal it because they GO STALE (nobody updates old entries after a reversal). The prior 'currency null at scale' (6b2d1f55, 9e7ebeb6) is therefore CONFIRMED an ARTIFACT of the content-parity baseline; against ecological notes, B2 wins on stale-note topics AND is cheaper everywhere. HONEST CAVEATS: (a) the binary-choice PROMPTS leak the current answer (named 'backbone'/'growl'/'LCASE'/'wktLiteral' in the question) so coverage is contaminated (cov=1.0 for ALL arms incl. cold B0) and owl_reasoner is fully leaked; the local_embeddings win is ROBUST DESPITE the leak (B1-notes ignored the prompt hint and served stale from the notes), but a clean re-run needs OPEN-ENDED prompts. (b) coverage was also FOOLED on local_embeddings B1-notes (cov=1.0 matched a NEGATED 'routing through MOOSE'), so the STRICT-currency verdict (coverage==1 AND no asserted-stale) + READING final_text was essential (reinforces Lesson 9fc21dc0). (c) N=3, one model, 4 tasks; currency win is 1/4, conditional on note staleness (realistic but variable). NEXT: open-ended prompts + more tasks to characterize the currency-win rate; efficiency win is already solid and clean. Relates to b3205dcb, 9e7ebeb6, 6b2d1f55, 9fc21dc0, fa9170f6, f2f4cd99." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/046bc2d8-18cc-4ddd-8c2a-a5200fc3647e> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "proposed" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/046bc2d8-18cc-4ddd-8c2a-a5200fc3647e> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-20T16:10:09.969051Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/046bc2d8-18cc-4ddd-8c2a-a5200fc3647e> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Ecological currency run VINDICATED: vs trivyn's REAL 287KB notes (not the graph export), B2 decisively beats B1-notes on local_embeddings (B1-notes served stale Candle 3/3; B2 current MOOSE 3/3) and B2 is 1.3-2.6x cheaper everywhere — content-parity hid both" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/06f53ce2-8df2-45c0-b0a0-892ab6089479> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/06f53ce2-8df2-45c0-b0a0-892ab6089479> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Acceptance test runs must preserve the exit code: no tail/head pipelines" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/06f53ce2-8df2-45c0-b0a0-892ab6089479> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "phase7-acceptance" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/06f53ce2-8df2-45c0-b0a0-892ab6089479> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "The first Phase 7 full-suite run was piped through tail -60, which made the pipeline exit 0 while cargo test had FAILED (resolver acceptance 8/40) and truncated the log to the last 60 lines. Rule: capture acceptance/verification runs with full output redirected to a file and check the command exit code plus per-binary result lines; never gate a verdict on a pipeline whose last stage is a filter. Complements the existing verification lessons: one orchestrator full-suite pass only counts if its exit status is actually observed." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/06f53ce2-8df2-45c0-b0a0-892ab6089479> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/06f53ce2-8df2-45c0-b0a0-892ab6089479> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-07-09T05:41:23.583446Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/06f53ce2-8df2-45c0-b0a0-892ab6089479> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Acceptance test runs must preserve the exit code: no tail/head pipelines" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/07efe798-acd4-4c6b-aebf-4318d2e0460e> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/07efe798-acd4-4c6b-aebf-4318d2e0460e> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "opencode local plugins export only plugin functions" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/07efe798-acd4-4c6b-aebf-4318d2e0460e> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "codex-mcp-client" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/07efe798-acd4-4c6b-aebf-4318d2e0460e> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "While implementing the MOOSEDev push plugin, opencode 1.17.x discovered the local .opencode/plugins/moosedev-push.ts file but rejected it with \"Plugin export is not a function\" when the module also exported a string id. The loader treats exported values as plugin functions, matching the docs' \"exports one or more plugin functions\" wording. Rule: local opencode plugin files should export only plugin function values; keep metadata as internal constants or comments, not module exports. Verification: after removing non-function exports and leaving one named async plugin function, `opencode debug config` loaded the plugin with no failed-load log." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/07efe798-acd4-4c6b-aebf-4318d2e0460e> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/07efe798-acd4-4c6b-aebf-4318d2e0460e> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-19T03:18:45.864252Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/07efe798-acd4-4c6b-aebf-4318d2e0460e> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "opencode local plugin modules must export only plugin functions" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/083473b5-4037-4e51-b594-f301bc4dea44> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/083473b5-4037-4e51-b594-f301bc4dea44> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Artifact skills should call checked-in generators" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/083473b5-4037-4e51-b594-f301bc4dea44> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "codex" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/083473b5-4037-4e51-b594-f301bc4dea44> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "When a graph-rendering skill needs nontrivial transformation logic, keep that logic in a checked-in generator and have the skill call it as the fast path. Do not expect each agent to recreate one-off scripts during execution; that leads to drift in markdown, status mapping, verification, and edge handling. The skill should remain the contract and fallback workflow, while the script is the shared implementation." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/083473b5-4037-4e51-b594-f301bc4dea44> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/083473b5-4037-4e51-b594-f301bc4dea44> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-25T16:59:14.582365Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/083473b5-4037-4e51-b594-f301bc4dea44> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Artifact skills should call checked-in generators" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/083473b5-4037-4e51-b594-f301bc4dea44> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#learnedFrom> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/233f460f-4f5c-4ac2-9e28-1405b6acf1a2> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/083473b5-4037-4e51-b594-f301bc4dea44> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#learnedFrom> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/87f558c6-e69b-41c7-9cfe-b000d6e1cc50> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/094087c7-654d-4af5-a873-68ecff0d30c0> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/094087c7-654d-4af5-a873-68ecff0d30c0> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Agent-initiated PULL fails for local models" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/094087c7-654d-4af5-a873-68ecff0d30c0> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/094087c7-654d-4af5-a873-68ecff0d30c0> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Evidence from the value benchmark + a Codex spike. In opencode (moosedev MCP offered, symmetric \"consult project memory\" guidance verified IN-CONTEXT via two no-tool probes, AGENTS.md confirmed loaded even under --pure), local models — qwen A3B and 27B, gemma-4-26b-a4b, gemma-4-31b dense — NEVER called get_relevant_context on coding tasks; all scored 0.4 using only read/edit/shell. In Codex (the harness the user observed pulling moosedev with GPT-5.5), a local gemma run with moosedev OFFERED (get_relevant_context appeared in 158 requests in the LM Studio log), the guidance overlay present, and the response cap cleared STILL used only exec_command (zero moosedev calls). So local-no-pull reproduces across two independent harnesses → it is a MODEL-capability property, not an opencode artifact. The harness only modulates FRONTIER pull-reliability (GPT-5.5 pulls reliably in Codex, inconsistently in opencode). Why: agent-initiated retrieval is gated by the model deciding to call a tool, which sub-frontier models won't do during coding. How to apply: for the local/self-hosted regime, ship PUSH (proactive injection); do not rely on pull. Directly motivates the push-mechanism ArchitecturalDecision." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/094087c7-654d-4af5-a873-68ecff0d30c0> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "superseded" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/094087c7-654d-4af5-a873-68ecff0d30c0> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-19T02:49:11.997601Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/094087c7-654d-4af5-a873-68ecff0d30c0> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Agent-initiated PULL of memory fails for local models across BOTH opencode and Codex — a model property, not a harness artifact" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/0a890ea9-f64f-42da-9e9c-764524d6276a> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/0a890ea9-f64f-42da-9e9c-764524d6276a> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "A dead MCP masquerades as a weak-model / capability problem — verify the tool launched" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/0a890ea9-f64f-42da-9e9c-764524d6276a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/0a890ea9-f64f-42da-9e9c-764524d6276a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "A silently-dead MCP server makes a coding agent fall back to grepping/exploring, which looks EXACTLY like a weak tool-caller, a prompt problem, or a memory-tool capability gap — but isn't. ROOT CAUSE here: a narrow .env secret-loader I added to config.py (_load_dotenv, for OPENROUTER_API_KEY) loaded the moosedev binary's WHOLE repo .env, which sets MOOSEDEV_BIN=$ROOT/target/release/moosedev (unexpanded $ROOT). That literal path overrode the valid computed default, so the codex MCP client command pointed at a nonexistent binary -> the moosedev server never launched -> get_relevant_context was never available -> EVERY B2 agent (gpt-5.4-mini, gpt-5.4 full, gpt-5.5) \"fell back\" to ripgrepping ~/.moosedev-stores/codegraph (0.5-1.2M tokens), which masqueraded as 'B2 thrashes on relevance' and 'mem0 wins relevance'.\n\nTHE TELL (how to detect it): tool_counts shows NO get_relevant_context, only list_mcp_resources/list_mcp_resource_templates (empty) or {} with huge tokens from command_execution (shell) reading the store files. The oracle path made it VISIBLE by raising FileNotFoundError on the bad bin; the tooluse path hid it (silent fallback to grep).\n\nPROOF IT WAS THE BUG: after fixing config (whitelist .env to OPENROUTER_API_KEY only + defensive MOOSEDEV_BIN that falls back to the valid default if the env path does not exist), the SAME gpt-5.4-mini called get_relevant_context 4/4, ~35k tokens (down from 0.5-1.2M), cov 0.82 — and B2 then TIES mem0 on relevance (mem0 ~40k). The weak-model, prompt, and store-grep-instinct hypotheses were all refuted.\n\nHOW TO APPLY: (1) before attributing agent behavior to model/prompt/capability, VERIFY the MCP tool actually launched (check tool_counts for the expected tool; a run that only greps + never calls the memory tool = suspect a dead server). (2) Never load a tool's whole .env into a bench's config; whitelist secrets and keep computed path defaults authoritative; make critical path config defensive (fall back if the env path does not exist). (3) An error in ONE code path (oracle) can expose a confound that a SILENT path (tooluse fallback) hides — chase the visible crash. Corrects the relevance half of Lesson 8120780a (to be superseded) and reframes Lesson f8f2f87c (the 1.68M set-completeness cost was this dead-MCP grep, not 'agent query competence'). Relates to 47f3f038 (bench design)." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/0a890ea9-f64f-42da-9e9c-764524d6276a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/0a890ea9-f64f-42da-9e9c-764524d6276a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-23T19:01:41.717919Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/0a890ea9-f64f-42da-9e9c-764524d6276a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "A dead MCP masquerades as a weak-model / capability problem — verify the tool launched" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/0a890ea9-f64f-42da-9e9c-764524d6276a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#learnedFrom> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/47f3f038-8fd7-4a96-9c74-15a24bf8be17> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/0b2a0f80-2902-49af-88d1-22906884614a> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/0b2a0f80-2902-49af-88d1-22906884614a> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Flat trivyn corpus makes B2 ≈ B1" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/0b2a0f80-2902-49af-88d1-22906884614a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/0b2a0f80-2902-49af-88d1-22906884614a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Verified via sparql against the trivyn store: all 89 records have hasLifecycleStatus 'accepted' (none superseded); there is NO supersede-like predicate; and there are ZERO domain-record→domain-record edges (the records do not link to each other). So the graph is a flat bag of independent typed records. Consequence: B2's get_relevant_context is symbolic but LEXICAL (BM25), so on a flat bag it has no traversal or lifecycle advantage over B1 free-text RAG — they retrieve the same records the same way. This mechanistically explains and GENERALIZES the single-hop null (Lesson 679a69af, and the whynot_tlo_merge result fa9170f6): the null is not fundamentally about hop-count, it is about the ABSENCE OF EXPLOITABLE STRUCTURE. To demonstrate structured>free-text (invariant #2), the graph must first contain the structure MOOSEDev uniquely manages — supersession/currency chains (the pre-registered H4 'structural kill-shot') or typed multi-hop links — and the task must require using it. Additional constraint from export_corpus.py: the B1 export bakes only `# title + description` into the searchable text and keeps lifecycle status as UNINDEXED metadata, so even once supersessions exist, B1 RAG is currency-blind by construction (a fair-parity currency test should put status into the B1 text so the only difference is whether the delivery ACTS on the lifecycle). Implication for the structured-memory thesis: its value is conditional on the graph having structure; on a flat capture it degrades to free-text parity." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/0b2a0f80-2902-49af-88d1-22906884614a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "proposed" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/0b2a0f80-2902-49af-88d1-22906884614a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-19T06:51:54.138065Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/0b2a0f80-2902-49af-88d1-22906884614a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "The trivyn corpus is a FLAT record-bag (no links, no supersessions) — so structured (B2) ≈ free-text (B1) by construction; invariant #2 can't be shown on it without first introducing exploitable structure" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/0e93fa86-ad45-4e78-95d9-bcd698afe699> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/0e93fa86-ad45-4e78-95d9-bcd698afe699> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Linked-graph bootstrap skill validated on burrow" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/0e93fa86-ad45-4e78-95d9-bcd698afe699> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/0e93fa86-ad45-4e78-95d9-bcd698afe699> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Pilot of the upgraded bootstrap skill (AD 059b01b7) on burrow — a Go repo never previously bootstrapped, in its own isolated moosedev store. A fresh headless Claude (Sonnet) following ONLY the skill (no hand-holding, no answer hints) produced a genuinely LINKED graph: 42 typed nodes (10 ArchitecturalDecision, 8 SystemComponent, 6 Constraint, 5 Requirement, 4 Alternative, 4 Consequence, 3 AntiPattern, 2 Lesson) and 46 relationship edges across ALL 7 predicates (isMotivatedBy 11, concerns 11, constrains 10, weighs 5, resultsIn 4, violates 3, learnedFrom 2), edge:node ratio 1.10, 0 orphans, 0 SHACL violations. INDEPENDENTLY verified via direct MCP sparql against the store (node/edge/orphan counts), not just the agent's self-report (invariant #6). Significance: (1) the skill GENERALIZES beyond trivyn to a fresh, moderately-documented repo; (2) the decoupled write-path (relate-SHACL AD 73918962) works END-TO-END — concerns->SystemComponent (11) and constrains->SystemComponent (3), the previously-impossible component links, were created and validated in practice; (3) the agent applied the anti-confabulation discipline, explicitly declining to invent weighs/resultsIn edges and decorative SystemComponents without evidence; (4) correctness spot-check: the agent independently rediscovered the three clusters pre-identified as the correctness oracle (read-only boundary, compartmentalization, plain-text inspectability). This realizes the rich-ADR capture model that Lessons 96456e40 / 3f807592 said was unbuilt. Not yet done: a full edge-by-edge correctness audit against source lines. Next: cold/md/RAG/structured comparison on burrow with the model suite (AD 8b48ab85)." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/0e93fa86-ad45-4e78-95d9-bcd698afe699> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/0e93fa86-ad45-4e78-95d9-bcd698afe699> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-19T18:04:50.938722Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/0e93fa86-ad45-4e78-95d9-bcd698afe699> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Linked-graph bootstrap skill validated on a fresh repo (burrow): skill-alone produced 42 nodes / 46 edges / 0 orphans, with working concerns/constrains->SystemComponent links" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/0e93fa86-ad45-4e78-95d9-bcd698afe699> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#learnedFrom> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/059b01b7-8d8b-493c-a3f1-ceb459eb2626> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/0fb76359-04fe-424a-8cb2-86f1880126c3> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/0fb76359-04fe-424a-8cb2-86f1880126c3> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Hybrid dense seed: recall gain, no answer gain" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/0fb76359-04fe-424a-8cb2-86f1880126c3> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/ce49a867-7ebc-41d5-879c-fa59eed3ae65> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/0fb76359-04fe-424a-8cb2-86f1880126c3> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "mcp" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/0fb76359-04fe-424a-8cb2-86f1880126c3> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "First measurement of the hybrid BM25F-dense seed (commit 4974d9a) on the trivyn-temporal at-scale graph (416 records, 37 currency chains). INSTRUMENT A (retrieval slice, deterministic, NO agent — bench/hybrid_seed_recall.py): for OLD-FRAMING queries (a stale-vocabulary user = the comprehension-debt case), hybrid lifts seed recall@3 0.676->0.784 and recall@5 0.784->0.892 (+0.108), MRR 0.516->0.550, with 1 HARD recovery (a reworded current record BM25F misses entirely, hybrid finds at #5) plus 13 rank-lifts (several crossing the top-3 expansion gate). NEUTRAL queries marginal (+0.028 recall@1) with a tiny -0.056 tail regression at k=10 (1/37 chain, RRF reshuffle). The gain is modest because BM25F is already strong on these self-announcing records (da87a7cc, 9e7ebeb6). INSTRUMENT B (end-to-end, codex/gpt-5.4-mini, ORACLE mode, 4 authored vocabulary-drift currency tasks x hybrid(0.5)/BM25F(0.99) x N=6, workdir-isolated + escape-graded — bench/run_hybrid_ab.sh): a TIE — memory-answered bm25f 19/24 vs hybrid 20/24 (Wilson CIs [0.60,0.91] vs [0.64,0.93], fully overlapping); only 1/48 cells escaped. MECHANISM: at oracle k=6 the pushed get_relevant_context already includes a SIBLING current record that covers the answer even under BM25F (e.g. merge_ns: the 'graph-derived prefixes and final-namespace rewrites' record covers the namespace question), so the seed-recall gain does not change answer-ability. This is 9e7ebeb6's 'recovers by construction' at the END-TO-END level. NET CLAIM (scoped to the retrieval slice per 8a06ad1d): the dense seed PROVABLY improves seed recall/rank on vocabulary-drift queries (the mechanism it was built for), but on this corpus at typical retrieval depth the agent already gets a sufficient record from BM25F, so end-to-end currency answering is unchanged. The dense seed's end-to-end value requires a task where NO covering record exists in BM25F's top-k AND the agent cannot fall back to readable code — a narrower condition than this benchmark exercises. Toggle is MOOSEDEV_DENSE_FLOOR (0.5 hybrid / 0.99 pure-BM25F) on the serve. Relates to 9e7ebeb6, 8a06ad1d, da87a7cc, and the hybrid AD b933bd10." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/0fb76359-04fe-424a-8cb2-86f1880126c3> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/0fb76359-04fe-424a-8cb2-86f1880126c3> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-21T09:13:59.718352Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/0fb76359-04fe-424a-8cb2-86f1880126c3> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Hybrid dense seed for get_relevant_context: a real RETRIEVAL-SLICE recall gain (+0.108 recall@3/5 on vocabulary-drift queries) that does NOT translate to an end-to-end answer gain at k=6 (oracle B2 19/24 vs 20/24) — BM25F already surfaces a covering sibling record" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/0fb76359-04fe-424a-8cb2-86f1880126c3> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#learnedFrom> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b933bd10-de56-4481-91dd-397a192a8022> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/10c2f724-788f-4a4f-857c-40458c9139bc> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/10c2f724-788f-4a4f-857c-40458c9139bc> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "One verification pass: subagents don't run the full test suite" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/10c2f724-788f-4a4f-857c-40458c9139bc> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/10c2f724-788f-4a4f-857c-40458c9139bc> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Claim: when orchestrating implementation subagents, do NOT bake \"run the full cargo test suite\" into each subagent's brief — subagents write code (at most `cargo check` their own module); the ORCHESTRATOR runs ONE verification pass at the end (clippy + targeted new tests + behavioral smoke), and the full suite runs once, just before commit.\n\nWhy (user correction, 2026-07-06: \"Why are you running cargo test OVER AND OVER again in subagents?\"): each subagent-run suite is a near-cold heavy build (moose + oxigraph fork + candle), the suite includes slow child-process integration tests, and the result is redundant with the orchestrator's own review pass — N subagents × full suite = N wasted builds for one change. MOOSEDev-specific amplifier: local builds against a discourse-branch moose need a temporary `discourse: None` toggle in state.rs, and每 toggling invalidates state.rs and everything downstream, multiplying rebuild cost — so batch ALL verification behind a single toggle-build-untoggle cycle rather than one per agent.\n\nHow to apply: put \"do NOT run the test suite; the orchestrator verifies\" in every implementation-subagent brief; verify behaviorally once (build → run the new surface → targeted `cargo test <module>` → clippy) and reserve the full suite for the pre-commit gate." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/10c2f724-788f-4a4f-857c-40458c9139bc> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "superseded" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/10c2f724-788f-4a4f-857c-40458c9139bc> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-07-07T03:29:10.388403Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/10c2f724-788f-4a4f-857c-40458c9139bc> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "One verification pass: subagents don't run the full test suite" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/10c2f724-788f-4a4f-857c-40458c9139bc> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#learnedFrom> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/4a86aabc-bd7d-4587-adb2-a051f0386dc5> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/237dd9e8-3a40-4cf9-8c03-695a8b929273> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/237dd9e8-3a40-4cf9-8c03-695a8b929273> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Temporary test needs aren't permanent architecture" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/237dd9e8-3a40-4cf9-8c03-695a8b929273> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "codex-mcp-client" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/237dd9e8-3a40-4cf9-8c03-695a8b929273> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Pattern: a user may ask for a temporary operational setting (for example binding the web UI to 0.0.0.0 for laptop testing) that should not supersede an accepted architecture decision. Rule: distinguish local/dev configuration from product defaults. Preserve conservative defaults such as localhost binding, expose the test need through env/.env configuration (MOOSEDEV_HTTP_ADDR), and record only durable product architecture as ArchitecturalDecision. If unsure whether a request is a permanent direction or a local test override, implement it as configurable rather than changing the default." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/237dd9e8-3a40-4cf9-8c03-695a8b929273> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/237dd9e8-3a40-4cf9-8c03-695a8b929273> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-20T00:50:34.702878Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/237dd9e8-3a40-4cf9-8c03-695a8b929273> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Do not turn temporary developer test needs into permanent architecture decisions" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/243c6c89-eb51-4ff0-95d0-c50f05dc5f12> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/243c6c89-eb51-4ff0-95d0-c50f05dc5f12> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Capability win reproduces on neutral public corpus (codegraph)" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/243c6c89-eb51-4ff0-95d0-c50f05dc5f12> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/243c6c89-eb51-4ff0-95d0-c50f05dc5f12> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Two-corpus validation of the capability finding (extends Lesson 6a70b02e, trivyn). codegraph (public, 53k-star TS code-knowledge-graph tool; doc-bootstrapped to 835 typed records — RICHER than trivyn: Constraint 122, AD 392, Requirement 107, Consequence 61, Lesson 58, AntiPattern 19; edges isMotivatedBy 497, constrains 332, concerns 343, resultsIn 91, learnedFrom 85, violates 31 — the four trivyn never instantiated). Agentic matrix B0/B1-rag/B2, N=2, codex/gpt-5.4-mini, grade_set. RESULT — the categorical win REPRODUCES on a neutral, public, not-our-doc-style corpus: B2 >> B1-rag >> B0 on ALL four classes. Per class: set_completeness B2 0.95 (14/15) vs B1-rag 0.42 vs B0 0; negation B2 0.75 vs B1-rag 0.14 vs B0 0; supersession B2 0.97 (6/6) vs B1-rag 0.79 vs B0 0; multi_hop B2 0.82 vs B1-rag 0.25 vs B0 0. Pooled B2 0.89 vs B1-rag 0.34 vs B0 0. HONEST CAVEATS: (1) pooled B2 0.89 < trivyn 0.94 for TWO non-capability reasons — (a) a FORMAT ARTIFACT: on the 297-item neg_accepted_ads_no_rationale, one of two B2 runs computed the exact 297-absence but WROTE IT TO A FILE instead of inlining (recall 0 by the set-grader), the other inlined all 297 (recall 1.0) — B2 knew the set both times; NOT patching the grader to read agent files (gaming). (b) supersession is LESS discriminating on codegraph (B1-rag 0.79) — only 26 supersedes (vs trivyn 42), small + self-describing, so flat RAG keeps up. (2) set-completeness is the CLEAN robust core on BOTH corpora (B2 1.00/0.95); codegraph's larger sets (122 vs 37) make B1-rag even more hopeless. (3) EFFICIENCY is a WASH (~1.1x pooled tokens): B2 much cheaper on supersession/set-completeness tool-calls but more expensive on the 297-set pagination — the win is ACCURACY, not tokens. The completeness-over-large-sets thesis now holds across a private AND a public corpus — the single biggest external-validity lever for any outward claim." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/243c6c89-eb51-4ff0-95d0-c50f05dc5f12> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/243c6c89-eb51-4ff0-95d0-c50f05dc5f12> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-23T08:41:26.688622Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/243c6c89-eb51-4ff0-95d0-c50f05dc5f12> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Capability win reproduces on neutral public corpus (codegraph)" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2629698e-4c6a-4618-939d-35d98cdd1dd4> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2629698e-4c6a-4618-939d-35d98cdd1dd4> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Label de-saturation grows the hybrid recall@3 edge" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2629698e-4c6a-4618-939d-35d98cdd1dd4> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/ce49a867-7ebc-41d5-879c-fa59eed3ae65> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2629698e-4c6a-4618-939d-35d98cdd1dd4> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "mcp" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2629698e-4c6a-4618-939d-35d98cdd1dd4> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "On the same trivyn-temporal store + queries, swapping the OLD (saturated) binary for the NEW one with MOOSE's label-designator contract active ROUGHLY DOUBLES the hybrid dense seed's retrieval-slice advantage at the gate-critical recall@3. Instrument A (bench/hybrid_seed_recall.py, 37 currency chains, deterministic, no codex), old-framing queries: recall@3 hybrid edge +0.108 -> +0.216 (BM25F-only 0.676->0.622 as content labels forfeit the 2x title boost; hybrid 0.784->0.838 as dense fills the gap); recall@5 edge +0.108 -> +0.081 (BM25F@5 catches up 0.784->0.811); MRR edge ~flat (+0.034 -> +0.033); still 1 hard recovery (61cc71b5) + 18 rank-lifts (was 13). MECHANISM: Core boost-forfeiture stops the self-announcing long labels from dominating the RRF fusion, so the dense channel's ranking surfaces — the dense seed earns MORE of its keep post-contract. SCOPE (per 8a06ad1d): retrieval slice ONLY; N=37 so magnitudes are indicative not precise; end-to-end (Instrument B, codex) untested on the de-saturated binary — prior B was a TIE (0fb76359), and whether the bigger @3 lift moves end-to-end answering is open. Relates to 0fb76359, b933bd10, 9e7ebeb6." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2629698e-4c6a-4618-939d-35d98cdd1dd4> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2629698e-4c6a-4618-939d-35d98cdd1dd4> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-21T19:14:14.25267Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2629698e-4c6a-4618-939d-35d98cdd1dd4> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Label de-saturation grows the hybrid recall@3 edge" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/277ef244-ea4c-452a-aff1-005034d4f525> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/277ef244-ea4c-452a-aff1-005034d4f525> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "growl/snarl slop-rdf duplicate C symbols fail the Linux link (macOS hides it)" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/277ef244-ea4c-452a-aff1-005034d4f525> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/6baa075c-db0d-48e0-800a-0cae86603b2a> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/277ef244-ea4c-452a-aff1-005034d4f525> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "lesson-capture" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/277ef244-ea4c-452a-aff1-005034d4f525> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "growl and snarl-shacl (pulled transitively via moose) each vendor + cc-compile the SAME slop-rdf C runtime, so both define identical #[no_mangle] rdf_* C symbols; neither declares a Cargo `links` key, so Cargo does not dedupe. Symptom: the v0.5.0 Linux build link-failed with ~37 duplicate-symbol errors (rdf_make_iri, rdf_graph_add, ...) under rust-lld, while the macOS arm64 build PASSED -- GNU ld/lld reject duplicate strong symbols, but macOS ld64 tolerates them, which is why a Mac build (and Trivyn on Mac) hid it. Fix applied (mirrors Trivyn's release RUSTFLAGS): (1) align growl to 0.6.1, whose slop-rdf core (slop_rdf.c/.h, slop_common.h, slop_runtime.h) is BYTE-IDENTICAL to snarl-shacl 0.4.1's -- verified by diff -- so the duplicate is a true no-op (growl 0.5.1's slop-rdf DIFFERED, which would have made the flag unsafe: mismatched ABI under one symbol name); (2) pass `-C link-arg=-Wl,--allow-multiple-definition` on the Linux build so the linker accepts the now-identical duplicates. That flag is a BROAD workaround (it silences any future duplicate too). The clean long-term fix, as the slop ecosystem grows, is shared -sys crates -- one for the slop standard library and one for slop-rdf, each declaring `links` -- that growl and snarl-shacl depend on, so the C compiles once and links once. Diagnostic technique (host-independent, works on a Mac): `nm` the compiled .a archives, compare the global-symbol intersection, and `diff` the vendored C sources -- this pinpoints the collision and proves ABI-identity without a Linux machine." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/277ef244-ea4c-452a-aff1-005034d4f525> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/277ef244-ea4c-452a-aff1-005034d4f525> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-07-05T05:32:27.406664Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/277ef244-ea4c-452a-aff1-005034d4f525> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "growl/snarl slop-rdf duplicate C symbols fail the Linux link (macOS hides it)" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/277ef244-ea4c-452a-aff1-005034d4f525> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#learnedFrom> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/ca1e5be2-308b-40ca-a928-dc286a20695b> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/27a62901-03d3-4c44-9463-582677170fac> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/27a62901-03d3-4c44-9463-582677170fac> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "get_relevant_context is B2's reliable workhorse; query NLQ whiffs" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/27a62901-03d3-4c44-9463-582677170fac> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/27a62901-03d3-4c44-9463-582677170fac> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Empirical Phase-2 de-risk observation (qwen3.6-27b via opencode against the moosedev MCP over the 28-record graph): the shallow lexical get_relevant_context returned the right ArchitecturalDecision and grounded a correct, citation-bearing answer, whereas the moosedev query (NLQ walk-planning) tool whiffed on two reasonable phrasings — low confidence, 'triples walked: 0', and once leaking 'Schema query for DefineClass requires a resolved target IRI but none was found' (a variant not caught by the existing schema-leak guard AD 717f60ed). Implications for the benchmark: (1) B2's value will come mostly from get_relevant_context (and sparql for exact reads), so the symmetric B2 AGENTS.md/system-prompt should steer the agent to get_relevant_context for recall and reserve query for genuine multi-hop NL questions; (2) MOOSEDev's internal NLQ token cost (the Phase-1 'tokens:' line, ~1.5k prompt / ~0.2k completion observed) accrues ONLY when query is invoked — get_relevant_context/sparql are no-LLM and free, which actually strengthens B2's H2/H3 cost/speed story; (3) honesty: do not let B2 lean on a finicky tool — measure all three tools as offered and let the data show which carries the load. Reinforces (does not duplicate) Requirement 14a4275c (tool-selection ladder) and Lesson 89dc91bd (walk-planning vs shallow recall by design)." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/27a62901-03d3-4c44-9463-582677170fac> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/27a62901-03d3-4c44-9463-582677170fac> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-18T16:06:17.331548Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/27a62901-03d3-4c44-9463-582677170fac> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "In live benchmarking, get_relevant_context is B2's reliable workhorse; the query (NLQ) tool often whiffs — steer B2's AGENTS.md accordingly" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/29a7fde7-01c1-4ddf-b690-8ae8d1bed1df> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/29a7fde7-01c1-4ddf-b690-8ae8d1bed1df> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Session graph display annotations cross graph boundaries" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/29a7fde7-01c1-4ddf-b690-8ae8d1bed1df> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "codex" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/29a7fde7-01c1-4ddf-b690-8ae8d1bed1df> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Session graph visualization must enrich display annotations from the referenced project and ontology graphs. The MOOSE chat session graph stores per-turn annotations and trace edges in its own named graph, but referenced project records, ontology classes, predicates, stages, sensors, and schema terms usually carry their rdfs:label and core display metadata in other named graphs. A UI response that reads only the session graph will show local-name fallbacks and empty details, and a trace filter that hides only trace instances will leave pipeline ontology support nodes behind. Fix: keep the session graph as the structural source, then add targeted read-only rdfs:label/rdf:type/core-display triples for URI terms already present, and make the UI trace toggle hide both trace instances and MOOSE pipeline support terms without mutating backend graph data." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/29a7fde7-01c1-4ddf-b690-8ae8d1bed1df> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/29a7fde7-01c1-4ddf-b690-8ae8d1bed1df> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-23T23:57:55.39065Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/29a7fde7-01c1-4ddf-b690-8ae8d1bed1df> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Session graph display annotations cross graph boundaries" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/29a7fde7-01c1-4ddf-b690-8ae8d1bed1df> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#learnedFrom> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/f4978d8a-6361-4628-bf7b-6b297de73c48> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2b1513e6-dae0-4e5b-9b90-0c58f4b77194> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2b1513e6-dae0-4e5b-9b90-0c58f4b77194> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Capability benchmarks need decision-dense corpora; code repos don't qualify" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2b1513e6-dae0-4e5b-9b90-0c58f4b77194> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2b1513e6-dae0-4e5b-9b90-0c58f4b77194> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Stage-2 of the capability benchmark aimed to validate the trivyn result on a NEUTRAL, public corpus (oxigraph-trivyn: real upstream Oxigraph, 2143 first-parent commits 2018-2026) to remove the private/own-doc-style confound. OBSTACLE (found via a $0 temporal-bootstrap triage dry-run): oxigraph is code-churn-heavy — 1756/2143 commits would SEND (mostly low-level code, e.g. 'oxttl cst: fix POG separator invariant'), and only 46 carry a decision/pivot cue (replace/migrate/rework/deprecate/drop) in the subject. A full temporal walk is infeasible (15-60h of agent episodes) AND would produce a noisy code-CHANGE graph, not decisions; a targeted pivot-only walk yields ~46-150 records — too few for any single TYPE to reach the >=40-item large-set regime where the capability win is categorical (Lesson df808a17: the win SCALES with set size). LESSON: the capability benchmark needs a DECISION-DENSE, EDGE-RICH corpus (40+ records of a type, with supersedes/isMotivatedBy/constrains edges). That density comes from DELIBERATE decision capture (trivyn: 416 records, 37 constraints, 141 accepted ADs) or a curated decision corpus (rust-rfcs: 634 RFCs, but a FLAT import with no inter-record edges → only set-completeness, no negation/supersession/multi-hop). Neutral + public + decision-dense + edge-rich repos are RARE — most public code repos record incremental code, not decisions. IMPLICATION for a future neutral validation: either bootstrap a decision-bearing artifact (CHANGELOG with Removed/Replaced → supersedes; issue/PR design discussions) rather than raw commits, or accept the private trivyn corpus and strengthen it (chosen: more large-class questions + N=3). A code repo's git history is the WRONG source for a capability corpus. Bug fixed en route: temporal_bootstrap._git decoded git output as strict UTF-8 and crashed on oxigraph's binary test-fixture diffs (now errors='replace')." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2b1513e6-dae0-4e5b-9b90-0c58f4b77194> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2b1513e6-dae0-4e5b-9b90-0c58f4b77194> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-23T01:12:53.899467Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2b1513e6-dae0-4e5b-9b90-0c58f4b77194> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Capability benchmarks need decision-dense corpora; code repos don't qualify" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2d79b2d2-49ce-4a55-8283-57c9ffa3c584> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2d79b2d2-49ce-4a55-8283-57c9ffa3c584> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Temporal bootstrap generalizes to burrow, a 2nd repo" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2d79b2d2-49ce-4a55-8283-57c9ffa3c584> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/ce49a867-7ebc-41d5-879c-fa59eed3ae65> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2d79b2d2-49ce-4a55-8283-57c9ffa3c584> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2d79b2d2-49ce-4a55-8283-57c9ffa3c584> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Re-ran the burrow temporal git-walk bootstrap after fixing the stale-binary bug (Lesson d7e5a23f rebuilt the release binary with the stamping feature). 34 decision-bearing episodes, gpt-5.4-mini via the codex capture backend. RESULT: 64 nodes (51 ArchitecturalDecision, 6 Constraint, 4 Rationale, 3 Requirement), 54 edges (40 isMotivatedBy, 6 constrains, 4 supersedes, 4 hasRationale), edge:node 0.84, validate_against_architecture Conforms 0 violations. FIX CONFIRMED FROM THE STORE (sparql, not the prompt): timeline = burrow's real commit range 2026-02-19..2026-02-25Z (NOT run-time), and the 4 supersede chains are GENUINELY look-back-correct — e.g. 'Phase 1 routine execution registers REST services only' (02-19) -> '...REST and RSS services' (02-21): new strictly later than old across DIFFERENT historical dates, not the run-order coincidence of the broken first run. The 4 reversals are real burrow refinements (zero-key weather.gov quickstart -> multi-source daily brief; REST-only -> REST+RSS; static-report-voice refinement; compact-prompt refinement). SIGNIFICANCE: (1) generalizes the temporal bootstrap from N=1 (moosedev 78/66/7, timeline 06-15..19) to N=2 (burrow 64/54/4, timeline 02-19..25), fulfilling Requirement 98b589fe; (2) confirms gpt-5.4-mini/codex (Lesson c0aa3509) as a reliable + cheap capture agent that actually runs the recall->supersede sequence Haiku could not. HONEST NOTES: burrow's organic feature/bugfix history yields FEWER supersedes (4) than moosedev's deliberately-reversal-rich history (7) — expected, not a defect. LLM capture is non-deterministic: the broken first run happened to be edge-richer (edge:node 1.03, incl. concerns->SystemComponent links) while this corrected run skewed to isMotivatedBy (0.84, no concerns/SystemComponent edges) — a richness variance worth a capture-skill nudge, but the supersede count (4) was STABLE across both runs. NEXT: add burrow currency reversal-pair tasks and run the B0/B1-md/B1-rag/B2 x oracle/tooluse matrix — a 2nd-corpus currency A/B that would test whether the structured-currency GUARANTEE (Rationale 2e88601d) generalizes beyond moosedev. Relates to d1b44d5e (moosedev N=1), c0aa3509 (codex capture model), d7e5a23f (stale-binary fix), 98b589fe (requirement now fulfilled), 2e88601d (currency result this would generalize); tooling bench/tb_report.py." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2d79b2d2-49ce-4a55-8283-57c9ffa3c584> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "proposed" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2d79b2d2-49ce-4a55-8283-57c9ffa3c584> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-20T05:59:31.556258Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2d79b2d2-49ce-4a55-8283-57c9ffa3c584> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Temporal bootstrap GENERALIZES to a 2nd repo (burrow, N=2): gpt-5.4-mini/codex captured 64 nodes / 54 edges / 4 look-back-correct supersede chains on burrow's real 2026-02-19..25 timeline, 0 violations" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2dcca5ff-f9c2-4541-9539-37c98c31c2ae> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2dcca5ff-f9c2-4541-9539-37c98c31c2ae> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Pull gap is real, push closes it" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2dcca5ff-f9c2-4541-9539-37c98c31c2ae> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2dcca5ff-f9c2-4541-9539-37c98c31c2ae> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Refines Lesson 3d319416. STILL TRUE: local models (gemma-26b, A3B, q27b-dense) did not effectively pull/act on memory during coding — all 0.4 at B2-tooluse on cache-gap — while frontier pulled reliably in Codex; and the pull-presentation confound (full ~9-tool surface, passive descriptions, multi-param schema) remains an open, untested variable. WITHDRAWN: the clause \"on execution-heavy tasks pull is moot because of the execution ceiling\" — there is no execution ceiling. REPLACED WITH: the pull gap is real and PUSH closes it — injecting the same record the pull tool would have returned took A3B from 0.4 (B2-tooluse/pull) to 1.0 (B2-oracle/push). So pull-vs-push is a meaningful comparison on coding tasks (not moot), and current evidence favors push for local models. The open pull experiment (recall-only single tool + directive description + single `topic` param) is still worth running to see whether better tool design makes a local model pull reliably." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2dcca5ff-f9c2-4541-9539-37c98c31c2ae> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2dcca5ff-f9c2-4541-9539-37c98c31c2ae> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasRationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/ee150eab-c520-48b2-849e-2621fbecd1b7> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2dcca5ff-f9c2-4541-9539-37c98c31c2ae> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-19T05:24:29.9739Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2dcca5ff-f9c2-4541-9539-37c98c31c2ae> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Pull gap is real (local models don't retrieve/act → 0.4 at B2-tooluse) and PUSH closes it (B2-oracle = 1.0); the \"pull moot via execution ceiling\" clause is withdrawn; pull's presentation-confound is still open" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2dcca5ff-f9c2-4541-9539-37c98c31c2ae> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#supersedes> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/3d319416-e868-4665-aa9f-522715268655> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2e3e9841-098f-4171-9074-35e3c7473ba9> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2e3e9841-098f-4171-9074-35e3c7473ba9> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Canonicalized rendezvous paths require precreated directories" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2e3e9841-098f-4171-9074-35e3c7473ba9> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "codex-mcp-client" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2e3e9841-098f-4171-9074-35e3c7473ba9> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Pattern: `socket_path_for` canonicalizes the data dir when it exists, then applies the Unix-socket length guard. `--serve` created the data dir before deriving the socket, but `--connect` initially did not, so first-run and later-run derivation could diverge for paths near the macOS socket length limit. Rule: if a derived rendezvous path depends on canonicalization and existence, create the directory before deriving it in every mode that participates in the rendezvous." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2e3e9841-098f-4171-9074-35e3c7473ba9> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2e3e9841-098f-4171-9074-35e3c7473ba9> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-18T03:14:33.445069Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2e3e9841-098f-4171-9074-35e3c7473ba9> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Canonicalized rendezvous paths require precreated directories" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2eca59fa-b557-4d2b-8e50-b6b60f70894f> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2eca59fa-b557-4d2b-8e50-b6b60f70894f> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Harness pitfall: agent reads sibling _work source" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2eca59fa-b557-4d2b-8e50-b6b60f70894f> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/ce49a867-7ebc-41d5-879c-fa59eed3ae65> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2eca59fa-b557-4d2b-8e50-b6b60f70894f> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "mcp" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2eca59fa-b557-4d2b-8e50-b6b60f70894f> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "On currency/drift Q&A tasks (no materialized tree, so the workdir holds only AGENTS.md+opencode.json), codex agents with danger-full-access run rg/find over '.' and '..' and, finding a SIBLING workdir's full source tree in the shared BENCH_HOME/_work (materialized by a CONCURRENT bench run replaying the trivyn checkout), READ it to answer — confounding the MEMORY test (the answer comes from code, not the graph) and ballooning agent_prompt ~10x (35-50k clean -> 250k-908k escaped). One agent also broadened to ~/code/moose source. KEY FACT: codex sandbox modes (read-only / workspace-write) confine WRITES, not READS, so they do NOT prevent this read-escape. TWO-PART FIX: (1) ISOLATE the run's agent workdirs via a new BENCH_WORK_ROOT override (bench/config.py) pointed at /tmp, so the agent's `find ..` hits a barren dir and cannot see a concurrent run's checkouts (also de-conflicts the two runs); (2) ESCAPE-AS-MEMORY-MISS grading — a pure-memory cell whose agent tokens exceed a threshold (clean oracle <=50k, escapees >=250k) read external source, so memory at that floor did NOT deliver the answer: count it as a memory MISS. This turns the confound into the actual metric ('answered FROM MEMORY'). After isolation, escape dropped to 1/48 cells. Same class as Lesson a80bbe88 (self-documenting/readable code lets non-memory arms comply): the drift tasks ask about code-discoverable internals, so a resourceful agent that CAN read the source bypasses memory. Always use an isolated WORK_ROOT + escape-aware grading for a pure-memory agentic A/B, and never share _work across concurrent runs." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2eca59fa-b557-4d2b-8e50-b6b60f70894f> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2eca59fa-b557-4d2b-8e50-b6b60f70894f> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-21T09:14:00.792715Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/2eca59fa-b557-4d2b-8e50-b6b60f70894f> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Benchmark harness pitfall: a pure-memory (materialize_tree:false) codex agent runs `find ..` and reads sibling _work source trees — answering from CODE not memory (10x token blowup), worst under a concurrent run sharing _work; fix = isolate WORK_ROOT + score escape as a memory-miss" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/33dfb6e2-1839-44be-a8ab-9cabd9259f1b> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/33dfb6e2-1839-44be-a8ab-9cabd9259f1b> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Stale substrate index masks position-fixture drift; re-index before acceptance" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/33dfb6e2-1839-44be-a8ab-9cabd9259f1b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/CodeEntity/0c042477-d0d6-4a04-8072-e0f7f1c53b36> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/33dfb6e2-1839-44be-a8ab-9cabd9259f1b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "phase7-acceptance" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/33dfb6e2-1839-44be-a8ab-9cabd9259f1b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "The resolver acceptance fixture (tests/fixtures/resolver_sample.json, 40 pinned line:col positions) stayed green through slice-2 phases 1-6 while actually drifted: the saved .moosedev/substrate index predated the phase-1 edits, so old-fixture-vs-old-index still agreed, and the suite only resolved against the CURRENT source after Phase 7 ran a fresh moosedev index - at which point 32/40 positions failed. Rule: any test that pins source positions is only exercised by a fresh index; run moosedev index (and repair the fixture per the test header) whenever sampled files change, and always before calling an acceptance run green. Phase 7 repaired all 32 drifted positions against v2 HEAD; the test passes 40/40 with the fresh index." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/33dfb6e2-1839-44be-a8ab-9cabd9259f1b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/33dfb6e2-1839-44be-a8ab-9cabd9259f1b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-07-09T05:41:22.810168Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/33dfb6e2-1839-44be-a8ab-9cabd9259f1b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Stale substrate index masks position-fixture drift; re-index before acceptance" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/33dfb6e2-1839-44be-a8ab-9cabd9259f1b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#learnedFrom> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d91288c9-5d4a-494f-95b5-5d5a26383b0a> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/34cbb7c9-5e63-46e3-a07e-b7a8b02eaf5d> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/34cbb7c9-5e63-46e3-a07e-b7a8b02eaf5d> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Rewriting a CLI dispatch file silently drops subcommands — retest every surface" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/34cbb7c9-5e63-46e3-a07e-b7a8b02eaf5d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/6baa075c-db0d-48e0-800a-0cae86603b2a> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/34cbb7c9-5e63-46e3-a07e-b7a8b02eaf5d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/34cbb7c9-5e63-46e3-a07e-b7a8b02eaf5d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Claim: after any rewrite of a dispatch surface (main.rs: Mode enum / parse_mode / USAGE / dispatch match), re-test EVERY documented subcommand — not just the one being added — because a wholesale rewrite silently drops existing arms and nothing fails at compile time if the dropped code was self-contained.\n\nEvidence: wiring `moosedev bootstrap --temporal` rewrote main.rs and dropped the entire `moosedev skills` subcommand (Mode::Skills, parse arm, dispatch, USAGE line, skills_mode) while keeping the skills_dir() helper (still referenced by init/temporal, so it compiled clean). Only init and bootstrap were re-tested; v0.6.0 shipped with two guidance strings (\"run `moosedev skills`\") pointing at a nonexistent command, and the commit message even claimed the command was added. Caught by the released-artifact acceptance check; restored in fee552b / v0.6.1.\n\nCheap prevention: (a) smoke every USAGE-listed subcommand after touching parse_mode (a --help-vs-dispatch inventory is one loop); (b) grep the tree for `moosedev <cmd>` references (guidance strings, docs, templates) to catch dangling pointers; (c) treat \"commit message claims X\" as a test obligation for X." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/34cbb7c9-5e63-46e3-a07e-b7a8b02eaf5d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/34cbb7c9-5e63-46e3-a07e-b7a8b02eaf5d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-07-07T03:28:38.17002Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/34cbb7c9-5e63-46e3-a07e-b7a8b02eaf5d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Rewriting a CLI dispatch file silently drops subcommands — retest every surface" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/34cbb7c9-5e63-46e3-a07e-b7a8b02eaf5d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#learnedFrom> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/4a86aabc-bd7d-4587-adb2-a051f0386dc5> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/392855d0-0d99-45d7-8fae-1c652c54d315> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/392855d0-0d99-45d7-8fae-1c652c54d315> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Capability Stage-0: structure wins categorically on completeness+cost (B1 recall≈0, B2 exact)" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/392855d0-0d99-45d7-8fae-1c652c54d315> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/ce49a867-7ebc-41d5-879c-fa59eed3ae65> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/392855d0-0d99-45d7-8fae-1c652c54d315> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/392855d0-0d99-45d7-8fae-1c652c54d315> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Capability benchmark Stage-0 ($0 offline, trivyn-temporal, 11 graph-derived questions; bench/capability_build.py + capability_probe.py). B2 ceiling = each question's exact SPARQL set (1 query, ~hundreds of tokens); B1 ceiling = BM25 set-recall@k over the 246KB/~63K-token text export. RESULT — the FIRST clear structural win after three retrieval nulls (7b41be4f, 8f06f329, and the hybrid-offset Lesson): the win is COMPLETENESS + COST (possible-vs-impossible + efficiency), NOT retrieval precision. For answer sets >=16 (all Constraints 37, Requirements 37, superseded ADs 37, all-superseded 42), NEGATION (accepted ADs with no isMotivatedBy = 104; Constraints with no rationale = 32), and MULTI-HOP, B1 recall@5 ≈ 0.00-0.11 and recall@25 ≈ 0.02-0.35 — top-k BM25 structurally cannot cover a large set, cannot identify an ABSENCE (the typed edge isn't in the B1 text export at all), and cannot traverse. B1 reaches recall 1.0 ONLY at k=all (ingest the entire corpus, ~63K tokens); B2 returns the exact set in ONE query. HONEST SCOPE: small sets (Lessons=2, chain-head=1) TIE — both arms handle 1-2 items; the categorical win is large-set/negation/multi-hop only. This is the TOOL-LEVEL ceiling; the agentic confirmation (can a RAG AGENT reconstruct the set via many queries+reasoning, and at what token/tool-call cost vs one SPARQL) is Stage 1 — but the $0 probe already shows completeness requires ingesting everything, so the EFFICIENCY gap should survive. Ground truth is graph-derived (SPARQL), never hand-authored; edge census verified 76/42/16/47. Routes the MOOSEDev value case toward capability + currency (the two demonstrable structural advantages), away from retrieval precision." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/392855d0-0d99-45d7-8fae-1c652c54d315> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/392855d0-0d99-45d7-8fae-1c652c54d315> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-22T23:52:47.134506Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/392855d0-0d99-45d7-8fae-1c652c54d315> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Capability Stage-0: structure wins categorically on completeness+cost (B1 recall≈0, B2 exact)" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/392855d0-0d99-45d7-8fae-1c652c54d315> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#learnedFrom> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/47f3f038-8fd7-4a96-9c74-15a24bf8be17> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/392855d0-0d99-45d7-8fae-1c652c54d315> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#learnedFrom> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/7b824b26-36bb-47ce-a235-0a4fdf31a662> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/3d319416-e868-4665-aa9f-522715268655> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/3d319416-e868-4665-aa9f-522715268655> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Local models did not pull memory as-tested" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/3d319416-e868-4665-aa9f-522715268655> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/3d319416-e868-4665-aa9f-522715268655> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Refined finding. As-tested, local models (gemma-26b, A3B, 27b-dense) did NOT invoke get_relevant_context during coding across opencode and Codex, while frontier (gpt-5.5) pulled reliably in Codex. BUT \"local-no-pull is a model property\" is NOT yet established, because tool presentation was an uncontrolled confound (many competing tools, passive descriptions, multi-param schema). OPEN EXPERIMENT (the right test of pull for local models): does a recall-only single-tool surface + a directive \"ALWAYS call before editing code or answering a why-question\" description + a single required `topic` param make a local model pull reliably? Must be run on a RECALL/Q&A task within local execution capability (e.g. whynot_tlo_merge), since execution-heavy tasks cannot measure delivery (local models hit an execution ceiling regardless — Lesson 5a0e66fe). Frontier pull-reliability being harness-dependent (Codex > opencode) still stands." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/3d319416-e868-4665-aa9f-522715268655> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "superseded" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/3d319416-e868-4665-aa9f-522715268655> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasRationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/a08fb20f-0e0c-4775-bca6-e5315a479fdf> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/3d319416-e868-4665-aa9f-522715268655> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-19T05:00:32.795405Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/3d319416-e868-4665-aa9f-522715268655> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Local models did not PULL memory as-tested — but tool presentation was an untested confound, and on execution-heavy tasks pull is moot (execution ceiling)" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/3d319416-e868-4665-aa9f-522715268655> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#supersedes> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/094087c7-654d-4af5-a873-68ecff0d30c0> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/3eab326f-a23d-4fba-9d3b-e0a6d1b93253> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/3eab326f-a23d-4fba-9d3b-e0a6d1b93253> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "One verification pass: subagents don't run the full test suite" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/3eab326f-a23d-4fba-9d3b-e0a6d1b93253> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/3eab326f-a23d-4fba-9d3b-e0a6d1b93253> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Claim: when orchestrating implementation subagents, do NOT bake \"run the full cargo test suite\" into each subagent's brief — subagents write code (at most `cargo check` their own module); the ORCHESTRATOR runs ONE verification pass at the end (clippy + targeted new tests + behavioral smoke), and the full suite runs once, just before commit.\n\nWhy (user correction, 2026-07-06: \"Why are you running cargo test OVER AND OVER again in subagents?\"): each subagent-run suite is a near-cold heavy build (moose + oxigraph fork + candle), the suite includes slow child-process integration tests, and the result is redundant with the orchestrator's own review pass — N subagents × full suite = N wasted builds for one change. MOOSEDev-specific amplifier: local builds against a discourse-branch moose need a temporary `discourse: None` toggle in state.rs, and each toggle invalidates state.rs and everything downstream, multiplying rebuild cost — so batch ALL verification behind a single toggle-build-untoggle cycle rather than one per agent.\n\nHow to apply: put \"do NOT run the test suite; the orchestrator verifies\" in every implementation-subagent brief; verify behaviorally once (build → run the new surface → targeted `cargo test <module>` → clippy) and reserve the full suite for the pre-commit gate." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/3eab326f-a23d-4fba-9d3b-e0a6d1b93253> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/3eab326f-a23d-4fba-9d3b-e0a6d1b93253> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasRationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/a621fda7-61ce-4b92-bf08-47a143d558fe> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/3eab326f-a23d-4fba-9d3b-e0a6d1b93253> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-07-07T03:29:49.442449Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/3eab326f-a23d-4fba-9d3b-e0a6d1b93253> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "One verification pass: subagents don't run the full test suite" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/3eab326f-a23d-4fba-9d3b-e0a6d1b93253> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#learnedFrom> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/4a86aabc-bd7d-4587-adb2-a051f0386dc5> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/3eab326f-a23d-4fba-9d3b-e0a6d1b93253> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#supersedes> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/10c2f724-788f-4a4f-857c-40458c9139bc> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/3f807592-035c-4659-8945-7399b1ab471a> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/3f807592-035c-4659-8945-7399b1ab471a> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Ontology models rich ADRs, capture elicits none" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/3f807592-035c-4659-8945-7399b1ab471a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/3f807592-035c-4659-8945-7399b1ab471a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Confirms the capture-tooling gap (Lesson 96456e40) from the ONTOLOGY's documented intent. The software-architecture domain ontology's provenance note states the model explicitly: 'The relationships are the heart — they encode the reasoning chains: a decision concerns system components, is motivated by requirements/constraints, has a rationale, weighs alternatives, results in consequences, and supersedes prior decisions … Rich in relationships, shallow in taxonomy.' It ships multi-hop competency questions (e.g. 'Which requirements motivated a specific architectural decision?', 'What constraints are violated by an anti-pattern?'). BUT: (1) the SHACL shapes (software-architecture_shapes.ttl) put sh:minCount 1 ONLY on metadata datatype props (hasAuthor, hasLifecycleStatus, hasTimestamp; hasComponentName for SystemComponent). Every OBJECT property — hasRationale, isMotivatedBy, weighs, resultsIn, concerns, violates, learnedFrom, supersedes — is type-checked-if-present but NEVER required (no minCount; the ArchitecturalDecisionShape sh:or branches are vacuously satisfied by zero edges). That is why the flat 89-record graph validates with 0 violations. (2) record_important_decision accepts only title/kind/description/status — no rationale, no relationship fields — and its description doesn't encourage them, so the LLM dumps everything into the free-text description blob (why trivyn records are self-contained prose). (3) Only supersede_decision/retract_decision require a rationale and auto-create edges (hasRationale, supersedes). CONCLUSION: relationships were meant to be populated by a RICH ADR CAPTURE (decision + rationale + motivating requirement/constraint + alternatives + consequences + components, minting the sub-nodes/edges as a byproduct, generalizing what supersede does for hasRationale), but that capture was never built. The fix has three parts: (a) enrich record_important_decision (or a record-ADR tool) to elicit + auto-mint the linked components, with a directive description; (b) add sh:severity sh:Warning SHACL shapes so validate nudges 'AD without rationale/isMotivatedBy' toward richness without hard-failing; (c) have the bootstrap emit structured components, not flat blobs. relate() (AD d542b826) is the low-level primitive; this is the capture-time population model on top of it." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/3f807592-035c-4659-8945-7399b1ab471a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "superseded" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/3f807592-035c-4659-8945-7399b1ab471a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-19T15:01:44.047088Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/3f807592-035c-4659-8945-7399b1ab471a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "The ontology was DESIGNED for rich relational ADRs (\"relationships are the heart\"), but SHACL makes every relationship optional and the capture tool elicits none — so the intended rich-ADR population model is unbuilt; edges only ever come from supersede" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4072ad24-7c49-4942-abbb-ca8f1282c36d> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4072ad24-7c49-4942-abbb-ca8f1282c36d> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "relate() range validation uses SHACL shapes, not dcam:rangeIncludes" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4072ad24-7c49-4942-abbb-ca8f1282c36d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "codex-mcp-client" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4072ad24-7c49-4942-abbb-ca8f1282c36d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Correction from the user during planning: dcam:rangeIncludes in the domain ontology is an annotation-style hint and should not drive MOOSEDev write-path validation. For relate(subject, predicate, object), the authoritative object constraint should come from loaded SHACL shapes: target class gives the subject class/domain, sh:property + sh:path + sh:class gives a single object class, and sh:or lists blank nodes with the same sh:path and alternate sh:class values for multi-range relationships such as isMotivatedBy, constrains, and learnedFrom. This keeps write validation aligned with the validator contract rather than ontology annotations." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4072ad24-7c49-4942-abbb-ca8f1282c36d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4072ad24-7c49-4942-abbb-ca8f1282c36d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-19T16:29:20.198578Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4072ad24-7c49-4942-abbb-ca8f1282c36d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "relate() range validation should use SHACL shape declarations, not dcam:rangeIncludes annotations" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/410d6c73-fbaf-4440-8c12-4dc288012049> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/410d6c73-fbaf-4440-8c12-4dc288012049> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Instrument B (regraded): hybrid = -19% tokens + objprop/oracle edge; tooluse is a tie" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/410d6c73-fbaf-4440-8c12-4dc288012049> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/410d6c73-fbaf-4440-8c12-4dc288012049> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Regrade-corrected (free, no agent re-run) after fixing two hybrid_ab_report.py grading bugs: (a) the escape proxy is now gated on materialize_tree — all 9 tasks are materialize_tree=false pure-memory, so escape NEVER legitimately applied and was misfiring on reasoning thrash; (b) the currency verdict is coverage-only (Lesson 9fc21dc0; the stale flag is a hint, not a gate). NET: the regrade OVERTURNED the prior 'drift/tooluse +20pp' headline (75f622d7) — that gap was an artifact over-penalizing BM25F (BM25F tooluse 10/20 -> 18/20 after the fix). CORRECTED RESULT (110 cells, gpt-5.4-mini, trivyn-temporal GROWL-modernized): (1) EFFICIENCY hybrid -19% agent tokens (5.66M->4.58M) — grading-independent, SOLID. (2) ACCURACY near-CEILING for both arms by coverage (most tasks 100/100). Hybrid's one clear accuracy edge is the HARDEST retrieval case, objprop_validate oracle: full coverage 5/5 vs bm25f 2/5 (+60pp on that task; the drifted-vocabulary current record BM25F cannot surface) -> pooled drift/oracle hybrid 20/20 vs bm25f 17/20 (+15pp). (3) drift/tooluse is a near-TIE: hybrid 19/20 vs bm25f 18/20 (+1 cell, merge_ns). Every cell hybrid >= bm25f (never worse). HONEST CONCLUSION: hybrid is weakly-better-or-equal AND ~19% cheaper, with a decisive edge only on the hardest-to-retrieve item (objprop, oracle) — NOT the broad tooluse win first reported. META-LESSON: grading artifacts can MANUFACTURE a false signal (inflated tooluse by suppressing BM25F) while ALSO hiding a real one (hybrid's objprop coverage) — verification-by-regrade caught both. CAVEATS: n=5 drift / 3 currency, single model gpt-5.4-mini, single corpus." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/410d6c73-fbaf-4440-8c12-4dc288012049> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/410d6c73-fbaf-4440-8c12-4dc288012049> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasRationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/a0631a99-8f7a-453d-ba03-60ad78c48d42> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/410d6c73-fbaf-4440-8c12-4dc288012049> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-22T20:50:45.724465Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/410d6c73-fbaf-4440-8c12-4dc288012049> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Instrument B (regraded): hybrid = -19% tokens + objprop/oracle edge; tooluse is a tie" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/410d6c73-fbaf-4440-8c12-4dc288012049> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#learnedFrom> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b933bd10-de56-4481-91dd-397a192a8022> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/410d6c73-fbaf-4440-8c12-4dc288012049> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#supersedes> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/75f622d7-8e77-42e4-b04b-4ecbec731976> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/440abc78-27e3-4528-8845-8252230e7576> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/440abc78-27e3-4528-8845-8252230e7576> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Competitor benchmarks compare whole systems: don't hand a rival MOOSEDev's captured graph" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/440abc78-27e3-4528-8845-8252230e7576> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/440abc78-27e3-4528-8845-8252230e7576> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "When benchmarking MOOSEDev against an EXTERNAL competitor memory tool (e.g. mem0), the competitor MUST ingest the same RAW SOURCE and capture its own way — it must NEVER be fed MOOSEDev's already-captured/curated graph (the \"content-parity-at-store\" shortcut I proposed and the user REJECTED).\n\nRATIONALE (user-driven correction): MOOSEDev's structured CAPTURE — typed extraction + alignment + supersession + validation (invariants #1-#3; active-capture AD 145af7e9) — is itself a core differentiator, not neutral shared plumbing. Feeding the rival the flattened graph hands it exactly the value under test (\"the graph wearing a markdown hat\") and is the SAME error AD b3205dcb caught for the content-parity B1 arms, now applied one layer up to an external tool. The unit of comparison is the WHOLE SYSTEM (capture + representation + retrieval) vs whole system, given identical raw material; a \"capture confound\" is not a confound when capture is part of the product.\n\nGROUND-TRUTH COROLLARY: grade against SOURCE-DERIVED ground truth (independently enumerated from the raw docs), NEVER the B2 graph's own SPARQL sets — grading mem0 against MOOSEDev's extraction output re-introduces the same bias at the grading end and also violates the existing primary-source guardrail (AD 47f3f038: \"grade against primary-source ground truth, never the in-graph record\").\n\nDESIGN (codegraph, public): give mem0 the same raw codegraph design docs that doc_bootstrap.py consumed to build B2; let mem0 run its own extraction into its own store; ask the suite in NL; grade vs source-derived sets. HONEST IMPLICATIONS: (a) set-completeness/negation become possible-vs-impossible (mem0 cannot even represent a typed \"Constraint\" set — the categorical capability axis of Lesson 8a06ad1d B), stated as whole-system; (b) supersession/multi-hop are NL-answerable and source-gradeable — the FAIR, contestable cells where mem0's temporal-reasoning gets a real shot; (c) the real COST is building source-derived ground truth (neutral-LLM enumeration + human spot-check, or MOOSEDev-seeded-but-source-audited with an explicit pass for MOOSEDev's own misses).\n\nThe content-parity-at-store variant survives ONLY as an optional, clearly-subordinate mechanistic control to decompose capture-vs-retrieval AFTER the headline whole-system result — never as the comparison itself. Extends AD b3205dcb to external tools; honors AD 47f3f038's primary-source guardrail; relates to capability axis Lesson 8a06ad1d and the two-corpus codegraph result Lesson 243c6c89." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/440abc78-27e3-4528-8845-8252230e7576> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/440abc78-27e3-4528-8845-8252230e7576> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-23T14:40:37.561455Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/440abc78-27e3-4528-8845-8252230e7576> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Competitor benchmarks compare whole systems: don't hand a rival MOOSEDev's captured graph" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/440abc78-27e3-4528-8845-8252230e7576> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#learnedFrom> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/47f3f038-8fd7-4a96-9c74-15a24bf8be17> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/440abc78-27e3-4528-8845-8252230e7576> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#learnedFrom> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/4bbb2125-2e2d-4a3f-9ab2-0b3ed55a1864> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/440abc78-27e3-4528-8845-8252230e7576> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#learnedFrom> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b3205dcb-2639-46f0-9b06-96414de81502> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/446952eb-1ba3-421d-b2d1-346baf04eae7> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/446952eb-1ba3-421d-b2d1-346baf04eae7> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Stale free-text notes are worse than no memory" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/446952eb-1ba3-421d-b2d1-346baf04eae7> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/446952eb-1ba3-421d-b2d1-346baf04eae7> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "User observation on the open-ended trivyn ecological run (Lesson 6227d977): on sparql_editor, cold B0 (no memory, no tree) scored 1/3 while B1-notes (greps the team's real notes) scored 0/3 — NO notes BEAT STALE notes. Reading the answers shows the mechanism: B0 either ABSTAINED honestly ('I can't determine the SPARQL editor library from this workspace', 2 of 3) or CORRECTLY guessed from prior knowledge ('@triply/yasqe (YASQE)', 1 of 3 — YASQE is the well-known standard SPARQL editor library, so the model's prior is right). B1-notes, by contrast, ALL 3 confidently served STALE 'CodeMirror' and CITED the stale CONVENTIONS.md note (codemirror-lang-sparql) — the stale note OVERRODE both the model's correct YASQE prior AND its tendency to abstain, manufacturing confident, provenance-bearing MISINFORMATION. SIGNIFICANCE: stale free-text memory is not merely unhelpful — it is NEGATIVE value (below the no-memory floor) and the WORST failure mode (confident + cited + wrong). It directly instantiates the MOOSEDev core thesis (CLAUDE.md: combat LLMs that 'optimize for sounding correct rather than being correct'): stale notes make the agent SOUND correct while BEING wrong; only currency-aware structured memory (B2: supersession/lifecycle filter -> 3/3 current) keeps it BEING correct. NUANCE (task-dependent): the B0>B1-notes inversion is clean where the notes are PURELY stale on a topic (sparql_editor); where notes are MIXED old+new (local_embeddings) B1-notes (1/3) >= B0 (0/3). PRECISE CLAIM: stale-on-a-topic free-text notes can be actively HARMFUL, dropping below the no-memory floor, by anchoring + citing the stale answer. This STRENGTHENS the currency value claim from 'structured beats stale free-text' to 'stale free-text is negative-value confident misinformation; currency-aware structured memory is the only arm that stays reliably correct.' Refines Lessons 6227d977 + 046bc2d8; relates to AD b3205dcb and the MOOSEDev open-source philosophy (symbolic/being-correct over sounding-correct)." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/446952eb-1ba3-421d-b2d1-346baf04eae7> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "proposed" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/446952eb-1ba3-421d-b2d1-346baf04eae7> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-20T16:49:09.693845Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/446952eb-1ba3-421d-b2d1-346baf04eae7> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Stale free-text notes are NEGATIVE value — worse than no memory: sparql_editor B0 (no notes) 1/3 > B1-notes (stale notes) 0/3, because the stale note converts honest abstention / correct-prior into CONFIDENT, CITED, WRONG answers (the MOOSEDev thesis, demonstrated)" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/470cd7bb-d196-4f5a-b3d5-84cbd04af217> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/470cd7bb-d196-4f5a-b3d5-84cbd04af217> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "-static-libstdc++ can't rewrite librocksdb-sys's explicit -lstdc++" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/470cd7bb-d196-4f5a-b3d5-84cbd04af217> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/6baa075c-db0d-48e0-800a-0cae86603b2a> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/470cd7bb-d196-4f5a-b3d5-84cbd04af217> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/470cd7bb-d196-4f5a-b3d5-84cbd04af217> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Claim: `-C link-arg=-static-libstdc++` is a silent NO-OP for MOOSEDev's Linux link — librocksdb-sys (via oxigraph→RocksDB) emits an EXPLICIT `cargo:rustc-link-lib=stdc++` (an explicit -lstdc++ on the link line), and -static-libstdc++ only rewrites the g++ driver's IMPLICIT libstdc++, never an explicit -l flag; rustc links via the gcc driver besides. The working fix: stage a directory containing ONLY libstdc++.a (symlink from `g++ -print-file-name=libstdc++.a`) and put it first in the search path via RUSTFLAGS `-L native=<dir>`, so -lstdc++ can only resolve to the static archive. `-static-libgcc` IS honored by the gcc driver (and residual dynamic libgcc_s needs only ancient GCC_* symbols — harmless).\n\nField context: v0.6.1 failed on Rocky/RHEL 9 with \"GLIBCXX_3.4.30 not found\" — ubuntu-22.04/GCC 12 builds demand GLIBCXX_3.4.30; Rocky 9 (GCC 11) tops out at 3.4.29. v0.6.2 shipped the no-op flag (build green, artifact unchanged — see the acceptance-check Lesson); the -L trick landed in d68c40a, verified by objdump on a workflow_dispatch probe artifact (NEEDED libstdc++ gone, ZERO GLIBCXX refs, max GLIBC_2.34 = Rocky 9's exact floor), and shipped in v0.6.3 (field-confirmed on Rocky 9). Resulting support floor: glibc ≥ 2.34 + OpenSSL 3 (Rocky/RHEL 9+, Ubuntu 22.04+, Debian 12+); RHEL 8 / Ubuntu 20.04 would additionally need an older-glibc build host (almalinux-8 container or zigbuild). Iteration technique: workflow_dispatch builds artifacts WITHOUT publishing (publish/tap jobs are tag-gated) — iterate on portability without burning version numbers. Sibling of the slop-rdf duplicate-symbol Lesson 277ef244 (same component, same macOS-hides-Linux-linker-truth theme)." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/470cd7bb-d196-4f5a-b3d5-84cbd04af217> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/470cd7bb-d196-4f5a-b3d5-84cbd04af217> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-07-07T03:29:02.543581Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/470cd7bb-d196-4f5a-b3d5-84cbd04af217> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "-static-libstdc++ can't rewrite librocksdb-sys's explicit -lstdc++" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/470cd7bb-d196-4f5a-b3d5-84cbd04af217> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#learnedFrom> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/ca1e5be2-308b-40ca-a928-dc286a20695b> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4b1b319e-b91d-46f8-bb22-9b911b539bcf> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4b1b319e-b91d-46f8-bb22-9b911b539bcf> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Comment new substrate invariants at the source" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4b1b319e-b91d-46f8-bb22-9b911b539bcf> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/CodeEntity/80e20cc1-8fc3-4d39-8627-a04c933864bd> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4b1b319e-b91d-46f8-bb22-9b911b539bcf> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "codex-mcp-client" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4b1b319e-b91d-46f8-bb22-9b911b539bcf> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Claim: substrate code needs local comments for invariants that are otherwise only recoverable from the v2 spec, review thread, or acceptance tests. Evidence: `src/code/substrate/` had correct behavior but left important contracts implicit: metadata-last completion, UTF-8-only positions, first-wins symbol metadata, defensive occurrence sorting, bounded resolver scan, synthetic crate marker filtering, and strict miss behavior. Rule: when adding substrate/resolver logic, document producer quirks and lookup invariants where they are enforced, while avoiding comments that merely restate syntax." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4b1b319e-b91d-46f8-bb22-9b911b539bcf> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4b1b319e-b91d-46f8-bb22-9b911b539bcf> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-07-07T21:04:16.193984Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4b1b319e-b91d-46f8-bb22-9b911b539bcf> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Comment new substrate invariants at the source" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4b1b319e-b91d-46f8-bb22-9b911b539bcf> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#learnedFrom> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/d13be5bb-55b0-4ecc-a2c2-78f0ede8f502> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4c43c364-f8b0-4f75-9d51-2086c60d890d> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4c43c364-f8b0-4f75-9d51-2086c60d890d> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "trivyn:labelProperty is a mirror hint; rdfs:label stays canonical" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4c43c364-f8b0-4f75-9d51-2086c60d890d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "codex-mcp-client" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4c43c364-f8b0-4f75-9d51-2086c60d890d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Correction from the user while implementing capture label-property support: trivyn:labelProperty should not be treated as replacing rdfs:label or as the primary label in MOOSEDev retrieval. It is a data-alignment hint identifying which class-specific datatype property carries the same human name that should also be written to rdfs:label. Capture should continue to write and search rdfs:label as the canonical label, while mirroring that label into the annotation-selected property such as SystemComponent.hasComponentName when SHACL requires it." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4c43c364-f8b0-4f75-9d51-2086c60d890d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4c43c364-f8b0-4f75-9d51-2086c60d890d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-19T16:38:08.0364Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4c43c364-f8b0-4f75-9d51-2086c60d890d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "trivyn:labelProperty is a typed-property mirror hint; rdfs:label remains the canonical instance label" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4ca1fdf4-8ccc-42cc-88a6-5a77a4574ed9> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4ca1fdf4-8ccc-42cc-88a6-5a77a4574ed9> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "De-saturation lifts hybrid end-to-end oracle answering" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4ca1fdf4-8ccc-42cc-88a6-5a77a4574ed9> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/ce49a867-7ebc-41d5-879c-fa59eed3ae65> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4ca1fdf4-8ccc-42cc-88a6-5a77a4574ed9> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "mcp" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4ca1fdf4-8ccc-42cc-88a6-5a77a4574ed9> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "On the de-saturated binary (MOOSE label-designator contract active), the prior end-to-end TIE (0fb76359) shifts to a DIRECTIONAL hybrid edge in the clean oracle mode. Instrument B (bench/run_hybrid_ab.sh, trivyn-temporal, codex/gpt-5.4-mini, 4 vocabulary-drift tasks x N=6, escape-graded, k=4 oracle push): pooled drift/oracle memory-answered = BM25F 19/24 [0.60,0.91] vs hybrid 22/24 [0.74,0.98] (was 20/24 pre-contract, a tie). The BM25F arm is UNCHANGED at 19/24 — the entire gain is in the hybrid arm (dense surfacing more under de-saturated RRF fusion), concentrated on the two HEADROOM tasks where BM25F's oracle top-4 did not already cover the answer: objprop_validate 33->67%, nlq_deadline 83->100%. This is the A-slice recall@3 gain (2629698e) propagating to answers. CAVEATS: CIs OVERLAP at N=24 (directional, NOT significant); the tooluse/agentic mode is escape-confounded (nlq_deadline tooluse 5/6 hybrid cells escaped >120k tok; pooled tooluse 12/24 vs 14/24, one task regressed) — fetch/escape behavior dominates retrieval quality there. Hybrid was also frequently more token-efficient (align oracle 37k->14k, nlq_deadline tooluse 256k->145k). NET: post-contract the dense seed's retrieval gain DOES move end-to-end currency answering in the clean oracle isolation, on tasks with headroom — refining 0fb76359's 'recall gain, no answer gain' (true at saturation). Next: bump N for significance; de-escape the tooluse arm. Relates to 2629698e, 0fb76359, b933bd10." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4ca1fdf4-8ccc-42cc-88a6-5a77a4574ed9> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "superseded" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4ca1fdf4-8ccc-42cc-88a6-5a77a4574ed9> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-21T20:13:06.310219Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4ca1fdf4-8ccc-42cc-88a6-5a77a4574ed9> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "De-saturation lifts hybrid end-to-end oracle answering" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4d34f8c6-27a5-4ff7-b50b-fc39ea192732> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4d34f8c6-27a5-4ff7-b50b-fc39ea192732> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "MOOSEDev read cost is moderate + query-dependent; the 1.68M was a dead-MCP grep" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4d34f8c6-27a5-4ff7-b50b-fc39ea192732> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4d34f8c6-27a5-4ff7-b50b-fc39ea192732> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "MOOSEDev's read cost is QUERY-MECHANISM-dependent and MODERATE — not the alarming 1.68M once attributed to it. CONFIRMED by a clean re-run with a working MCP (gpt-5.4-mini, codegraph): B2 returns the complete 122-constraint set via sparql/query at ~78-167k tokens (recall 1.0), and answers relevance via get_relevant_context at ~35k tokens (cov 0.82). The buggy 1.68M was the DEAD-MCP grep of the store (broken MOOSEDEV_BIN, Lesson 0a890ea9), NOT 'the agent choosing the wrong query'.\n\nCOROLLARIES: (a) targeted get_relevant_context is comparable to mem0's recall in cost (~35-40k); (b) completeness via SPARQL is moderate (tens-to-low-hundreds of K tokens for a 122-set agentic run) and is a capability mem0 lacks entirely; (c) there is NO 'B2 payoff conditional on agent query competence' downside — gpt-5.4-mini reaches for the right tool reliably once the MCP is alive (relevance get_relevant_context 4/4; set-completeness via sparql). The active/push layer (AD 145af7e9) remains a valid efficiency lever, but is NOT required to avoid a 'thrash' that was actually a harness bug. Supersedes f8f2f87c; relates to 0a890ea9 (the bug), 392855d0 (tool ceiling), 8a06ad1d (capability axis), e80db883 (corrected turf result)." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4d34f8c6-27a5-4ff7-b50b-fc39ea192732> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4d34f8c6-27a5-4ff7-b50b-fc39ea192732> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasRationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/fccd0ced-ab3f-4e87-a5d7-4e02e55d3d73> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4d34f8c6-27a5-4ff7-b50b-fc39ea192732> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-23T19:17:47.866259Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4d34f8c6-27a5-4ff7-b50b-fc39ea192732> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "MOOSEDev read cost is moderate + query-dependent; the 1.68M was a dead-MCP grep" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/4d34f8c6-27a5-4ff7-b50b-fc39ea192732> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#supersedes> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/f8f2f87c-4b2a-436c-abfb-23cf32e08cc3> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/51932e6f-02db-47bd-ad2d-df1a299fa12d> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/51932e6f-02db-47bd-ad2d-df1a299fa12d> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Instrument B: hybrid retrieval converts ranking lift to answers (drift/tooluse +20pp, -19% tokens)" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/51932e6f-02db-47bd-ad2d-df1a299fa12d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/51932e6f-02db-47bd-ad2d-df1a299fa12d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "End-to-end B2 hybrid(0.5) vs BM25F(0.99) on trivyn-temporal (GROWL-modernized graph, MOOSE core full-text-search #42), codex/gpt-5.4-mini, 110 cells, 0 timeouts/errors. RESULT: hybrid wins the vocabulary-DRIFT signal, concentrated in TOOLUSE/pull — pooled drift/tooluse 10/20->14/20 (50%->70%, +20pp); drift/oracle 16/20->17/20 (80%->85%, +5pp, push already near-saturated). Per-task tooluse: align_confidence 60->100, merge_ns 80->100 (tokens 290k->126k), objprop_validate 0->20 (both weak), nlq_deadline 60->60 (no help). EFFICIENCY: hybrid -19% agent tokens overall (5.66M->4.58M) — finds the current record faster, less escape-to-source. MECHANISM: confirms Instrument A seed-recall (hybrid promotes the current record higher: old-framing recall@3 +0.216, 19/37 rank-improved) CONVERTS to answer quality, concentrated where the agent's own query depends on retrieval (pull), minimal in oracle/push. ANTI-CASES: currency regression floor null as predicted (Lesson 6b2d1f55) EXCEPT geospatial hybrid 100->67 (1/3 cell + token blowup 45k->157k, 1 escape — hybrid occasionally surfaces a distracting dense neighbor); objprop_validate weak for BOTH arms (retrievability of that current record worth checking). CAVEATS: n=5 drift / 3 currency (CIs overlap, e.g. tooluse [0.30,0.70] vs [0.48,0.85]), single model gpt-5.4-mini, single corpus — directionally and efficiency positive, NOT conclusive. Extends the hybrid seed-recall A/B (Instrument A); relates to bench-design AD 47f3f038 and currency Rationale 952b72d1." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/51932e6f-02db-47bd-ad2d-df1a299fa12d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "superseded" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/51932e6f-02db-47bd-ad2d-df1a299fa12d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-22T20:08:19.545362Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/51932e6f-02db-47bd-ad2d-df1a299fa12d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Instrument B: hybrid retrieval converts ranking lift to answers (drift/tooluse +20pp, -19% tokens)" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/51932e6f-02db-47bd-ad2d-df1a299fa12d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#learnedFrom> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/b933bd10-de56-4481-91dd-397a192a8022> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/51b09e67-a088-4a50-94df-16f160cf5684> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/51b09e67-a088-4a50-94df-16f160cf5684> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Decouple-code-from-ontology extends to write-path validation and labeling" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/51b09e67-a088-4a50-94df-16f160cf5684> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/51b09e67-a088-4a50-94df-16f160cf5684> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "User correction during planning: relate()'s old require_information_record guard and capture's hardcoded hasTitle were the code being \"too coupled to the ontology\" — they baked ontological assumptions (every linkable node is an InformationRecord; every class is labeled by hasTitle) into Rust instead of deferring to what the ontology declares. This GENERALIZES Constraint 19bb4d8a (resolve IRIs by local name; never hardcode namespaces): the same discipline governs VALIDATION logic — relate() now reads the predicate's SHACL shape contract for valid endpoint kinds (AD 73918962) — and LABELING — capture reads each class's labelProperty annotation, mirroring rdfs:label into e.g. hasComponentName. How to apply: derive write-path constraints/conventions from the loaded ontology/shapes at runtime, never from hardcoded class names or property assumptions; a blunt type guard is a coupling smell. Why: the ontology is the regenerable source of truth — hardcoded assumptions silently reject valid data (the SystemComponent case relate() used to block) or rot on ontology change." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/51b09e67-a088-4a50-94df-16f160cf5684> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/51b09e67-a088-4a50-94df-16f160cf5684> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-19T17:34:33.289587Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/51b09e67-a088-4a50-94df-16f160cf5684> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Decouple-code-from-ontology extends to write-path VALIDATION and LABELING, not just IRI resolution" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/51f65b34-1870-4392-aa65-5a52ea7698f9> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/51f65b34-1870-4392-aa65-5a52ea7698f9> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "4-arm benchmark skeleton validated: B0/B1-md/B1-rag/B2" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/51f65b34-1870-4392-aa65-5a52ea7698f9> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/51f65b34-1870-4392-aa65-5a52ea7698f9> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Follow-on to Lesson 679a69af: the harness now implements the AD 4bbb2125 four-arm design and re-ran clean on MOOSEDev-on-itself (single-hop Q&A, qwen3.6-27b via opencode, tooluse). Results: B0 0.0 (grepped empty tree, no answer; 33.7k tok, 48s); B1-md 1.0 cited (native grep+glob over docs/decisions/*.md; 25.5k tok, 60s); B1-rag 1.0 cited (one recall() call; 18.5k tok, 31s); B2 1.0 cited (one get_relevant_context call; 20.6k tok, 25s). Two takeaways: (1) the pre-registered NULL holds — all three memory arms tie at 1.0 on a single-hop, small-KB question; structure does not beat free-text when one lookup suffices. (2) EARLY MECHANISM SIGNAL (1 datapoint, treat as preliminary): even at score-parity the ACCESS MECHANISM already separates cost/speed — B1-md (agent greps+reads markdown files) was the most expensive memory arm (25.5k tok, 60s) while the targeted memory tools were cheaper/faster (B1-rag 18.5k/31s; B2 20.6k/25s, fastest). This foreshadows H2/H3 at scale: markdown-grep should BALLOON in tokens/time as the doc set grows (must grep/read many files), whereas a precise tool call returns just the needed record — so B2 (and B1-rag) advantage on cost/speed likely appears BEFORE any quality (H1) advantage. Internal NLQ tokens stayed 0 (agent used get_relevant_context, not query). B1-md implementation: render the content-parity export to one md file per record under docs/decisions/ in the throwaway workdir; agent uses opencode's native search. Harness validated end-to-end for all four arms." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/51f65b34-1870-4392-aa65-5a52ea7698f9> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/51f65b34-1870-4392-aa65-5a52ea7698f9> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-18T16:35:56.91288Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/51f65b34-1870-4392-aa65-5a52ea7698f9> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "4-arm benchmark skeleton validated (B0/B1-md/B1-rag/B2); even at the single-hop null, markdown-grep costs more tokens/time than a memory tool" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/56d142f9-8299-4b60-8d41-60b7048f17e5> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/56d142f9-8299-4b60-8d41-60b7048f17e5> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Month-0: B2 retrieval value is gated by capture quality, which is gated by source (commit) quality" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/56d142f9-8299-4b60-8d41-60b7048f17e5> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/56d142f9-8299-4b60-8d41-60b7048f17e5> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Month-0 in-anger baseline (2026-06-24; gpt-5.4-mini agent, local-qat blind judge): trivyn mean gap judge(B2)-judge(B0) = +0.15 (n=10), moose = +0.25 (n=6). Clean run, 0 failures, no dead-MCP (every B2 fired get_relevant_context).\n\nHONEST PER-PROBE PATTERN (3 buckets): (1) B2 wins +1.0 on genuinely NON-LOCAL 'why' decisions where B0 guesses wrong — growl, ontology_persist, arctic_fleet, and clustering (the last ONLY because its captured rationale was maintainer-CORRECTED first, AD 1d36f22e->a31b75d3). (2) Ties at 1.0 on single-hop decisions still embodied in the fresh tree — the longitudinal signal is the gap WIDENING as the tree drifts from the decision over months, NOT the month-0 floor (retrieval-slice caveat, Lesson 8a06ad1d). (3) B2 LOSES on yasqe (-1.0) and editions (-0.5).\n\nKEY FINDING (confirms the maintainer's commit-quality concern, now in data): the temporal-bootstrap capture inherits COMMIT-MESSAGE quality. For commit-SILENT decisions the graph holds no real 'why', so B2 honestly answers 'rationale not recorded' and can LOSE to a cold agent's plausible INFERENCE of the (also-inferred) gold. So B2's value is gated by CAPTURE quality, which is gated by SOURCE quality. Both losing probes (yasqe, editions) are exactly the commit-silent/inferred-gold ones.\n\nMITIGATION: the maintainer enriches thin captures (supersede the thin rationale with the real why, as done for clustering); agent runs are gold-INDEPENDENT so re-judging after a gold/capture fix is free. IMPLICATION: the trial's LIVE-capture phase (recording rationale at decision time, where it is richest) should largely avoid the thin-capture failure mode that retroactive commit archaeology produces. Operationalizes the in-anger trial (AD 07415633 / d3d4d7b1)." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/56d142f9-8299-4b60-8d41-60b7048f17e5> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/56d142f9-8299-4b60-8d41-60b7048f17e5> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-24T16:04:23.917302Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/56d142f9-8299-4b60-8d41-60b7048f17e5> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Month-0: B2 retrieval value is gated by capture quality, which is gated by source (commit) quality" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/56d142f9-8299-4b60-8d41-60b7048f17e5> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#learnedFrom> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/07415633-e7f0-410b-9eec-2a7bf9fcff97> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/59ae4ade-1010-46ef-80cc-63790da204bb> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/59ae4ade-1010-46ef-80cc-63790da204bb> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Build the serve via build-release.sh, not bare cargo" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/59ae4ade-1010-46ef-80cc-63790da204bb> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/19df26dc-076b-4339-bee6-bfdc602c13ff> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/59ae4ade-1010-46ef-80cc-63790da204bb> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/3193c9a7-8f50-4af0-b0b6-f05ebaa23393> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/59ae4ade-1010-46ef-80cc-63790da204bb> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/8d48edbd-7ee2-4a52-9eac-f2a09c858637> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/59ae4ade-1010-46ef-80cc-63790da204bb> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "mcp" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/59ae4ade-1010-46ef-80cc-63790da204bb> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "The MOOSEDev web UI is embedded ONLY under the `embedded-frontend` cargo feature (include_dir!($CARGO_MANIFEST_DIR/ui/dist) in src/api/handlers/static_files.rs). A bare `cargo build --release` (no feature) silently compiles the #[cfg(not(feature=\"embedded-frontend\"))] fallback that serves 'MOOSEDev UI is not embedded in this build' and 404s the whole web UI — with NO build-time error; you only notice the blank/404 UI at runtime. ALWAYS build the serve binary via scripts/build-release.sh, which runs `npm --prefix ui run build` (-> ui/dist) THEN `cargo build --release --features embedded-frontend`. Hit this by rebuilding with bare `cargo build --release` to pick up an unrelated src change (label_shape) and then running the dogfood serve on the UI-less binary: GET / returned the fallback. After scripts/build-release.sh + serve restart, GET / = 200 with the real index.html and /assets/*.js = 200. The footgun is documented in build-release.sh's own header." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/59ae4ade-1010-46ef-80cc-63790da204bb> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/59ae4ade-1010-46ef-80cc-63790da204bb> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-21T21:05:25.124703Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/59ae4ade-1010-46ef-80cc-63790da204bb> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Build the serve via build-release.sh, not bare cargo" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/59ae4ade-1010-46ef-80cc-63790da204bb> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#learnedFrom> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/0dddde16-e3eb-4e5d-89b3-825f813b4361> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/5a0e66fe-e430-4cfb-9399-4b36f44561f0> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/5a0e66fe-e430-4cfb-9399-4b36f44561f0> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Local-model execution ceiling on multi-module tasks" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/5a0e66fe-e430-4cfb-9399-4b36f44561f0> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/5a0e66fe-e430-4cfb-9399-4b36f44561f0> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Definitive cache-gap matrix (task: add an is_inferred field to SchemaTriple AND thread it through the ontology_patterns cache + sqlite/postgres migrations + INSERT/SELECT/reconstruction paths). gpt-5.5 (frontier): cold=1.0 AND oracle=1.0. gemma-26b: cold/push/oracle all 0.4. A3B-35b MoE: push/oracle 0.4. 27b-DENSE + thinking ON + oracle: 0.4 (9.4 min, 28 steps, full reasoning trace). Every local model tested — dense or MoE, reasoning on or off, with the lesson handed to it verbatim in the task prompt (oracle) — adds the struct field but NEVER makes the cross-module cache+migration edits the lesson explicitly spells out (it touches only extraction.rs). So the bottleneck is multi-file EXECUTION/instruction-follow-through capability, NOT knowledge or its delivery; push/pull/oracle cannot unlock it, and a richer system-prompt nudge won't either (oracle already IS optimal prompt placement). This CORRECTS the earlier claim 'A3B oracle=1.0 → push delivers value to weak models': those cache-gap 1.0 runs were FRONTIER (openai provider, confirmed in the saved event logs — e.g. run 884fe011), and NO local model ever cleared cache-gap. Implications: (1) constraint-CODE tasks requiring multi-module execution cannot demonstrate memory's value for local models; (2) memory's demonstrable local-model value must be sought in RECALL/Q&A and simple single-edit correct-choice tasks that are within local execution capability; (3) for complex multi-module execution, a frontier model is required regardless of memory. Adds a third task-failure mode (execution ceiling) to the two in Lesson f2f4cd99 (default-action-already-correct, recoverable-from-code) and reinforces Lesson 72cc1962 (frontier traces code)." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/5a0e66fe-e430-4cfb-9399-4b36f44561f0> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "superseded" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/5a0e66fe-e430-4cfb-9399-4b36f44561f0> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-19T04:59:47.12218Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/5a0e66fe-e430-4cfb-9399-4b36f44561f0> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Local models hit an EXECUTION ceiling on multi-module coding tasks regardless of memory delivery — only frontier threads the cache; the cache-gap \"oracle 1.0\" was a frontier misattribution" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/5a697fc3-64eb-4e47-9952-acd60112d9c4> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/5a697fc3-64eb-4e47-9952-acd60112d9c4> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Recall must gate \"relevant\" behind a match-score floor" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/5a697fc3-64eb-4e47-9952-acd60112d9c4> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/5a697fc3-64eb-4e47-9952-acd60112d9c4> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "get_relevant_context returned unrelated records (Unix sockets, daemon lifecycle, vector-cache) for the topic \"alignment of new concepts to the architecture ontology\", all printed under a \"Relevant recorded knowledge\" header. Root cause: graph::relevant_context calls moose EntityIndexCache::search_classes, which returns IndexMatch{score} sorted descending, but the wrapper discarded the score (.map(|h| (h.iri, h.class_iri))) and applied no floor. So a multi-word topic that overlaps a record on a single incidental token — score scaled by overlap fraction to <=0.4 (entity_index::search Level 3) — was surfaced as \"relevant\". For a correctness-first system this is the cardinal failure: asserting a relevance the symbolic layer cannot back (invariant #6, be correct not plausible). Fix shipped: filter hits below TOPIC_RELEVANCE_FLOOR=0.45 (just above the single-token-overlap ceiling of 0.4; below exact-token 0.75 and >=2/3-coverage 0.8), and return an honest topic-aware empty-state (\"No recorded knowledge relevant to X\") rather than padding to limit. General rule: any tool that claims \"relevant\" must apply a relevance threshold and prefer an honest empty result over high-recall noise. Altitude observation: effort went into T-box concept alignment (the L0/L1/L2 suggest_parent stack) which has fired ~once and did not help, while A-box recall — where agents actually live every call — was lexical-only with no floor. Invest in the A-box." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/5a697fc3-64eb-4e47-9952-acd60112d9c4> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/5a697fc3-64eb-4e47-9952-acd60112d9c4> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-18T03:48:44.848018Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/5a697fc3-64eb-4e47-9952-acd60112d9c4> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Recall must gate \"relevant\" behind a match-score floor" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/5ac2174a-4058-43be-907f-b4d3ad7a1f5e> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/5ac2174a-4058-43be-907f-b4d3ad7a1f5e> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Benchmark harness pitfalls: opencode --pure, LM Studio truncation" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/5ac2174a-4058-43be-907f-b4d3ad7a1f5e> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/5ac2174a-4058-43be-907f-b4d3ad7a1f5e> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Methodology lessons from the value-benchmark runs. (1) opencode --pure disables external PLUGINS but does NOT disable AGENTS.md — verified by binary (opencode reads AGENTS.md CONTENT into the prompt via the project-config path, gated by OPENCODE_DISABLE_PROJECT_CONFIG, not --pure) AND by two agent probes (the agent quoted the memory guidance with zero tool/file calls). So the symmetric B1/B2 \"consult memory\" guidance WAS in-context; the agent ignoring it for code actions is real behavior, not a delivery bug. (2) LM Studio enforces a FIXED per-model generation reserve (~37k tokens for gemma at any context) so EFFECTIVE input budget = loaded_context − reserve; an over-budget prompt is silently middle-truncated (TruncateMiddle keeps the head n_keep≈9k + the tail, drops the middle). It is NOT VRAM (unloading the second model didn't change it) and NOT the \"Limit Response Length\" setting (clearing the 2048 cap didn't change it). Mitigation: raise the loaded context until input budget ≥ the agent's accumulated prompt (gemma at 131072 eliminated it on the read-heavy cache-gap task), and/or set opencode compaction {auto:true, prune:true, reserved:N} so it compacts BEFORE overflow. Corollary: context placed in the HEAD (system prompt) survives TruncateMiddle while mid-conversation tool results get dropped — another argument for push/system-prompt placement over pull. (3) Frontier single-runs are high-variance (gpt-5.5 edited in one run, no-op'd to 0.0 in another; codex-spark similar) → require N trials with mean±CI (pre-registered H10), never single-cell conclusions." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/5ac2174a-4058-43be-907f-b4d3ad7a1f5e> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/5ac2174a-4058-43be-907f-b4d3ad7a1f5e> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-19T02:50:12.714403Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/5ac2174a-4058-43be-907f-b4d3ad7a1f5e> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Benchmark harness pitfalls (opencode/LM Studio): --pure keeps AGENTS.md; LM Studio reserves a fixed per-model generation budget that silently middle-truncates; frontier single-runs need N trials" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/5d4a3fac-c6d9-484d-acfc-2d90afadb71a> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/5d4a3fac-c6d9-484d-acfc-2d90afadb71a> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Tool-level capture-gap fix is built: inline relations + suggester + advisory" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/5d4a3fac-c6d9-484d-acfc-2d90afadb71a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/5d4a3fac-c6d9-484d-acfc-2d90afadb71a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "The diagnosis of 3f807592 STANDS (the ontology models rich relational ADRs; SHACL leaves every object property optional so a flat graph validates clean; the old capture tool elicited no links) — it is now RESOLVED at the tool layer rather than only the skill layer. record_important_decision accepts inline relations; a link-suggester (hybrid retrieval + a SHACL RelationCatalogue for legality, suggest-only) surfaces legal candidate links at capture and via the suggest_links tool; validate_against_architecture reports a non-blocking under-linked advisory driven by the shapes' sh:or branches. Apply mode is suggest-only (the agent asserts via the validated path) to avoid confabulating edges into the trusted graph. Remaining work: declarative sh:severity (MOOSE-core, deferred) and human-confirmed backfill of the existing ~110-record under-linked backlog via suggest_links." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/5d4a3fac-c6d9-484d-acfc-2d90afadb71a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/5d4a3fac-c6d9-484d-acfc-2d90afadb71a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasRationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/f99703a9-9688-4e82-a195-532c7be0eddd> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/5d4a3fac-c6d9-484d-acfc-2d90afadb71a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-22T07:53:53.652684Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/5d4a3fac-c6d9-484d-acfc-2d90afadb71a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Tool-level capture-gap fix is built: inline relations + suggester + advisory" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/5d4a3fac-c6d9-484d-acfc-2d90afadb71a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#learnedFrom> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/8353c51a-795a-414f-b978-4781647a1ffe> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/5d4a3fac-c6d9-484d-acfc-2d90afadb71a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#supersedes> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/3f807592-035c-4659-8945-7399b1ab471a> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/5e998125-3c10-40fc-92e0-140eab752e01> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/5e998125-3c10-40fc-92e0-140eab752e01> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Honor explicit skill requests after implementation" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/5e998125-3c10-40fc-92e0-140eab752e01> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "codex-mcp-client" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/5e998125-3c10-40fc-92e0-140eab752e01> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "When the user explicitly asks to use a named skill after an implementation is already working, treat it as a process correction and run the skill on the recent changes before closing. For code-simplification specifically, read the skill instructions, scope the pass to the changed files, make only behavior-preserving simplifications that improve comprehension, and rerun focused verification. This prevents leaving a valid but heavier implementation unreviewed when the user has requested a simplification pass." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/5e998125-3c10-40fc-92e0-140eab752e01> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/5e998125-3c10-40fc-92e0-140eab752e01> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-24T21:34:31.564677Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/5e998125-3c10-40fc-92e0-140eab752e01> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Honor explicit skill requests after implementation" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6227d977-3eaf-462f-8a6a-18d4a2906f07> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6227d977-3eaf-462f-8a6a-18d4a2906f07> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Ecological re-run: B2 beats stale notes" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6227d977-3eaf-462f-8a6a-18d4a2906f07> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6227d977-3eaf-462f-8a6a-18d4a2906f07> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Re-ran the trivyn ECOLOGICAL currency comparison (B0 / B1-notes=greps the team's real 287KB docs / B2=MOOSEDev graph; tooluse, gpt-5.4-mini, N=3) with OPEN-ENDED prompts (no leaked options, AD b3205dcb fix) + STRICT-currency verdict (coverage AND not-asserted-stale) + READING final_text, over 5 tasks. RESULTS: (1) OPEN-ENDED FIX CONFIRMED: the cold B0 floor is now clean on non-guessable tasks — owl_reasoner B0 0/3 (cannot guess the obscure 'growl'; was a contaminated 3/3 under the leaky binary-choice prompt), local_embeddings 0/3, nlq_filter 0/3, sparql_editor 1/3. EXCEPTION/honest finding: geospatial B0 3/3 — REVEALED as genuinely GUESSABLE (cold B0 gave the full correct 'synthesized geo:wktLiteral POINT(lon lat)' answer; wktLiteral is the standard GeoSPARQL default = the model's prior), so geospatial is an INVALID memory task and is DROPPED (exactly the guessability measurement f2f4cd99 prescribes). (2) CURRENCY (B2 vs the team's REAL notes, 4 valid tasks): sparql_editor B2 3/3 vs B1-notes 0/3 = DECISIVE WIN — B1-notes confidently served STALE 'CodeMirror' explicitly CITING the stale CONVENTIONS.md note (codemirror-lang-sparql), while B2 served current 'YASQE' per the recorded decision (B1-notes coverage 0: 'yasqe' is absent from the notes, so NO marker-fooling — the cleanest case). local_embeddings B2 3/3 vs B1-notes 1/3 = WIN but NOISY: the notes contain BOTH the old Candle path AND some MOOSE mentions, so B1-notes is inconsistent (1/3 current) while B2 is consistent (3/3) — realistic: contradictory notes make free-text unreliable. nlq_filter + owl_reasoner = TIES (the notes happen to be current on LCASE/growl; both arms 3/3). So 2 of 4 valid tasks are decisive/clear B2 currency wins where the notes went stale; 2 ties where the notes were current. When the win occurs the free-text arm is CONFIDENTLY WRONG (cites the stale note). (3) EFFICIENCY: NOISY/MIXED at N=3, NOT the uniform 1.3-2.6x the first run suggested — B2 clearly cheaper on owl (55k vs 144k tok) and nlq (103k vs 177k) but ~equal on sparql (102k vs 95k) and slightly MORE on local_embeddings (135k vs 102k). Codex token counts are high-variance; SOFTEN the efficiency claim to task/variance-dependent, not uniform (the first run's clean 1.3-2.6x was partly favorable variance). NET (the honest, defensible MOOSEDev currency claim vs how teams ACTUALLY keep notes): structured memory's currency advantage is REAL and sometimes DECISIVE, CONDITIONAL on the notes having gone stale (the realistic condition); free-text ties when its notes are current; structured is consistent where free-text (contradictory notes) is noisy; validity is now clean (open-ended prompts; guessable task dropped). Refines/extends 046bc2d8 (first ecological run, whose 1.3-2.6x efficiency is now softened) and AD b3205dcb; relates 9fc21dc0 (strict-currency + reading essential), f2f4cd99 (geospatial guessable)." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6227d977-3eaf-462f-8a6a-18d4a2906f07> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "proposed" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6227d977-3eaf-462f-8a6a-18d4a2906f07> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-20T16:42:53.064253Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6227d977-3eaf-462f-8a6a-18d4a2906f07> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Open-ended ecological re-run (trivyn, 5 tasks): structured B2 DECISIVELY beats real-notes B1-notes on currency where notes went stale — sparql_editor 3/3 vs 0/3 (B1-notes cited the stale CodeMirror note; B2 served YASQE); ties where notes current; efficiency noisy not uniform; geospatial revealed guessable" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/622ae0ff-e8b2-447f-8abc-7513d1626ea8> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/622ae0ff-e8b2-447f-8abc-7513d1626ea8> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Capture follows incentive minus friction; mint-only slots need inline fields" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/622ae0ff-e8b2-447f-8abc-7513d1626ea8> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/622ae0ff-e8b2-447f-8abc-7513d1626ea8> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Pattern: graph capture tracks INCENTIVE minus FRICTION, and the rich-ADR cluster won't fill until the friction is removed at the point of capture. Quantified on the moosedev self-graph (49 live-captured decisions): edges that are AUTO-created (supersedes, hasRationale) or that link REUSABLE HUBS the workflow already mines (isMotivatedBy: 14/49) get captured; edges whose target must be MINTED per-decision and is only SHACL-ADVISED (weighs->Alternative, resultsIn->Consequence) stayed at ZERO (Alternative=0, Consequence=0), while incentivized + frictionless Lessons flooded (97). The prior tool-level capture-gap fix (AD 8353c51a / Lesson 5d4a3fac: inline relations + suggester + advisory) did NOT move them, because suggest_links only proposes links to records that ALREADY EXIST and Alternatives/Consequences never exist; minting one was a 3-call dance small models won't do (pull-gap, Lesson 2dcca5ff). Resolution (AD faba413e): give the mint-only slots first-class FLAT inline fields on record_important_decision that mint + link in one call (schema-as-elicitation, least-confusing for small models). NOT a temporal-bootstrap artifact — this graph is live-captured.\n\nRule: when a typed slot requires MINTING a new node (not linking an existing hub) and is only SHACL-advised, neither a suggester (blind to non-existent nodes) nor a response nudge (needs multi-turn follow-up small models skip) will fill it — add a one-call inline-mint path, or it stays empty. Corollary: measure capture coverage PER-PREDICATE (node census + edge histogram), because an aggregate 'it validates' hides per-slot zeros (0 SHACL violations never requires edges)." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/622ae0ff-e8b2-447f-8abc-7513d1626ea8> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/622ae0ff-e8b2-447f-8abc-7513d1626ea8> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-25T19:16:20.507633Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/622ae0ff-e8b2-447f-8abc-7513d1626ea8> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Capture follows incentive minus friction; mint-only slots need inline fields" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/622ae0ff-e8b2-447f-8abc-7513d1626ea8> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#learnedFrom> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/faba413e-6180-455c-a26a-8c3db9850adc> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6414d529-85a7-4dc1-8d7b-c7060de9154b> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6414d529-85a7-4dc1-8d7b-c7060de9154b> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Normalize source paths before substrate lookup" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6414d529-85a7-4dc1-8d7b-c7060de9154b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/CodeEntity/41fe0fcd-d041-4272-87fa-cad8e8909bbc> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6414d529-85a7-4dc1-8d7b-c7060de9154b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "codex-mcp-client" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6414d529-85a7-4dc1-8d7b-c7060de9154b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Claim: CLI and future URI-fed resolver entry points must normalize source paths to the substrate key format before lookup. Evidence: the resolver index keys are repo-relative forward-slash paths, so passing raw debug CLI arguments made semantically identical paths such as `./src/runtime.rs`, absolute repo paths, or `src\\runtime.rs` miss even when `src/runtime.rs` resolved correctly. Rule: strip a leading `./`, convert absolute paths under the repo root to repo-relative paths, and normalize separators to `/` before calling `Substrate::resolve`; keep user-facing diagnostics on the original argument." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6414d529-85a7-4dc1-8d7b-c7060de9154b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6414d529-85a7-4dc1-8d7b-c7060de9154b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-07-07T16:35:25.000526Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6414d529-85a7-4dc1-8d7b-c7060de9154b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Normalize source paths before substrate lookup" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6414d529-85a7-4dc1-8d7b-c7060de9154b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#learnedFrom> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/77b7f5f7-bab4-4bf6-9ca6-dc047e01112d> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/65160e57-9bfe-449a-b753-b40ad230e1e6> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/65160e57-9bfe-449a-b753-b40ad230e1e6> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Use worklist closure for graph-hide propagation" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/65160e57-9bfe-449a-b753-b40ad230e1e6> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "codex" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/65160e57-9bfe-449a-b753-b40ad230e1e6> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "When UI graph filtering mutates a hidden set based on graph edges, a single pass over edges is order-dependent and can leak nodes that become reachable only after a later mutation. Use an explicit worklist/fixpoint for visibility propagation whenever hiding expands through graph connectivity. This preserves behavior for shallow traces while making deeper future trace shapes deterministic." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/65160e57-9bfe-449a-b753-b40ad230e1e6> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/65160e57-9bfe-449a-b753-b40ad230e1e6> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-24T00:20:26.114675Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/65160e57-9bfe-449a-b753-b40ad230e1e6> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Use worklist closure for graph-hide propagation" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/65160e57-9bfe-449a-b753-b40ad230e1e6> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#learnedFrom> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/f4978d8a-6361-4628-bf7b-6b297de73c48> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6582117b-cc47-4b82-b79c-696309d01dcc> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6582117b-cc47-4b82-b79c-696309d01dcc> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Keep generated-artifact business logic out of API handlers" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6582117b-cc47-4b82-b79c-696309d01dcc> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "codex" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6582117b-cc47-4b82-b79c-696309d01dcc> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "When adding first-class generated artifacts like ADR rendering, keep deterministic generation/rendering logic in a reusable domain/service module and keep REST handlers thin. This prevents HTTP glue from becoming the business-logic owner and preserves reuse across UI, CLI, MCP, and future artifact surfaces." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6582117b-cc47-4b82-b79c-696309d01dcc> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6582117b-cc47-4b82-b79c-696309d01dcc> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-26T02:01:32.166217Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6582117b-cc47-4b82-b79c-696309d01dcc> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Keep generated-artifact business logic out of API handlers" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6582117b-cc47-4b82-b79c-696309d01dcc> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#learnedFrom> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/242ae2b2-1ff5-42d2-8ca8-c33deefc3d08> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/679a69af-05a7-4310-a1de-330a34376535> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/679a69af-05a7-4310-a1de-330a34376535> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Benchmark skeleton: single-hop null, floor B2≫B0" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/679a69af-05a7-4310-a1de-330a34376535> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/ce49a867-7ebc-41d5-879c-fa59eed3ae65> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/679a69af-05a7-4310-a1de-330a34376535> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/679a69af-05a7-4310-a1de-330a34376535> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "First empirical run of the value benchmark (bench/), MOOSEDev-on-itself, single context-recovery Q&A ('why shared backend over Unix socket'), qwen3.6-27b via opencode headless, tooluse mode. Results: B0 (cold) score 0.0 — flailed with grep/glob/read over an empty workdir (33k agent tokens, 62s), produced no answer; B1 (free-text BM25 RAG over the content-parity export) score 1.0 — one recall call, grounded+cited (18k tokens, 47s); B2 (moosedev MCP) score 1.0 — one get_relevant_context call, grounded+cited (20k tokens, 24s, fastest). Interpretation: this is the PRE-REGISTERED NULL — on a small KB with a single-hop question, structured (B2) does NOT beat free-text (B1) because one lookup suffices and everything fits; the harness correctly shows the null (disconfirmability works). B2−B0 is the trivial floor. Token (H2) and speed (H3) directions already appear: both memory arms used ~half B0's agent tokens and B2 was fastest. Internal NLQ tokens were 0 because the agent used get_relevant_context (no-LLM symbolic), not query — consistent with Lesson 27a62901. VALIDATES the harness components: opencode driver + per-arm memory-as-MCP, content-parity B1 corpus, telemetry extraction (agent tokens/steps/tools + internal NLQ tokens via the Phase-1 line + wall-clock), programmatic grading, JSONL output. Caveat/next: the skeleton ran B0 against an EMPTY workdir; the real matrix must give B0 the actual repo working tree so cold has a fair shot from code. The thesis (B2>B1) is expected only on the larger, multi-hop trivyn / rust-rfcs corpora (Phase 3-4). Backend lifecycle per Lesson a7dec1f3 (one explicit --serve, NO_AUTOSPAWN) held up — runs were ~24-62s with no hangs." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/679a69af-05a7-4310-a1de-330a34376535> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/679a69af-05a7-4310-a1de-330a34376535> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-18T16:23:31.580978Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/679a69af-05a7-4310-a1de-330a34376535> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Phase-2 benchmark skeleton works end-to-end and reproduces the predicted single-hop null (B2≈B1) plus the floor (B2≫B0)" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6a70b02e-f013-4a7a-92d5-07fa6ae860d7> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6a70b02e-f013-4a7a-92d5-07fa6ae860d7> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Capability Stage-1 (N=3): categorical win across all four classes" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6a70b02e-f013-4a7a-92d5-07fa6ae860d7> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6a70b02e-f013-4a7a-92d5-07fa6ae860d7> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Tightened (N=3, 15-question suite, n=7-11/cell) agentic capability benchmark on trivyn-temporal (codex/gpt-5.4-mini, B0/B1-rag/B2, grade_set). Categorical accuracy win CONFIRMED across ALL FOUR classes: set_completeness B2 1.00 (10/10) vs B1-rag 0.20 vs B0 0.00; negation B2 0.96 vs B1-rag 0.46 vs B0 0.00; supersession B2 0.95 vs B1-rag 0.59 vs B0 0.09; multi_hop B2 0.82 vs B1-rag 0.00 vs B0 0.00. The 2nd large-class negation (neg_accepted_ads_no_rationale, 109-absence) REPRODUCED the kill-shot (pooled negation B1-rag 0.46). HONEST THRESHOLD NOTE: pooled B2 F1=0.94, a hair under the pre-registered strict 0.95 (verdict reads WEAK/REVIEW). This is ENTIRELY multi_hop (0.82) and is a PRECISION ARTIFACT not a capability gap: B2 multi_hop RECALL=1.00 (always traverses to the right answer); F1 is dinged because the agent's path-EXPLANATION bullets ('- This motivates the decision X', naming the intermediate node) get counted as spurious predicted items (precision 0.5 when bulleted, 1.0 when prose). On the pure COMPLETENESS axis (recall) B2 ~=0.99 vs B1-rag ~=0.37 — the clean categorical gap. Kept F1 as the pre-registered headline and reported 0.94 honestly rather than switching to recall to clear the bar (no metric-shopping). EFFICIENCY (modest, unchanged): B2 ~52-65% of B1-rag tokens, ~3x fewer tool-calls on set/negation/supersession; multi_hop INVERTS (B1 fails fast/cheap). Extends Lesson 392855d0 (Stage-0 tool ceiling) + grading-artifact discipline a03dbe13. Completeness-over-large-sets thesis holds; the strict 0.95 bar was fractionally too tight for the hardest (multi-hop) class given explanatory-bullet precision." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6a70b02e-f013-4a7a-92d5-07fa6ae860d7> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6a70b02e-f013-4a7a-92d5-07fa6ae860d7> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasRationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/ab1777b1-b810-46da-89d4-3a22d05d2563> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6a70b02e-f013-4a7a-92d5-07fa6ae860d7> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-23T02:58:35.484633Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6a70b02e-f013-4a7a-92d5-07fa6ae860d7> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Capability Stage-1 (N=3): categorical win across all four classes" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6a70b02e-f013-4a7a-92d5-07fa6ae860d7> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#supersedes> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/df808a17-3593-4c1b-9f12-5c28051cc931> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6b2d1f55-edea-45a9-aac6-b403a20ec04a> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6b2d1f55-edea-45a9-aac6-b403a20ec04a> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Corrected trivyn currency mining: chains not rank-inverted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6b2d1f55-edea-45a9-aac6-b403a20ec04a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6b2d1f55-edea-45a9-aac6-b403a20ec04a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Setting up the at-scale trivyn currency A/B, my first rank-inversion mining claimed 20/35 chains were rank-inverted (superseded AD outranks current AD in BM25). ANALYSIS ERROR: it scored only the current AD's rank and IGNORED the companion 'Rationale: <title>' record the temporal bootstrap mints for every decision. A no-codex structural pre-flight (printing B1's actual top-6 record titles per task) revealed the current answer is DOUBLE-REPRESENTED — the AD plus its near-duplicate Rationale — and at least one of the two is in B1's top-6 for every task. Corrected mining (current counts as present if the AD OR its Rationale is in top-6): 0 of 35 chains decisive; B1 recovers (serves current) on ALL of them. So trivyn, despite scale (416 records, 42 supersede chains), offers ZERO decisive currency pairs. IMPLICATION: the decisive structured-currency advantage (B1 serves stale, e.g. moosedev glrc) is NOT enabled by corpus scale — it is SUPPRESSED by rich temporal capture: self-announcing current records (they narrate the reversal, carrying both old and new keywords) + the companion Rationale double-represent the current answer, so currency-blind BM25 almost always surfaces it. Cross-corpus tally of decisive free-text currency failures: moosedev 1/4 (glrc), burrow 0/3, trivyn 0/35 -> 1 of ~42 real pairs. CONCLUSION (STRENGTHENS Rationale 952b72d1): structured memory's currency value is the absolute GUARANTEE (B2 current-only); free-text currency fails only under a rare rank-inversion that the bootstrap's own capture richness actively suppresses — so it is NOT a demonstrable average-case advantage, even at scale. DECISION: do NOT run the trivyn currency A/B codex matrix (structural pre-flight predicts ~35 ties — wasted tokens); the trivyn-temporal config + 4 verified tasks + currency-blind B1 export remain as artifacts. PROCESS WIN: the structural pre-flight caught my mining error BEFORE codex spend (verification-first). Relates to 952b72d1 (cross-corpus currency), de96fbac (trivyn bootstrap), 9fc21dc0 (currency grading), 8a06ad1d (anti-degradation-at-scale hypothesis — here capture-richness dominates scale). NEXT: trivyn's scale is better spent on the EFFICIENCY matrix (H2/H3, with a cold B0 arm), where scale should actually move the needle, not currency." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6b2d1f55-edea-45a9-aac6-b403a20ec04a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "proposed" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6b2d1f55-edea-45a9-aac6-b403a20ec04a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-20T14:55:55.6052Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6b2d1f55-edea-45a9-aac6-b403a20ec04a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Corrected trivyn currency mining: 0/35 chains decisive (not the 20 first claimed) — each current decision is DOUBLE-REPRESENTED (AD + companion Rationale) and self-announcing, so BM25 surfaces current in B1's top-6 every time; rank-inversion is suppressed by rich temporal capture, not enabled by scale" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6fe1a3bd-2cd5-44bf-82fe-165b35d37f1c> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6fe1a3bd-2cd5-44bf-82fe-165b35d37f1c> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Acceptance-check the released artifact; a green release run proves nothing" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6fe1a3bd-2cd5-44bf-82fe-165b35d37f1c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/6baa075c-db0d-48e0-800a-0cae86603b2a> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6fe1a3bd-2cd5-44bf-82fe-165b35d37f1c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6fe1a3bd-2cd5-44bf-82fe-165b35d37f1c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Claim: a green release pipeline is NOT evidence the release works — verify the actual published artifact, covering EVERY user-facing surface, and convert each field failure into a CI gate so green comes to MEAN the property holds.\n\nEvidence, twice in one day (v0.6.0→0.6.3): (1) v0.6.0 shipped all-green but the released binary REJECTED `moosedev skills` — a command two shipped guidance strings pointed at; caught only by installing the release and exercising each subcommand. (2) v0.6.2 shipped all-green with a no-op portability fix — objdump on the released tarball showed the binary still NEEDed libstdc++.so.6/GLIBCXX_3.4.30, i.e. the exact field failure (Rocky 9) it claimed to fix. The fix pattern that ended it: (a) a post-release acceptance script that installs the real artifact and smokes every surface (--help inventory, each subcommand, init outputs); (b) run acceptance from a NEUTRAL cwd — a 0.5.2 check run from the repo dir loaded the repo's .env and produced a false negative; (c) encode the field failure as a CI assertion — the \"Verify Linux binary portability\" step objdumps the built binary and FAILS on dynamic libstdc++ or glibc > 2.34, so the next regression is caught pre-publish. Rule: for every release, verify the artifact, not the checkmark; for every field failure, leave a gate behind." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6fe1a3bd-2cd5-44bf-82fe-165b35d37f1c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6fe1a3bd-2cd5-44bf-82fe-165b35d37f1c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-07-07T03:28:29.680429Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6fe1a3bd-2cd5-44bf-82fe-165b35d37f1c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Acceptance-check the released artifact; a green release run proves nothing" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6fe1a3bd-2cd5-44bf-82fe-165b35d37f1c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#learnedFrom> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/4a86aabc-bd7d-4587-adb2-a051f0386dc5> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/6fe1a3bd-2cd5-44bf-82fe-165b35d37f1c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#learnedFrom> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/ca1e5be2-308b-40ca-a928-dc286a20695b> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/72cc1962-fa4e-4109-9d6a-ee7a93ad9665> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/72cc1962-fa4e-4109-9d6a-ee7a93ad9665> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Frontier models recover code-rule knowledge by exploration" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/72cc1962-fa4e-4109-9d6a-ee7a93ad9665> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/72cc1962-fa4e-4109-9d6a-ee7a93ad9665> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Two independent trivyn code tasks, same result: gpt-5.5 COLD (no memory at all) scored 1.0. (a) cache-gap (\"add a field to SchemaTriple\"; the non-obvious requirement is to thread the new field through the ontology_patterns cache + the sqlite/postgres migrations, else it is silently dropped): gpt-5.5 traced the persistence code and threaded the cache. (b) alignment \"landmine\" (\"fix a numeric property over-aligning to a too-specific CCO parent\"; obvious reach = tighten L2 abs_threshold/margin_threshold [the rejected approach]; correct = add a discriminator-based veto entry to CcoFloatingValuePropertyRule in cco_veto_rules.rs): gpt-5.5 explored, found cco_veto_rules.rs, and added the veto discriminator — never touched the threshold. In a well-organized codebase the correct mechanism is always discoverable in the code, so a capable explorer recovers it without memory. Implication: constraint-CODE tasks are memory_or_code and CANNOT demonstrate memory's value for frontier models; memory's code-task value concentrates in the weak/local regime (which can't trace AND won't pull → needs push). Frontier runs are also high-variance (gpt-5.5 edited in one run, no-op'd in another) → need N trials. Refines Lesson a80bbe88: \"non-local\" is not sufficient — the knowledge must be non-recoverable-from-code (and from git history)." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/72cc1962-fa4e-4109-9d6a-ee7a93ad9665> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/72cc1962-fa4e-4109-9d6a-ee7a93ad9665> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-19T02:49:29.2811Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/72cc1962-fa4e-4109-9d6a-ee7a93ad9665> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "On a clean codebase, frontier models recover code-rule knowledge by exploration; constraint-CODE tasks are memory_or_code and can't show memory value at the frontier" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/72e16372-3513-4c8f-a808-ad4c9caa5abe> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/72e16372-3513-4c8f-a808-ad4c9caa5abe> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "moose-branch drift: build MOOSEDev mainline against moose master" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/72e16372-3513-4c8f-a808-ad4c9caa5abe> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/6baa075c-db0d-48e0-800a-0cae86603b2a> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/72e16372-3513-4c8f-a808-ad4c9caa5abe> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "lesson-capture" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/72e16372-3513-4c8f-a808-ad4c9caa5abe> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "MOOSEDev mainline must compile against moose MASTER (what CI clones and releases build against), not whatever branch your local moose is on. Symptom: the v0.5.0 Linux release build failed with E0560 -- state.rs's EngineConfig literal set a `discourse` field that exists only on moose's `discourse` WIP branch, not master. Root cause + why it hid: a GLOBAL ~/.cargo/config.toml `paths = [\".../moose\"]` override forces EVERY local cargo build to use your local moose checkout (whatever branch), so moosedev code silently drifts to the moose branch you're developing and a local build (especially on macOS) never catches the mismatch with master. Rule: keep unreleased-moose-branch fields/APIs OUT of mainline -- put moose-integration work on a moosedev branch paired with the moose branch. To catch drift before a release, build against a master moose checkout (bypassing the global override) or add a CI-parity local check. The failing CI log is authoritative -- it builds against master, so its errors localize exactly what mainline references beyond master." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/72e16372-3513-4c8f-a808-ad4c9caa5abe> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/72e16372-3513-4c8f-a808-ad4c9caa5abe> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-07-05T05:32:26.674997Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/72e16372-3513-4c8f-a808-ad4c9caa5abe> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "moose-branch drift: build MOOSEDev mainline against moose master" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/72e16372-3513-4c8f-a808-ad4c9caa5abe> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#learnedFrom> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/ca1e5be2-308b-40ca-a928-dc286a20695b> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/75f622d7-8e77-42e4-b04b-4ecbec731976> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/75f622d7-8e77-42e4-b04b-4ecbec731976> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Instrument B (corrected): hybrid wins drift; anti-cases were grading artifacts" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/75f622d7-8e77-42e4-b04b-4ecbec731976> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/75f622d7-8e77-42e4-b04b-4ecbec731976> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "CORRECTS the anti-case caveats of the superseded version; the core (+20pp drift/tooluse, -19% tokens) stands and is strengthened. End-to-end B2 hybrid(0.5) vs BM25F(0.99), trivyn-temporal (GROWL-modernized, MOOSE core full-text-search #42), codex/gpt-5.4-mini, 110 cells, 0 timeouts/errors. CORE (unchanged): hybrid wins the vocabulary-DRIFT signal — pooled drift/tooluse 10/20->14/20 (50%->70%, +20pp), drift/oracle 16/20->17/20; EFFICIENCY hybrid -19% agent tokens (5.66M->4.58M, finds the current record faster -> less thrash). ANTI-CASES DIAGNOSED (free transcript inspection) as GRADING ARTIFACTS: (1) objprop_validate — agents answered CORRECTLY+CURRENTLY (coverage 1.0 on most cells) but mem% was suppressed by the stale-marker false-positive (extends 9fc21dc0): matcher trips on backtick-wrapped negation ('no `debug_assert`') AND on 'debug-only' which is IN the current decision's OWN title; the prompt ('across debug and release builds') forces the narration. By COVERAGE hybrid WINS objprop: 5/5 full-coverage oracle vs bm25f 2/5 (tooluse 4/5 tie). (2) geospatial — all 6 cells coverage 1.0 (correct); the lone hybrid 'regression' cell answered in 224 chars / 1 tool call but burned 339k tokens of internal thrash, tripping the tooluse escape proxy (>250k); materialize_tree=False means NO source to escape to, so it is misclassified thrash, not escape -> a TIE. NET: both artifacts dissolve and STRENGTHEN the result (objprop->coverage win, geospatial->tie). TWO HARNESS BUGS (fixable + re-gradeable for free via regrade.py, no codex): (a) the escape proxy must be GATED on materialize_tree (a pure-memory task cannot escape to source); (b) the stale-marker matcher false-positives on backtick-wrapped negations and on stale markers overlapping the cited decision's title (objprop's 'debug-only' marker should be removed/retuned). CAVEATS unchanged: n=5 drift / 3 currency, single model gpt-5.4-mini, single corpus." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
