<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/783928aa-3c48-44d0-a96c-c0085f08f601> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/783928aa-3c48-44d0-a96c-c0085f08f601> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Traversal test: B2 beats flat RAG" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/783928aa-3c48-44d0-a96c-c0085f08f601> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/783928aa-3c48-44d0-a96c-c0085f08f601> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "First end-to-end test of structured traversal on a deliberately-structured chain (seed AD --isMotivatedBy--> deep Requirement; the deep record is lexically gated from the query — BM25 returns the seed but not the deep). Task traversal_ingestion_order (memory-only Q&A: 'why are source rows ingested in deterministic sorted order?'; the WHY — reproducible byte-identical KG for review/audit diffs — lives only in the deep Requirement). Frontier gpt-5.5, N=3. RESULTS (score / reached-deep / tools / steps / tokens / sec): cold 0.16 / 0-3 / 7.0 / 3.7 / 10.4k / 22; md-files (B1-md, flat markdown the agent greps) 1.00 / 3-3 / 3.3 / 4.0 / 12.0k / 16; rag-pull (B1-rag BM25 tooluse) 0.08 / 0-3 / 2.0 / 3.0 / 10.0k / 12; struct-pull (B2 tooluse, get_relevant_context + bounded relational expansion) 1.00 / 3-3 / 1.0 / 2.0 / 12.4k / 8; rag-push (B1-rag oracle, BM25 inject) 0.08 / 0-3 / 0 / 1 / 5.2k / 5; struct-push (B2 oracle, expansion inject) 1.00 / 3-3 / 0 / 1 / 7.2k / 5. THREE FINDINGS: (1) structure/traversal DECISIVELY beats flat RAG (1.00 vs 0.08) — BM25 similarity can't reach the lexically-gated deep record and the agent can't browse the RAG corpus; the 'obvious' RAG MCP is the WORST memory option here, worse than plain md files. (2) HONEST SURPRISE: md-files also scores 1.00 — a FRONTIER agent manually BROWSES the markdown (reads the seed's 'satisfies a recorded downstream requirement', then greps/opens the requirement file). So on ACCURACY structure does NOT beat md-files for frontier; structure's win is EFFICIENCY/THRASHING: struct-push 0 tools/1 step/7.2k tok/5s vs md-files 3.3 tools/4 steps/12k tok/16s — same answer, ~half the tokens, a third of the wall-clock, zero exploration. struct-pull also wins on tools/steps/time (1 vs 3.3 calls, 8s vs 16s) at similar tokens. (3) cold (0.16) and RAG (0.08) never reach the deep content (0/3), confirming it is NOT guessable — md-files/struct genuinely RETRIEVED it. INTERPRETATION ('how much does a well-structured KG help?'): a lot vs RAG; an efficiency win vs the realistic md-files status quo for frontier. The ACCURACY win over md-files is predicted for LOCAL models (won't manually browse/follow references — the no-explore pattern), which is the next test (re-add local). Consistent with the efficiency-not-capability through-line (AD 7b824b26) and validates structured traversal (invariant #2) now that structure EXISTS to exploit (contrast the flat-graph nulls, Lessons 0b2a0f80/aaee7652). Caveat: B1-md here is FLAT markdown (no cross-references); a fair md baseline would render edges as md links — but it already ties on accuracy, so cross-refs would only help its efficiency, not change the accuracy story." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/783928aa-3c48-44d0-a96c-c0085f08f601> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "proposed" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/783928aa-3c48-44d0-a96c-c0085f08f601> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-19T15:17:43.458777Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/783928aa-3c48-44d0-a96c-c0085f08f601> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Traversal test (frontier, N=3): once the KG is structured, B2 traversal reaches the deep answer 3/3 and most efficiently (push: 0 tools/1 step/5s); it DECISIVELY beats flat RAG (0.08, never reaches) but only TIES md-files on accuracy for frontier (which manually browses) — the win vs md-files is efficiency; the accuracy win is expected for local (pending)" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/78a02cc5-ecc9-4241-bfe0-f5fc60bd3db6> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/78a02cc5-ecc9-4241-bfe0-f5fc60bd3db6> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "De-saturation lifts hybrid end-to-end answering" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/78a02cc5-ecc9-4241-bfe0-f5fc60bd3db6> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "mcp" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/78a02cc5-ecc9-4241-bfe0-f5fc60bd3db6> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "End-to-end B2 hybrid(0.5) vs BM25F(0.99), de-saturated binary, codex/gpt-5.4-mini, 4 vocabulary-drift tasks x N=6, trivyn-temporal, MODE-AWARE escape grading (120k oracle / 250k tooluse, hybrid_ab_report.py). Memory-answered (strict currency = coverage==1 AND not stale per 9fc21dc0, AND not escape): ORACLE BM25F 19/24 [0.60,0.91] vs hybrid 22/24 [0.74,0.98]; TOOLUSE BM25F 14/24 [0.39,0.76] vs hybrid 19/24 [0.60,0.91]. BOTH modes show a directional hybrid edge post-contract (a tie pre-contract, 0fb76359) — the A-slice recall@3 gain (2629698e) propagating to answers on the headroom tasks (objprop_validate oracle 33->67, nlq_deadline oracle 83->100). gpt-5.4-mini is a RELIABLE tool caller: 48/48 tooluse cells invoked >=1 tool, 0 timeouts, 43/48 scored 1.0, climbing get_relevant_context->query->sparql. Only 3 GENUINE escapes (nt<=2 + 363-709k tok = dropped to codex shell to read source), ALL under BM25F — weaker retrieval pushes the agent off-memory; hybrid had 0. CAVEAT: N=24, CIs overlap (directional, not significant). Relates to 2629698e, 0fb76359, b933bd10." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/78a02cc5-ecc9-4241-bfe0-f5fc60bd3db6> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/78a02cc5-ecc9-4241-bfe0-f5fc60bd3db6> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasRationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/960885ad-ca1a-40ef-b4a8-a165b277b862> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
