<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/dd5e7d15-54a4-4dee-8f44-6c1198756a9d> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Enrich: record→record edges only, via RDF-1.2 reification" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/dd5e7d15-54a4-4dee-8f44-6c1198756a9d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/11e01ea2-f520-4f7c-a165-09532dacd43f> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/dd5e7d15-54a4-4dee-8f44-6c1198756a9d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/dd5e7d15-54a4-4dee-8f44-6c1198756a9d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Two implementation refinements to AD e0b7b528, both confirmed by the dogfood prototype. (1) ENCODING: the inferred-edge provenance tag is RDF 1.2 reification (R rdf:reifies «s p o» ; prov:wasGeneratedBy <activity>), NOT the RDF-star << s p o >>-as-subject the AD describes. The Trivyn oxigraph fork is RDF 1.2 — Term::Triple is admitted only in OBJECT position (oxrdf triple.rs: Quad/Triple subjects are NamedOrBlankNode), and the codebase test-rejects SPARQL UPDATE (tests/sparql.rs) — so the reifier idiom is the ONLY Transaction-API path. It preserves the AD's per-triple-provenance + drop-and-rerun intent (clear_reasoner_inferences recovers inferred triples from reifiers attributed to the GROWL agent). (2) SCOPING: enrich_delta keeps only record→record OBJECT-PROPERTY edges (subject AND object are asserted A-box nodes of kg/project), NOT the full prp-inv/spo/dom-rng/cax-sco closure the AD names. Feeding the whole ontology T-box makes GROWL also emit CCO/BFO T-box closure, datatype-property liftings (record→literal), and rdf:type completions — 882 raw edges on the dogfood graph vs only 69 record→record. The other ~813 are invisible to record_neighbors (it follows only edges whose OBJECT is an InformationRecord), so they add zero retrieval value while bloating storage/export and shifting SHACL targeting. The 69 kept (the bidirectional-walk win): motivates 6, isRationaleFor 21, isSupersededBy 19, isConstrainedBy 2, BFO part-of 21. Code: src/reasoning/mod.rs (enrich_delta abox-subject + object-is-record filters; enrich/enrich_now), src/provenance/mod.rs (reasoner_inference_quads, clear_reasoner_inferences), trigger in src/graph/mod.rs AppState.ensure_enriched. Verified: 3 unit + 1 integration test, 0 new SHACL violations, idempotent." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/dd5e7d15-54a4-4dee-8f44-6c1198756a9d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/dd5e7d15-54a4-4dee-8f44-6c1198756a9d> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-22T04:40:22.35549Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
