<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/de96fbac-ca2f-4b95-a1be-5536354b2649> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/de96fbac-ca2f-4b95-a1be-5536354b2649> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Temporal bootstrap at scale on trivyn, N=3" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/de96fbac-ca2f-4b95-a1be-5536354b2649> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/de96fbac-ca2f-4b95-a1be-5536354b2649> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Third temporal git-walk bootstrap (after moosedev 78/66/7 Lesson d1b44d5e, and burrow 64/54/4 Lesson 2d79b2d2), now at scale and run overnight. 320 first-parent commits -> 255 decision-bearing episodes (65 mechanical skips), gpt-5.4-mini via the codex backend, resumable. RESULT: 416 nodes (291 ArchitecturalDecision, 47 Rationale, 37 Constraint, 37 Requirement, 2 Lesson, 1 Consequence, 1 SystemComponent); 186 edges (76 isMotivatedBy, 47 hasRationale, 42 supersedes, 16 constrains, 3 concerns, 1 learnedFrom, 1 resultsIn); edge:node 0.45; validate_against_architecture Conforms, 0 violations. TIMELINE (from the store, not the prompt): trivyn's real 2025-07-14 .. 2026-06-18 (~11 months) — correct historical stamping at scale. SUPERSEDE CHAINS: 42, ALL look-back-correct (new.hasTimestamp >= old) across genuinely different historical dates (so look-back correctness is real, not run-order coincidence). Many genuine reversals (OWL reasoning screen added 2025-08 -> retired 2026-05; CodeMirror 6 -> YASQE SPARQL editor; `reasonable` submodule -> `growl` crate; domain hints added 2025-10 -> removed 2026-04 full add-then-remove cycle; free/pro split -> dev/beta/academic editions); ~5-6 are degenerate same-title self-supersedes (capture artifact, as in burrow chain 1) so ~36 genuine. SIGNIFICANCE: (1) temporal bootstrap N=3 generalization at SCALE (~6x burrow/moosedev node count); (2) 42 supersede chains (6x burrow's 4) = rich currency material, far more likely to contain a RANK-INVERTED pair (superseded outranks current in BM25) to demonstrate the structured-currency advantage decisively like moosedev glrc; (3) 416 records + a cold B0 arm + multi-hop tasks should finally surface the efficiency H2/H3 differences burrow was too small for. HONEST CAVEAT: edge:node 0.45 is LOWER than burrow/moosedev (~0.85) — per-episode capture on trivyn's larger diffs skewed to supersedes/isMotivatedBy/hasRationale and produced few concerns/constrains/weighs, so the 291 ADs are loosely linked (fewer multi-hop paths than the node count implies; a capture-skill richness gap worth a nudge). NEXT: (a) efficiency matrix on trivyn-temporal (B0/B1-md/B1-rag/B2 incl. cold + multi-hop); (b) mine the 42 chains for a rank-inverted currency pair. Relates to d1b44d5e, 2d79b2d2, 952b72d1 (cross-corpus currency), c0aa3509 (codex capture); private corpus -> store stays local in ~/.moosedev-stores/trivyn-temporal." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
