<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/de96fbac-ca2f-4b95-a1be-5536354b2649> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Temporal bootstrap at SCALE (trivyn, N=3): gpt-5.4-mini/codex captured 416 nodes / 186 edges / 42 look-back-correct supersede chains over trivyn's real 2025-07..2026-06 timeline, 0 violations" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/df808a17-3593-4c1b-9f12-5c28051cc931> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/df808a17-3593-4c1b-9f12-5c28051cc931> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Capability Stage-1 (agentic): structure wins categorically on large-set completeness; efficiency edge modest" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/df808a17-3593-4c1b-9f12-5c28051cc931> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/ce49a867-7ebc-41d5-879c-fa59eed3ae65> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/df808a17-3593-4c1b-9f12-5c28051cc931> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/df808a17-3593-4c1b-9f12-5c28051cc931> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Capability benchmark Stage-1 — AGENTIC confirmation of the Stage-0 tool-ceiling (Lesson 392855d0). trivyn-temporal, codex/gpt-5.4-mini, B0/B1-rag/B2 × 11 graph-derived capability_qa questions, tooluse, graded by grade_set (set recall/precision/F1). Harness: bench/run_capability.sh, grade_set.py, capability_report.py (regrade-safe). RESULT — ACCURACY VERDICT PASSES (pre-registered): pooled over the hard classes (set/negation/multi-hop) B2 F1=0.96, B1-rag F1=0.31, B0=0.00. Per class: set_completeness B2 1.00 (7/7 pass) vs B1-rag 0.28 vs B0 0; negation B2 0.97 vs B1-rag 0.54 vs B0 0; supersession B2 0.85 vs B1-rag 0.61 vs B0 0; multi_hop B2 0.67 vs B1-rag 0.00 vs B0 0. THE WIN SCALES WITH UNDERLYING SET SIZE, not the question phrasing: large sets (>=~40) are categorical — neg_accepted_ads_no_motivation (104-absence in 141 ADs): B1-rag made 30 tool calls and got 11/104 (recall 0.11), B2 made 7 calls and got 99/104 (0.95); set_all_constraints (37): B1 7/37, B2 37/37. SMALL sets/single-item lookups TIE — neg_constraints_no_rationale (32-absence in a 37-class) B1-rag 0.91 (listing ~all 37 constraints accidentally covers a 32/37 absence), sup_head_of_reversal (single chain head) both ~1.0. So the categorical advantage is COMPLETENESS OVER LARGE SETS (set-completeness, large-negation, multi-hop traversal) — where flat top-k RAG cannot enumerate — not negation or supersession per se. EFFICIENCY VERDICT = REVIEW (modest, NOT the pre-registered <20%): B2 pooled tot_tok 167.9K vs B1-rag 320.6K = 1.9x (B2 ~52% of B1); tool-calls 2.5-4.8x fewer on set/negation; multi_hop INVERTS (B1 fails fast/cheap at 0.3x B2 tokens). The <20% threshold was over-calibrated on the currency precedent; the honest efficiency edge is ~2x tokens + ~3x fewer tool-calls, SECONDARY to the categorical accuracy win. METHODOLOGY: a grader artifact scored exact-correct B1+B2 prose/scalar chain-head answers as 0.0 (n_predicted=0 -> precision 0 -> F1 0); fixed by flooring n_predicted at matched (extends grading-artifact Lesson a03dbe13). CAVEAT: N=1 per question; negation/supersession/multi_hop have only 1-2 questions each (thin per-class Wilson bars) — the set_completeness sweep (7/7 B2, 0/7 B1) is the robust core. Next: oxigraph-trivyn (neutral/public) generalization." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
