<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/df808a17-3593-4c1b-9f12-5c28051cc931> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#learnedFrom> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/47f3f038-8fd7-4a96-9c74-15a24bf8be17> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/df808a17-3593-4c1b-9f12-5c28051cc931> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#learnedFrom> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/ArchitecturalDecision/7b824b26-36bb-47ce-a235-0a4fdf31a662> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/e1e4091c-0a8e-4445-ad6d-521be2644c60> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/e1e4091c-0a8e-4445-ad6d-521be2644c60> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "codex exec hangs on piped stdin" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/e1e4091c-0a8e-4445-ad6d-521be2644c60> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/ce49a867-7ebc-41d5-879c-fa59eed3ae65> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/e1e4091c-0a8e-4445-ad6d-521be2644c60> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "mcp" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/e1e4091c-0a8e-4445-ad6d-521be2644c60> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "codex exec (codex-cli 0.141.0) reads ADDITIONAL instructions from stdin when stdin is a PIPE rather than a TTY, and blocks until EOF (help: 'If stdin is piped and a prompt is also provided, stdin is appended as a <stdin> block'). bench/run.py used subprocess.run(cmd, capture_output=True) with NO stdin=, so the codex child inherited an open pipe under non-interactive launch (agent/cron) and HUNG the full CELL_TIMEOUT (600s) producing 0 tokens, 0 events, no MCP tool call (the raw events.json was 0 bytes). MASKED when the bench scripts are launched via the user's interactive `!` TTY (the scripts even say 'Launch via `!`'); the bug surfaces ONLY under automation. ROOT-CAUSE FIX: stdin=subprocess.DEVNULL on the agent subprocess in run.py (the prompt is always passed as an arg, so the agent never needs stdin). Minimal repro/verification: `codex exec -m gpt-5.4-mini --json 'reply OK' < /dev/null` exits in ~6s with output, vs hanging indefinitely without the redirect. Extends the harness-pitfalls Lesson 5ac2174a (which covered opencode/LM Studio); this is the codex-backend analogue." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/e1e4091c-0a8e-4445-ad6d-521be2644c60> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/e1e4091c-0a8e-4445-ad6d-521be2644c60> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-21T09:14:00.327731Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/e1e4091c-0a8e-4445-ad6d-521be2644c60> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Benchmark harness pitfall: `codex exec` reads piped stdin and blocks on EOF — an unattended/agent launch (no TTY) hangs the full cell timeout with zero output; fix stdin=DEVNULL" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/e80db883-7235-4283-aef2-34eddc4b961c> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Lesson> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/e80db883-7235-4283-aef2-34eddc4b961c> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Phase-2 turf (corrected): B2 ties mem0 on relevance + currency, wins completeness" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/e80db883-7235-4283-aef2-34eddc4b961c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/ce49a867-7ebc-41d5-879c-fa59eed3ae65> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/e80db883-7235-4283-aef2-34eddc4b961c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/e80db883-7235-4283-aef2-34eddc4b961c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "CORRECTED Phase-2 codegraph competitor result (supersedes 8120780a, which was confounded by the dead-MCP bug, Lesson 0a890ea9).\n\nRELEVANCE (mem0's turf) — TIE. With a WORKING MCP, B2 (gpt-5.4-mini) calls get_relevant_context 4/4 at ~35k tokens, cov ~0.82; mem0's recall ~40k tokens, cov 0.67-0.90 — comparable cost AND accuracy. Oracle/push cheaper (~16k). The earlier \"B2 thrashes / mem0 wins relevance\" was ENTIRELY a broken MOOSEDEV_BIN -> dead MCP -> grep fallback (0.5-1.2M tokens), NOT a model/prompt/capability problem (the weak-model and store-grep-instinct hypotheses were both refuted by the fix). CAVEAT: relevance markers are prior-contaminated (cold B0 0.33-0.80), so coverage is noisy; the tool-usage + token parity is the robust tie signal.\n\nCURRENCY (mem0's temporal turf) — TIE. All memory arms 1.00 on the cur_mcp_handshake reversal; cold B0 0.00 (stale).\n\nCOMPLETENESS / NEGATION / SUPERSESSION (B2's turf) — B2 CATEGORICAL, fair + judge-validated: B2 1.00 vs mem0 ~0.15 vs notes ~0.05. UNAFFECTED by the bug (the complete set is recoverable from B2's structured store regardless of query mechanism; mem0's top-k cannot enumerate it by any means).\n\nSYNTHESIS (clean): MOOSEDev TIES mem0 where mem0 is built to win (simple relevance recall + currency) and WINS categorically on completeness/negation/traversal — a SUPERSET on the structural axis, parity on mem0's. The inverse-trades intuition (mem0 cheap-but-incomplete) holds in spirit, but mem0 does NOT beat B2 on relevance; they tie. Relates to Lessons 0a890ea9 (the bug), a6529240 (judge fairness), 243c6c89/8a06ad1d (capability axis). Full matrix: bench/EVALUATION_MEM0.md." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/e80db883-7235-4283-aef2-34eddc4b961c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/e80db883-7235-4283-aef2-34eddc4b961c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasRationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/29297125-b214-4e7d-99ee-beb938c15e98> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Lesson/e80db883-7235-4283-aef2-34eddc4b961c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-23T19:03:27.891068Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
