<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Pattern/a820e93a-131b-41fd-bb53-5bc4607ccb7b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Generated artifact pages use shared UI shell components" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Pattern/c6010de5-9bdd-4e46-90a6-a7f48c6819ce> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Pattern> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Pattern/c6010de5-9bdd-4e46-90a6-a7f48c6819ce> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Deterministic per-RFC bootstrap of the rust-lang/rfcs benchmark corpus" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Pattern/c6010de5-9bdd-4e46-90a6-a7f48c6819ce> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/ce49a867-7ebc-41d5-879c-fa59eed3ae65> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Pattern/c6010de5-9bdd-4e46-90a6-a7f48c6819ce> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Pattern/c6010de5-9bdd-4e46-90a6-a7f48c6819ce> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Phase-3 public thesis corpus is provisioned and frozen. Source: fresh clone of rust-lang/rfcs pinned at SHA 7160a96b584ddd8b80128d90f0cf41b0eaa26a3e, under ~/code/moosedev_benches/rust-rfcs (BENCH_HOME; gitignored, outside the open repo). Method (bench/bootstrap_rust_rfcs.py): deterministic, no-LLM extraction — one merged RFC (text/NNNN-name.md) → one ArchitecturalDecision record; title = \"RFC N: feature\"; description = the RFC's OWN sections (## Summary + Motivation/Problems + Rationale and alternatives/Alternatives + Drawbacks), the why & why-not, captured verbatim, each section capped at 1800 chars. Writes go through ONE persistent MCP session to an explicit `moosedev --serve` backend on the per-corpus data dir (BENCH_HOME/rust-rfcs/.moosedev) with MOOSEDEV_NO_AUTOSPAWN=1 and the shared ontology dir (avoids the backend-lifecycle thrash of Lesson a7dec1f3). Result: 634 records written in 0.3s (record_important_decision is symbolic — no per-record LLM); validate_against_architecture → Conforms, 0 violations; B1 export (corpus/rust-rfcs.json) via sparql = 634 chunks; parity_check.py confirms chunks == graph records and every chunk body == the graph's stored hasDescription (PARITY OK). Capture policy honored: grading ground truth will be the RFC text in the working tree, never these records (no circularity). Limitation: record_important_decision can't yet write object properties, so RFC-to-RFC cross-references live in the description text (not yet typed relations) and supersede chains aren't asserted — see Requirement b2f8240c; multi-hop tasks rely on textual references for now, and H4 supersession will be exercised via explicit supersede_decision calls in task design. Trivyn corpus (private, strong-model synthesis) is the remaining Phase-3 item." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Pattern/c6010de5-9bdd-4e46-90a6-a7f48c6819ce> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Pattern/c6010de5-9bdd-4e46-90a6-a7f48c6819ce> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-18T17:12:46.642762Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Pattern/c6010de5-9bdd-4e46-90a6-a7f48c6819ce> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Deterministic per-RFC bootstrap of the rust-lang/rfcs benchmark corpus (634 records, content parity via sparql)" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Pattern/d7b2801b-6cb4-46ad-88bd-2b5d92e9f373> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Pattern> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Pattern/d7b2801b-6cb4-46ad-88bd-2b5d92e9f373> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "trivyn benchmark corpus bootstrapped via strong-model synthesis" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Pattern/d7b2801b-6cb4-46ad-88bd-2b5d92e9f373> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/ce49a867-7ebc-41d5-879c-fa59eed3ae65> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Pattern/d7b2801b-6cb4-46ad-88bd-2b5d92e9f373> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Pattern/d7b2801b-6cb4-46ad-88bd-2b5d92e9f373> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Phase-3b private thesis corpus is provisioned. Source: pinned clone of trivyn (origin Trivyn/trivyn, PRIVATE) at SHA 1e6e44dff78038d7e3cca6c6439e8f8cacda0d63, under ~/code/moosedev_benches/trivyn — clone, graph, B1 export, tasks, and run transcripts all stay in BENCH_HOME, never the open repo. Method (bench/bootstrap-existing-codebase skill): 6 read-only survey subagents in parallel, each over a subsystem cluster (architecture & MOOSE boundary; ingestion & extraction; ontologies/alignment/SHACL; graph/DB/SPARQL/AI; frontend & conventions; pitfalls & git history), each reading the spec/ files, docs-dev handbook chapters, CONVENTIONS, and git log and returning high-signal typed records (kind/title/description + evidence) under the capture-vs-skip bar. ~100 candidates consolidated/deduped to 89 (records.json), written via bench/bootstrap_trivyn.py through one persistent MCP session to the per-corpus backend (BENCH_HOME/trivyn/.moosedev, NO_AUTOSPAWN). Distribution: 32 ArchitecturalDecision, 20 Constraint, 16 Lesson, 11 Pattern, 9 AntiPattern, 1 Requirement — decision/constraint/anti-pattern dense, suited to constraint-adherence CODE tasks (the real value signal, unlike self-documenting moosedev-on-itself) and why/why-not multi-hop Q&A. validate_against_architecture → 0 violations; B1 export (trivyn.json in BENCH_HOME) = 89 chunks; parity_check → PARITY OK. Grading ground truth for trivyn tasks will be the trivyn docs/code itself, never these records (capture policy). Phase 3 (rust-rfcs + trivyn) now complete; see Pattern c6010de5 (rust-rfcs). Remaining gate before the headline runs: moose search_records (fair B2 retrieval)." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Pattern/d7b2801b-6cb4-46ad-88bd-2b5d92e9f373> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Pattern/d7b2801b-6cb4-46ad-88bd-2b5d92e9f373> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-18T18:27:57.77369Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Pattern/d7b2801b-6cb4-46ad-88bd-2b5d92e9f373> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "trivyn benchmark corpus bootstrapped via strong-model synthesis (89 records, private in BENCH_HOME)" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/2456f9ef-08c6-4f3a-ab94-dd2213df53a6> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Rationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/2456f9ef-08c6-4f3a-ab94-dd2213df53a6> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Rationale: encode the get_relevant_context→query→sparql precision/cost ladder" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/2456f9ef-08c6-4f3a-ab94-dd2213df53a6> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/2456f9ef-08c6-4f3a-ab94-dd2213df53a6> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "The superseded requirement coupled a still-valid goal (reliable tool selection / the precision-cost ladder) to a now-reversed prohibition (\"no A-box vector index; get_relevant_context must not be upgraded to vector search\"). The prohibition is superseded by Constraint af5ebd6d, which permits dense as a bounded seed feeding symbolic expansion; the tool-selection work item remains valid and is carried forward here." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/2456f9ef-08c6-4f3a-ab94-dd2213df53a6> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/2456f9ef-08c6-4f3a-ab94-dd2213df53a6> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-21T07:26:00.337169Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/2456f9ef-08c6-4f3a-ab94-dd2213df53a6> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Rationale: Encode the get_relevant_context → query → sparql precision/cost ladder in tool-selection guidance (A-box dense seed now permitted)" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/262a87b8-8a96-49be-bb11-4fdcbe22fb1a> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Rationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/262a87b8-8a96-49be-bb11-4fdcbe22fb1a> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Rationale: no A-box index, precision via walks" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/262a87b8-8a96-49be-bb11-4fdcbe22fb1a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/262a87b8-8a96-49be-bb11-4fdcbe22fb1a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "The superseded Constraint framed the absence of A-box semantic similarity as a gap with a sanctioned workaround (embed instance text in moosedev via the backbone). That is misleading: not indexing instances is a deliberate MOOSE design choice — walk planning was devised to avoid the vector-index/RAG trap and yield more precise, auditable retrieval. The proposed \"workaround\" is an anti-pattern, not a gap to fill." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/262a87b8-8a96-49be-bb11-4fdcbe22fb1a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/262a87b8-8a96-49be-bb11-4fdcbe22fb1a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-18T04:57:07.675692Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/262a87b8-8a96-49be-bb11-4fdcbe22fb1a> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Rationale: MOOSE deliberately does not index instance (A-box) data; precision comes from walk planning" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/280c1722-9f41-4488-954c-333bec2c56ca> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Rationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/280c1722-9f41-4488-954c-333bec2c56ca> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Rationale: benchmark model suite spans the capability spectrum" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/280c1722-9f41-4488-954c-333bec2c56ca> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/280c1722-9f41-4488-954c-333bec2c56ca> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Extends the opencode-only harness decision: testing the v1 thesis (memory = efficiency at the frontier, capability for weak models) requires spanning model families and capability tiers, which no single harness hosts cleanly. Claude Code headless (claude -p) natively runs and token-accounts Claude models via --output-format json, so opencode is no longer the sole driver. The symmetric memory-as-MCP-server principle is retained." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/280c1722-9f41-4488-954c-333bec2c56ca> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/280c1722-9f41-4488-954c-333bec2c56ca> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-19T18:00:02.317673Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/280c1722-9f41-4488-954c-333bec2c56ca> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Rationale: Benchmark model suite spans the capability spectrum (codex-spark / Sonnet / Haiku / A3B), run per-harness; within-model token-ratio is the efficiency metric" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/29297125-b214-4e7d-99ee-beb938c15e98> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Rationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/29297125-b214-4e7d-99ee-beb938c15e98> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Rationale: Phase-2 turf (corrected): B2 ties mem0 on relevance + currency, wins completeness" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/29297125-b214-4e7d-99ee-beb938c15e98> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/29297125-b214-4e7d-99ee-beb938c15e98> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "The original turf result said \"mem0 wins simple relevance (B2 thrashes)\", but that was confounded by a dead-MCP harness bug (Lesson 0a890ea9): a broken MOOSEDEV_BIN meant get_relevant_context never launched, so B2's agent fell back to grepping the store (0.5-1.2M tokens). After fixing the bin, gpt-5.4-mini calls get_relevant_context 4/4 at ~35k tokens (cov 0.82) — B2 TIES mem0 on relevance, it does not lose. The completeness win is unaffected." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/29297125-b214-4e7d-99ee-beb938c15e98> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/29297125-b214-4e7d-99ee-beb938c15e98> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-23T19:03:27.891068Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/29297125-b214-4e7d-99ee-beb938c15e98> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Rationale: Phase-2 turf (corrected): B2 ties mem0 on relevance + currency, wins completeness" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/2e88601d-30a7-4443-95ce-c8055827178c> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Rationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/2e88601d-30a7-4443-95ce-c8055827178c> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Corrected-grader currency: B2 current, free-text fails at push" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/2e88601d-30a7-4443-95ce-c8055827178c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/ce49a867-7ebc-41d5-879c-fa59eed3ae65> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/2e88601d-30a7-4443-95ce-c8055827178c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/2e88601d-30a7-4443-95ce-c8055827178c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Re-graded all stored currency runs with the negation/markdown-aware grader (no agent re-runs; final_text is logged per row — see Lesson 9fc21dc0 and the reproducible bench/regrade.py). Measuring currency by coverage of the CURRENT markers (robust) instead of the brittle stale-marker substring, the 4-pair result holds on the METRIC, not just hand-read final_text: B2 is 100% current in every cell (25/25 across gpt-5.3-codex-spark, gpt-5.4-mini, gpt-5.5, qwen3.6-a3b and both oracle+tooluse). Free-text (B1-rag) is 100% current on 3 pairs (connect_daemon, ontology, supersede) and collapses only on glrc — the rank-inverted pair where the SUPERSEDED 'pure-symbolic' record outranks the current record in BM25. New mechanistic refinement of abe11031: that collapse is REGIME-DEPENDENT. In ORACLE/push (top-k retrieved chunks injected into the prompt) B1-rag glrc = 1/13 (8%, catastrophic) because the agent is handed the stale top hit and free text has no currency signal to override it; in TOOLUSE (agent runs its own searches) B1-rag glrc recovers to 10/11 (91%) because the agent can dig past the stale top hit. B2 = 100% in BOTH regimes (oracle 13/13, tooluse 12/12). Takeaway: structured current-only retrieval is a GUARANTEE; free-text currency is a content/rank/DELIVERY-regime gamble — worst exactly where push delivery meets BM25 rank-inversion. Refines abe11031; grading basis from Lesson 9fc21dc0; written up in bench/RESULTS.md (human-readable view)." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/2e88601d-30a7-4443-95ce-c8055827178c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "proposed" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/2e88601d-30a7-4443-95ce-c8055827178c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-20T03:53:43.76858Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/2e88601d-30a7-4443-95ce-c8055827178c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Corrected-grader currency result: B2 100% current in EVERY cell (25/25, all models × both regimes); free-text's glrc catastrophe is localized to the oracle/push regime (8%) and recovers under tooluse (91%)" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/51338ce8-1662-4fa3-8401-9c72f8f1339b> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Rationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/51338ce8-1662-4fa3-8401-9c72f8f1339b> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Rationale: clean currency A/B, structured beats free-text" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/51338ce8-1662-4fa3-8401-9c72f8f1339b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/51338ce8-1662-4fa3-8401-9c72f8f1339b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "The earlier currency test was confounded (free-text was made currency-aware via baked-in status, and a no-code framing made agents flail), so it concluded the structured-representation edge \"has not appeared in any test.\" This run removed both confounds exactly as aaee7652 prescribed — currency-blind B1 (--no-status) and memory-only recall — on a graph that actually contains supersession chains (the temporal bootstrap), and the structured edge appeared decisively (push: 0% vs 100% current across all models). The central conclusion of aaee7652 is therefore overturned: the representation edge does appear, conditional on exploitable structure + an un-confounded test." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/51338ce8-1662-4fa3-8401-9c72f8f1339b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/51338ce8-1662-4fa3-8401-9c72f8f1339b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-19T23:35:24.07404Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/51338ce8-1662-4fa3-8401-9c72f8f1339b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Rationale: Clean currency A/B on the temporal graph: structured memory DECISIVELY beats free-text on anti-staleness (push: 0% vs 100% current, ALL models) — overturns the earlier \"structured representation never wins\" (aaee7652)" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/558acbcf-5aae-4bfa-9d91-10e2e68ea367> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Rationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/558acbcf-5aae-4bfa-9d91-10e2e68ea367> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Retract duplicate don't-index-instance-data lesson (walk planning)" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/558acbcf-5aae-4bfa-9d91-10e2e68ea367> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/558acbcf-5aae-4bfa-9d91-10e2e68ea367> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Duplicate of Lesson/89dc91bd (don't index instance data — walk planning), already covered by that Lesson plus two Constraints. Recorded during the M4 bootstrap dry-run without a list-all recall first." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/558acbcf-5aae-4bfa-9d91-10e2e68ea367> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/558acbcf-5aae-4bfa-9d91-10e2e68ea367> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-18T06:08:01.783362Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/558acbcf-5aae-4bfa-9d91-10e2e68ea367> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Rationale: retract Don't index instance data — MOOSE uses walk planning for precise, auditable recall" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/588b3f17-8dfa-4290-990f-28fbc98d2ea2> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Rationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/588b3f17-8dfa-4290-990f-28fbc98d2ea2> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Rationale: in-place status/retract transition" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/588b3f17-8dfa-4290-990f-28fbc98d2ea2> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/588b3f17-8dfa-4290-990f-28fbc98d2ea2> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Half of the prior requirement is now implemented: supersede works on any InformationRecord kind (not just ArchitecturalDecision), type-preserving, in branch feat/supersede-lifecycle (commit cd80831) — verified live by retiring Constraint 0c2106ab and Requirement f1ccd65b. What remains is the OTHER half: there is still no way to transition a record's lifecycle status IN PLACE — e.g. mark a Requirement implemented/accepted, or retract/deprecate it — without replacing it via supersede. Dogfood evidence: this very requirement cannot be marked \"implemented\" without superseding it (which marks it \"superseded\", not \"done\"). Narrowing the requirement to that remaining gap." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/588b3f17-8dfa-4290-990f-28fbc98d2ea2> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/588b3f17-8dfa-4290-990f-28fbc98d2ea2> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-18T05:18:28.243587Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/588b3f17-8dfa-4290-990f-28fbc98d2ea2> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Rationale: Add an in-place status/retract transition for knowledge records" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/5e8e2a69-a7af-41df-a8bf-23ead1ecb62f> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Rationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/5e8e2a69-a7af-41df-a8bf-23ead1ecb62f> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Rationale: A-box dense only as a bounded seed" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/5e8e2a69-a7af-41df-a8bf-23ead1ecb62f> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/5e8e2a69-a7af-41df-a8bf-23ead1ecb62f> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "71637748 banned A-box vector indexing as a \"vector-index/RAG trap.\" The new design addresses that concern rather than ignoring it: dense is a bounded SEED that feeds symbolic walk planning (not a replacement), gated by a confidence floor that preserves honest-empty-state, with symbolic-first anchoring keeping the symbolic layer primary; and a durable+incremental index removes the startup-cost objection (warm restart re-embeds nothing). The capability now exists in MOOSE core by deliberate direction change (instance vector store + search_records_hybrid), so an outright ban no longer reflects the architecture. This narrows — not abandons — the original intent: walk planning stays the precision engine." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/5e8e2a69-a7af-41df-a8bf-23ead1ecb62f> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/5e8e2a69-a7af-41df-a8bf-23ead1ecb62f> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-21T07:23:17.439642Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/5e8e2a69-a7af-41df-a8bf-23ead1ecb62f> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Rationale: Instance (A-box) dense retrieval is permitted only as a bounded SEED for get_relevant_context; walk planning remains the precision engine" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/7a911f2e-d44b-4ec3-92b6-6ee696119fac> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Rationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/7a911f2e-d44b-4ec3-92b6-6ee696119fac> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Rationale: push delivery value unproven for local models" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/7a911f2e-d44b-4ec3-92b6-6ee696119fac> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/7a911f2e-d44b-4ec3-92b6-6ee696119fac> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "The original push AD justified itself with \"oracle (harness-injected context) scored 1.0 where pull scored 0.4 on the same weakest model.\" That is FALSE: the cache-gap 1.0 runs were FRONTIER (gpt-5.5, openai provider, confirmed in saved event logs), not a local model. No local model (gemma-26b, A3B-35b MoE, 27b-dense+thinking) clears cache-gap at any delivery — all 0.4 (see Lesson 5a0e66fe, the execution ceiling). So the cited evidence that push delivers value to weak models was a misattribution and must be withdrawn." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/7a911f2e-d44b-4ec3-92b6-6ee696119fac> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/7a911f2e-d44b-4ec3-92b6-6ee696119fac> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-19T05:00:12.319849Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/7a911f2e-d44b-4ec3-92b6-6ee696119fac> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Rationale: Push delivery (opencode plugin) is built and MECHANICALLY validated; its VALUE for local models is unproven — execution ceiling on code tasks, pending on recall tasks" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/7bc926b9-a904-4534-b298-438a704e7e57> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Rationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/7bc926b9-a904-4534-b298-438a704e7e57> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Rationale: A-box dense as a bounded seed" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/7bc926b9-a904-4534-b298-438a704e7e57> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/7bc926b9-a904-4534-b298-438a704e7e57> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "The original lesson recorded a blanket \"don't index instance data / never vector-search get_relevant_context\" rule. That rule is narrowed by a deliberate direction change: MOOSE core now ships a coherent instance vector store with a matched embedding pair and a confidence floor, and Constraint af5ebd6d sanctions dense as a bounded seed. The lesson's enduring kernel — don't let dense replace auditable walk-planning precision — is preserved; the over-broad prohibition is corrected." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/7bc926b9-a904-4534-b298-438a704e7e57> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/7bc926b9-a904-4534-b298-438a704e7e57> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-21T07:26:07.134711Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/7bc926b9-a904-4534-b298-438a704e7e57> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Rationale: A-box dense retrieval is fine as a bounded SEED — the trap is dense REPLACING walk planning, not dense seeding it" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/8423e995-ce75-41c8-889c-2fb550708ea2> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Rationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/8423e995-ce75-41c8-889c-2fb550708ea2> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Retract duplicate shared-backend decision" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/8423e995-ce75-41c8-889c-2fb550708ea2> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/8423e995-ce75-41c8-889c-2fb550708ea2> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Duplicate of ArchitecturalDecision/0d81e237 (the canonical, more detailed M5 shared-backend decision). Recorded during the M4 bootstrap dry-run without a list-all recall first." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/8423e995-ce75-41c8-889c-2fb550708ea2> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/8423e995-ce75-41c8-889c-2fb550708ea2> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-18T06:08:01.782556Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/8423e995-ce75-41c8-889c-2fb550708ea2> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Rationale: retract Shared --serve backend with thin --connect proxies for concurrent multi-client access" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/8f42538f-3c46-4e03-be7d-c700d1ccd2b1> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Rationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/8f42538f-3c46-4e03-be7d-c700d1ccd2b1> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Rationale: UUID deep links dispatch to canonical typed record interfaces" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/8f42538f-3c46-4e03-be7d-c700d1ccd2b1> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "codex" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/8f42538f-3c46-4e03-be7d-c700d1ccd2b1> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "The generic RecordPage made the same ADR, Requirement, or Lesson look different depending on whether it was reached from an external UUID link or selected in its UI list. The corrected contract routes typed records into their established generated-artifact interfaces while retaining the generic fallback required for Constraints and unsupported kinds." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/8f42538f-3c46-4e03-be7d-c700d1ccd2b1> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/8f42538f-3c46-4e03-be7d-c700d1ccd2b1> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-07-10T05:20:33.097334Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/8f42538f-3c46-4e03-be7d-c700d1ccd2b1> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Rationale: UUID deep links dispatch to canonical typed record interfaces" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/94851bc0-5787-45fc-98b1-61c3a8111a44> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Rationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/94851bc0-5787-45fc-98b1-61c3a8111a44> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Rationale: De-saturation lifts hybrid end-to-end answering" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/94851bc0-5787-45fc-98b1-61c3a8111a44> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "mcp" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/94851bc0-5787-45fc-98b1-61c3a8111a44> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "The tooluse figures (12/24 vs 14/24) were a grading artifact, not a model weakness. The 120k escape threshold (calibrated for single-push ORACLE ~50k) mis-flags legitimate 3-4 tool-call cells, which reach 120-190k via codex's cumulative per-turn prompt accounting, not source-reading: all 10 cells in 120-250k made >=3 MCP calls AND scored 1.0 (successes counted as misses). Re-grading escape at >250k corrects it." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/94851bc0-5787-45fc-98b1-61c3a8111a44> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/94851bc0-5787-45fc-98b1-61c3a8111a44> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-21T20:19:05.735664Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/94851bc0-5787-45fc-98b1-61c3a8111a44> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Rationale: De-saturation lifts hybrid end-to-end answering" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/952b72d1-a480-40b8-9fc0-6d5483fe3a2c> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Rationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/952b72d1-a480-40b8-9fc0-6d5483fe3a2c> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Cross-corpus currency: structured guarantees current, free-text gambles" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/952b72d1-a480-40b8-9fc0-6d5483fe3a2c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/952b72d1-a480-40b8-9fc0-6d5483fe3a2c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Across both temporally-bootstrapped corpora — moosedev-temporal (4 pairs) + burrow-temporal (3 pairs), N>=5/cell, codex gpt-5.4-mini + gpt-5.3-codex-spark, oracle+tooluse, graded by coverage-of-current-markers (Lesson 9fc21dc0): (1) B2 get_relevant_context NEVER SERVED a superseded record on any of the 7 pairs — current-only by construction (verified in pre-flight + 0 stale-served across all runs). The single B2 non-current answer (burrow report_voice, tooluse, 1/21) was the agent IGNORING memory and confabulating from the harness AGENTS.md/opencode.json overlay ('this project's local files don't define a synthesis-system rule') — a tooluse pull-gap, NOT the retrieval mechanism failing. (2) B1-rag currency-blind BM25 served current on 6/7 pairs (wherever the current record ranks >= the superseded) and collapsed only on the 1 RANK-INVERTED pair (moosedev glrc: 46% overall, ~8% in oracle/push) where the superseded record outranks the current in BM25. (3) burrow added 3 pairs, ALL non-rank-inverted -> 3 ties (quickstart, rest_rss, report_voice all ~100%/100%); rank-inversion thus occurred 1/7 (~14%) across organic histories — partly because the temporal-capture skill writes self-announcing current records (they narrate the reversal, so they carry both old+new keywords and rank well in BM25). (4) REGIME: the catastrophe is worst in oracle/push (stale top hit injected) and recovers in tooluse (agent digs past it); burrow's ties hold in both modes. NET CLAIM: structured currency is INSURANCE — an absolute guarantee (rank/corpus/model/regime-independent) against a free-text failure mode that is RARE but CATASTROPHIC (a confident, wrong, stale answer); it is NOT a uniform currency-accuracy win, since free-text ties whenever the current record ranks well (the common case). Honest scoping: demonstrating the structured ADVANTAGE requires a rank-inverted pair, which is uncommon organically, so the defensible value is the GUARANTEE, not an average-case delta. Generalizes/refines the moosedev-only currency results (Rationale abe11031, 2e88601d) to N=2 corpora; uses the burrow temporal bootstrap (Lesson 2d79b2d2) and tasks_public/burrow-temporal/*_currency.json." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/952b72d1-a480-40b8-9fc0-6d5483fe3a2c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "proposed" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/952b72d1-a480-40b8-9fc0-6d5483fe3a2c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-20T06:55:47.634627Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/952b72d1-a480-40b8-9fc0-6d5483fe3a2c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Cross-corpus currency conclusion (moosedev + burrow, 7 reversal pairs, N=2 corpora): structured = absolute current-only GUARANTEE; free-text = rank-dependent gamble that ties on 6/7 and collapses only on the 1 rank-inverted pair" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/960885ad-ca1a-40ef-b4a8-a165b277b862> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Rationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/960885ad-ca1a-40ef-b4a8-a165b277b862> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Rationale: De-saturation lifts hybrid end-to-end answering" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/960885ad-ca1a-40ef-b4a8-a165b277b862> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "mcp" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/960885ad-ca1a-40ef-b4a8-a165b277b862> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "The superseded record's tooluse figures (BM25F 21/24 vs hybrid 22/24) came from a score==1.0 hand-proxy, not the grader's strict-currency metric. The fixed mode-aware grader (hybrid_ab_report.py, escape 120k oracle / 250k tooluse) gives the authoritative mem-answered: tooluse BM25F 14/24 vs hybrid 19/24 — hybrid is FURTHER ahead than the proxy showed, because the old 120k cutoff over-penalized hybrid's legitimate multi-call cells (masking the edge / even inverting it to a spurious 12-vs-14 bm25f lead). Lesson: read the grader, not a proxy." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/960885ad-ca1a-40ef-b4a8-a165b277b862> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/960885ad-ca1a-40ef-b4a8-a165b277b862> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-21T20:25:57.047862Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/960885ad-ca1a-40ef-b4a8-a165b277b862> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Rationale: De-saturation lifts hybrid end-to-end answering" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/a0631a99-8f7a-453d-ba03-60ad78c48d42> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Rationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/a0631a99-8f7a-453d-ba03-60ad78c48d42> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Rationale: Instrument B (regraded): hybrid = -19% tokens + objprop/oracle edge; tooluse is a tie" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/a0631a99-8f7a-453d-ba03-60ad78c48d42> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/a0631a99-8f7a-453d-ba03-60ad78c48d42> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "The free regrade (after fixing the two hybrid_ab_report.py grading bugs) OVERTURNED the prior 'drift/tooluse +20pp' headline I recorded in 75f622d7. That gap was an ARTIFACT: the stale-flag + materialize_tree-blind escape proxy over-penalized BM25F's correct-but-narrating / high-token tooluse cells (BM25F tooluse 10/20 -> 18/20 after the fix). Corrected, tooluse is a near-tie (hybrid 19/20 vs bm25f 18/20); hybrid's real edge is in oracle/objprop coverage (5/5 vs 2/5) plus the -19% token efficiency. Recording the regraded result so the live finding is honest rather than the inflated one." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/a0631a99-8f7a-453d-ba03-60ad78c48d42> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/a0631a99-8f7a-453d-ba03-60ad78c48d42> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-22T20:50:45.724465Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/a0631a99-8f7a-453d-ba03-60ad78c48d42> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Rationale: Instrument B (regraded): hybrid = -19% tokens + objprop/oracle edge; tooluse is a tie" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/a08fb20f-0e0c-4775-bca6-e5315a479fdf> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Rationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/a08fb20f-0e0c-4775-bca6-e5315a479fdf> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Rationale: local no-pull confounded by tool presentation" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/a08fb20f-0e0c-4775-bca6-e5315a479fdf> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/a08fb20f-0e0c-4775-bca6-e5315a479fdf> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "The original lesson concluded local-no-pull is \"a model property, not an opencode artifact.\" That is overstated. (1) Pull was measured WITHOUT controlling tool presentation — the full ~9-tool moosedev surface, passive tool descriptions, amid all of opencode's own tools — a known-bad setup for small-model tool selection; so the \"model property\" claim is not established until retested with a recall-only single tool + a directive description + a single-param schema. (2) On execution-heavy tasks (cache-gap) the pull question is moot anyway, because local models cannot act on the lesson even when it is handed to them in-prompt (oracle=0.4 — Lesson 5a0e66fe)." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/a08fb20f-0e0c-4775-bca6-e5315a479fdf> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/a08fb20f-0e0c-4775-bca6-e5315a479fdf> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-19T05:00:32.795405Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/a08fb20f-0e0c-4775-bca6-e5315a479fdf> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Rationale: Local models did not PULL memory as-tested — but tool presentation was an untested confound, and on execution-heavy tasks pull is moot (execution ceiling)" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/a40b9f68-3627-4a5f-9860-2ba8cef084e7> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Rationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/a40b9f68-3627-4a5f-9860-2ba8cef084e7> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Rationale: recall precision via walk, no A-box index" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/a40b9f68-3627-4a5f-9860-2ba8cef084e7> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/a40b9f68-3627-4a5f-9860-2ba8cef084e7> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Correction: MOOSE was deliberately designed NOT to build a semantic/vector index over instance (A-box) data — walk planning exists precisely to avoid that imprecise-RAG trap and deliver more precise, auditable results. The superseded requirement proposed embedding-ranked A-box recall and embedding-based instance reconciliation, which reintroduces exactly that trap (violates invariants #1 symbolic-primary and #8 leverage-MOOSE). The precise retrieval path already exists symbolically, so the real work is tool selection, not a new index." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/a40b9f68-3627-4a5f-9860-2ba8cef084e7> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/a40b9f68-3627-4a5f-9860-2ba8cef084e7> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-18T04:57:08.718081Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/a40b9f68-3627-4a5f-9860-2ba8cef084e7> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Rationale: Improve recall precision via symbolic walk/sparql + tool-selection guidance (no A-box vector index)" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
