<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/ab1777b1-b810-46da-89d4-3a22d05d2563> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Rationale: Capability Stage-1 (N=3): categorical win across all four classes" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/ab1777b1-b810-46da-89d4-3a22d05d2563> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/ab1777b1-b810-46da-89d4-3a22d05d2563> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Tightened N=3 re-run with the 15-question suite (n=7-11/cell) refines the N=1 numbers and adds the honest threshold + multi-hop precision-artifact analysis; supersedes the N=1 finding as the current capability result." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/ab1777b1-b810-46da-89d4-3a22d05d2563> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/ab1777b1-b810-46da-89d4-3a22d05d2563> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-23T02:58:35.484633Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/ab1777b1-b810-46da-89d4-3a22d05d2563> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Rationale: Capability Stage-1 (N=3): categorical win across all four classes" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/abe11031-8ec9-4ac4-bf3e-49bbb5884e87> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Rationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/abe11031-8ec9-4ac4-bf3e-49bbb5884e87> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Rationale: 4 reversal pairs, structured guarantees current" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/abe11031-8ec9-4ac4-bf3e-49bbb5884e87> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/abe11031-8ec9-4ac4-bf3e-49bbb5884e87> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Tested 3 additional reversal pairs to check whether the get_relevant_context currency win generalizes. It does NOT generalize as a universal free-text failure: B2 guarantees current on all 4 pairs, but B1 failed catastrophically only on get_relevant_context (where the superseded record outranks the current in BM25) and recovered on the other 3 (where the current record ranks well and self-announces). So the accurate claim is structured GUARANTEE vs free-text content/rank-dependent gamble, not a flat 0%-vs-100% — a scope correction to the single-pair result." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/abe11031-8ec9-4ac4-bf3e-49bbb5884e87> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/abe11031-8ec9-4ac4-bf3e-49bbb5884e87> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-19T23:50:30.250542Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/abe11031-8ec9-4ac4-bf3e-49bbb5884e87> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Rationale: Currency A/B across 4 reversal pairs: structured memory GUARANTEES current (B2 100%/pair, all models); free-text currency is a RANK-dependent gamble — catastrophic (0%) only when the superseded record outranks the current in BM25, else it recovers (~100%)" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/bd2042a1-3e4e-4f9e-8173-b503f0f35d4e> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Rationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/bd2042a1-3e4e-4f9e-8173-b503f0f35d4e> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Rationale: flat graph, capture gap not ontology" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/bd2042a1-3e4e-4f9e-8173-b503f0f35d4e> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/bd2042a1-3e4e-4f9e-8173-b503f0f35d4e> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "The prior finding (f36482eb) established that the capture surface creates no inter-record edges except supersession, but did not localize the gap to a layer. A follow-up sparql over the loaded ontology's owl:ObjectProperty definitions shows the architecture ontology DOES define the needed relationship vocabulary, so the model is adequate and the gap is specifically the MCP WRITE PATH — not the ontology. This re-points the fix at the tooling layer." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/bd2042a1-3e4e-4f9e-8173-b503f0f35d4e> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/bd2042a1-3e4e-4f9e-8173-b503f0f35d4e> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-19T07:00:26.354224Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/bd2042a1-3e4e-4f9e-8173-b503f0f35d4e> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Rationale: The flat graph is a CAPTURE/TOOLING gap, NOT an ontology gap: the architecture ontology defines a rich relationship vocabulary (violates, concerns, constrains, isMotivatedBy, learnedFrom, resultsIn, weighs, supersedes) but the MCP write tools populate only supersedes + hasRationale" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/c490a03d-6f26-4679-9075-c8668af1426c> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Rationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/c490a03d-6f26-4679-9075-c8668af1426c> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Rationale: no execution ceiling, injection enabled fix" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/c490a03d-6f26-4679-9075-c8668af1426c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/c490a03d-6f26-4679-9075-c8668af1426c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Last session's \"execution ceiling\" rested on two errors, both refuted by primary evidence. (a) B0+oracle injects no context: run.py:176 gates injection on `mode=='oracle' AND arm!='B0'`, so the dense-27b/gemma/A3B \"oracle 0.4\" runs cited as the ceiling (18665903, 41dbc597, ea9687d9) were actually COLD runs — a category error. (b) The genuine local push success (e0ee0429, B2-oracle, A3B, score 1.0) was misread as frontier by generalizing from a DIFFERENT 1.0 run (884fe011, which is frontier-cold B0-tooluse) instead of checking e0ee0429's own identity; agent_model=lmstudio/qwen3.6-35b-a3b-mlx + a 1.697M-token local fingerprint (frontier runs here are ≤177k) + a complete cross-module patch confirm it was the local A3B. Net: memory injection took a local model 0.4→1.0 on the multi-module cache-gap task; no ceiling exists." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/c490a03d-6f26-4679-9075-c8668af1426c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/c490a03d-6f26-4679-9075-c8668af1426c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-19T05:24:06.250137Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/c490a03d-6f26-4679-9075-c8668af1426c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Rationale: No execution ceiling — a local model made the FULL multi-module cache-gap fix when the record was INJECTED (push/B2-oracle = 1.0) vs 0.4 cold/pull; the earlier \"ceiling\" was a B0-oracle artifact plus a provider misread" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/ccfac08f-0221-4a0b-b690-2dedc02be062> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Rationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/ccfac08f-0221-4a0b-b690-2dedc02be062> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Rationale: push/injection delivery is built and evidence-supported" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/ccfac08f-0221-4a0b-b690-2dedc02be062> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/ccfac08f-0221-4a0b-b690-2dedc02be062> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "The prior AD downgraded push to \"value unproven — execution ceiling.\" That downgrade rested on the now-refuted ceiling claim (see the Lesson superseding 5a0e66fe). Primary evidence — run.py:176 oracle-arm gating (B0+oracle = cold), the e0ee0429 patch (full cross-module implementation), and agent_model + the 1.697M-token local fingerprint — shows the only genuine injection test on a local model scored 1.0 and was the only condition to beat 0.4. Push value for local models is therefore supported (n=1, pending replication), not unproven." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/ccfac08f-0221-4a0b-b690-2dedc02be062> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/ccfac08f-0221-4a0b-b690-2dedc02be062> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-19T05:24:22.905811Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/ccfac08f-0221-4a0b-b690-2dedc02be062> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Rationale: Push/injection delivery: built, mechanically validated, AND evidence-supported — injecting the record took a local model 0.4→1.0 on the multi-module cache-gap task (the only condition that worked)" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/deadcb05-97ad-403e-817c-dd47cfbb92d3> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Rationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/deadcb05-97ad-403e-817c-dd47cfbb92d3> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Rationale: retract With a module-level link in place, token-less positions (comments, blank lines) surface the module dossier via rust-analyzer whole-file module occurrences - 2026-07-08 acceptance finding, resolution pending" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/deadcb05-97ad-403e-817c-dd47cfbb92d3> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "phase7-acceptance" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/deadcb05-97ad-403e-817c-dd47cfbb92d3> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Resolved: AD ab379ef4 (whole-file module occurrences are not position hits) removed the module fallback - token-less positions now miss honestly, so this consequence no longer holds." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/deadcb05-97ad-403e-817c-dd47cfbb92d3> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/deadcb05-97ad-403e-817c-dd47cfbb92d3> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-07-09T14:41:49.542636Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/deadcb05-97ad-403e-817c-dd47cfbb92d3> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Rationale: retract With a module-level link in place, token-less positions (comments, blank lines) surface the module dossier via rust-analyzer whole-file module occurrences - 2026-07-08 acceptance finding, resolution pending" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/ee150eab-c520-48b2-849e-2621fbecd1b7> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Rationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/ee150eab-c520-48b2-849e-2621fbecd1b7> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Rationale: pull gap is real, push closes it" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/ee150eab-c520-48b2-849e-2621fbecd1b7> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/ee150eab-c520-48b2-849e-2621fbecd1b7> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "The superseded lesson claimed pull is moot on execution-heavy tasks because local models hit an execution ceiling. That premise is false (e0ee0429: A3B B2-oracle = 1.0, full multi-module patch — see the Lesson superseding 5a0e66fe). Pull-vs-push is therefore a real, live comparison on coding tasks, and the current evidence shows push closing the pull gap (0.4→1.0). The valid parts (local-no-pull as-tested; the tool-presentation confound) are retained." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/ee150eab-c520-48b2-849e-2621fbecd1b7> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/ee150eab-c520-48b2-849e-2621fbecd1b7> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-19T05:24:29.9739Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/ee150eab-c520-48b2-849e-2621fbecd1b7> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Rationale: Pull gap is real (local models don't retrieve/act → 0.4 at B2-tooluse) and PUSH closes it (B2-oracle = 1.0); the \"pull moot via execution ceiling\" clause is withdrawn; pull's presentation-confound is still open" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/ee42fef4-9089-4921-8b33-9315a60f7a99> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Rationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/ee42fef4-9089-4921-8b33-9315a60f7a99> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Rationale: Instrument B (corrected): hybrid wins drift; anti-cases were grading artifacts" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/ee42fef4-9089-4921-8b33-9315a60f7a99> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/ee42fef4-9089-4921-8b33-9315a60f7a99> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Free transcript inspection (no agent re-run) showed BOTH anti-case caveats in the superseded version were GRADING ARTIFACTS, not hybrid weaknesses. objprop_validate's low mem% is the stale-marker narration false-positive (extends Lesson 9fc21dc0): the matcher trips on backtick-wrapped negation ('no `debug_assert`') AND on the stale marker 'debug-only' which is literally in the CURRENT decision's own title ('...without debug-only panics'), so citing the canonical decision self-trips — under coverage (the 9fc21dc0-endorsed verdict) hybrid WINS objprop (full coverage 5/5 oracle vs bm25f 2/5). geospatial's 'regression' is one cell's 339k-token internal reasoning thrash tripping the tooluse escape proxy on a materialize_tree=False task with NO source to escape to (answer was correct, 224 chars, 1 tool call) — a tie, not a regression. Correcting the record so the live finding reflects the strengthened result and names the two harness bugs." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/ee42fef4-9089-4921-8b33-9315a60f7a99> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/ee42fef4-9089-4921-8b33-9315a60f7a99> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-22T20:29:09.141039Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/ee42fef4-9089-4921-8b33-9315a60f7a99> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Rationale: Instrument B (corrected): hybrid wins drift; anti-cases were grading artifacts" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/ee5cbe86-48df-4fec-b078-4d16353452be> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Rationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/ee5cbe86-48df-4fec-b078-4d16353452be> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Rationale: GROWL enrich co-locates inferred edges in kg/project" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/ee5cbe86-48df-4fec-b078-4d16353452be> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/11e01ea2-f520-4f7c-a165-09532dacd43f> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/ee5cbe86-48df-4fec-b078-4d16353452be> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/ee5cbe86-48df-4fec-b078-4d16353452be> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Reading Trivyn's actual enrich implementation (trivyn/src/rdf/reasoning.rs) showed materialize_property_inferences writes inferred triples INTO the data graph + per-triple RDF-star prov, NOT a separate inferred named graph (that's only Trivyn's full-reasoning path, run_reasoning). And confirmed moosedev's get_relevant_context expansion reads are all kg/project-scoped (record_neighbors src/graph/mod.rs:1585, build_context_item:1760, list_instances:1728), so co-locating inferred edges in kg/project makes them first-class with zero hot-path change, while a separate kg/inferred graph would need unioning into 5-8 reads. The separate-graph placement in the superseded record predated reading Trivyn's code and the kg/project-scoped-read finding." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/ee5cbe86-48df-4fec-b078-4d16353452be> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/ee5cbe86-48df-4fec-b078-4d16353452be> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-22T03:20:15.613005Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/ee5cbe86-48df-4fec-b078-4d16353452be> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Rationale: GROWL enrich co-locates inferred edges in kg/project" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/f99703a9-9688-4e82-a195-532c7be0eddd> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Rationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/f99703a9-9688-4e82-a195-532c7be0eddd> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Rationale: Tool-level capture-gap fix is built: inline relations + suggester + advisory" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/f99703a9-9688-4e82-a195-532c7be0eddd> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/f99703a9-9688-4e82-a195-532c7be0eddd> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "The \"unbuilt\" conclusion of 3f807592 is now false. Parts (a) and (b) of its prescribed fix shipped at the open-source tool layer (AD 8353c51a): record_important_decision takes inline relations (atomic, SHACL-validated); a symbolic link-suggester + suggest_links tool surface legal candidates; validate emits a non-blocking under-linked advisory. Part (c) was already done by the bootstrap skill (AD 059b01b7). One refinement vs the diagnosis: the validate nudge is a Rust/SPARQL advisory rather than declarative sh:severity sh:Warning, because MOOSE's M3 validator has no severity handling and skips sh:class/sh:or — declarative severity is a deferred MOOSE-core change." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/f99703a9-9688-4e82-a195-532c7be0eddd> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/f99703a9-9688-4e82-a195-532c7be0eddd> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-22T07:53:53.652684Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/f99703a9-9688-4e82-a195-532c7be0eddd> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Rationale: Tool-level capture-gap fix is built: inline relations + suggester + advisory" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/fa5b6ae3-bab5-4afa-a21e-ac1f18e5467b> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Rationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/fa5b6ae3-bab5-4afa-a21e-ac1f18e5467b> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Rationale: relate() validates endpoints against SHACL shapes" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/fa5b6ae3-bab5-4afa-a21e-ac1f18e5467b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "codex-mcp-client" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/fa5b6ae3-bab5-4afa-a21e-ac1f18e5467b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "The prior relate design required both endpoints to be InformationRecords, which rejected legitimate relationships to SystemComponent and allowed some predicate/object mistakes because it did not consult declared shape constraints. User correction clarified that dcam:rangeIncludes should not drive validation; SHACL shapes are the authoritative contract for relationship ranges, and trivyn:labelProperty is a typed-property mirror hint while rdfs:label remains canonical." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/fa5b6ae3-bab5-4afa-a21e-ac1f18e5467b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/fa5b6ae3-bab5-4afa-a21e-ac1f18e5467b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-19T17:07:19.956747Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/fa5b6ae3-bab5-4afa-a21e-ac1f18e5467b> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Rationale: relate() validates relationship endpoints against SHACL shapes; capture keeps rdfs:label canonical and mirrors it into class-specific typed properties" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/fccd0ced-ab3f-4e87-a5d7-4e02e55d3d73> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Rationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/fccd0ced-ab3f-4e87-a5d7-4e02e55d3d73> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Rationale: MOOSEDev read cost is moderate + query-dependent; the 1.68M was a dead-MCP grep" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/fccd0ced-ab3f-4e87-a5d7-4e02e55d3d73> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/fccd0ced-ab3f-4e87-a5d7-4e02e55d3d73> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "f8f2f87c attributed B2's 1.68M set-completeness cost to 'agent query competence' (the agent allegedly choosing list_mcp_resources over SPARQL). The clean re-run with a fixed MCP (Lesson 0a890ea9) shows the 1.68M was actually the DEAD-MCP grep of the store (broken MOOSEDEV_BIN), and with a working MCP B2 returns the 122-set via sparql at ~78-167k tokens (recall 1.0). So the cause was a harness bug, not query competence — there is no 'B2 payoff conditional on agent query competence' problem; gpt-5.4-mini calls the right tool reliably when the MCP works." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/fccd0ced-ab3f-4e87-a5d7-4e02e55d3d73> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/fccd0ced-ab3f-4e87-a5d7-4e02e55d3d73> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-23T19:17:47.866259Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/fccd0ced-ab3f-4e87-a5d7-4e02e55d3d73> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Rationale: MOOSEDev read cost is moderate + query-dependent; the 1.68M was a dead-MCP grep" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/08b807a4-d7fa-4b0a-ad84-78158a4a8088> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Requirement> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/08b807a4-d7fa-4b0a-ad84-78158a4a8088> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Frictionless onboarding & install for external adopters" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/08b807a4-d7fa-4b0a-ad84-78158a4a8088> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "onboarding-capture" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/08b807a4-d7fa-4b0a-ad84-78158a4a8088> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Productization goal (user framing, 2026-07-01): someone other than the author must be able to install and use MOOSEDev easily, WITHOUT source access to the closed MOOSE engine. Concretely: a one-command install channel (script + Homebrew) delivering a self-contained binary, plus one-command project setup (`moosedev init`) that wires MCP config and the version-controlled memory. This is the distribution funnel (invariant #11), un-gated by the in-anger trial. Sibling to Requirement d459cac2 (version-controllable KG — the sharing enabler); distinct from Requirement 5565038e (cross-machine merge dedup — the multi-person case, deferred/trial-gated)." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/08b807a4-d7fa-4b0a-ad84-78158a4a8088> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/08b807a4-d7fa-4b0a-ad84-78158a4a8088> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-07-04T17:37:12.171565Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/08b807a4-d7fa-4b0a-ad84-78158a4a8088> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Frictionless onboarding & install for external adopters" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/14a4275c-d688-466e-96b5-9d4b46ea593c> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Requirement> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/14a4275c-d688-466e-96b5-9d4b46ea593c> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Recall precision via symbolic walk/sparql" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/14a4275c-d688-466e-96b5-9d4b46ea593c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/14a4275c-d688-466e-96b5-9d4b46ea593c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Recall precision comes from existing symbolic mechanisms, not instance embeddings: (a) query (NLQ) gives walk-planned, synthesized, trace-bearing answers; (b) sparql gives exact structural reads; (c) get_relevant_context stays a fast, deterministic, SHALLOW anchor/browse tool — the 0.45 relevance floor is the correct honesty fix and it must NOT be upgraded to vector search. Real work item: make tool selection reliable — sharpen the get_relevant_context / query / sparql tool descriptions (and CLAUDE.md) to encode the precision/cost ladder so agents escalate from shallow anchor-recall to walk-planned reasoning. A-box reconciliation (dedup/contradiction) stays symbolic + LLM-as-sensor per Requirement b5b101dd, not vector similarity. No custom pipeline; compose existing MOOSE (invariant #8)." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/14a4275c-d688-466e-96b5-9d4b46ea593c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "superseded" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/14a4275c-d688-466e-96b5-9d4b46ea593c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasRationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/a40b9f68-3627-4a5f-9860-2ba8cef084e7> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/14a4275c-d688-466e-96b5-9d4b46ea593c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-18T04:57:08.718081Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/14a4275c-d688-466e-96b5-9d4b46ea593c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Improve recall precision via symbolic walk/sparql + tool-selection guidance (no A-box vector index)" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/14a4275c-d688-466e-96b5-9d4b46ea593c> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#supersedes> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/f1ccd65b-f816-470b-9b59-8c4f85716bb3> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/1ae3b79a-f2c5-41ba-a221-cc79bfe9edc2> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Requirement> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/1ae3b79a-f2c5-41ba-a221-cc79bfe9edc2> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Add an in-place status/retract transition for knowledge records" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/1ae3b79a-f2c5-41ba-a221-cc79bfe9edc2> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/1ae3b79a-f2c5-41ba-a221-cc79bfe9edc2> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "supersede_decision now generalizes the REPLACE transition to all InformationRecord subclasses, but the lifecycle still lacks a non-replacing status transition. Needed: a set-status / retract primitive that flips an existing record's hasLifecycleStatus (e.g. proposed→accepted, accepted→implemented, *→deprecated) WITHOUT minting a replacement, preserving provenance. The status vocabulary itself is thin — there is no \"implemented\"/\"done\" value distinct from \"accepted\" — so this likely also wants an explicit completed/implemented status. Until then, an implemented Requirement can only be marked by superseding it, which conflates \"fulfilled\" with \"replaced\". Relates to b5b101dd (detect/surface/supersede contradictory entries) and the read path that already hides superseded/deprecated for all kinds." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/1ae3b79a-f2c5-41ba-a221-cc79bfe9edc2> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/1ae3b79a-f2c5-41ba-a221-cc79bfe9edc2> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasRationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/588b3f17-8dfa-4290-990f-28fbc98d2ea2> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/1ae3b79a-f2c5-41ba-a221-cc79bfe9edc2> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-18T05:18:28.243587Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/1ae3b79a-f2c5-41ba-a221-cc79bfe9edc2> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Add an in-place status/retract transition for knowledge records" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/1ae3b79a-f2c5-41ba-a221-cc79bfe9edc2> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#supersedes> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/32c4bffe-17d4-47bd-ac76-2b0b6f31dd62> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/32c4bffe-17d4-47bd-ac76-2b0b6f31dd62> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Requirement> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/32c4bffe-17d4-47bd-ac76-2b0b6f31dd62> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Extend the supersede/retract lifecycle beyond ArchitecturalDecision" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/32c4bffe-17d4-47bd-ac76-2b0b6f31dd62> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/32c4bffe-17d4-47bd-ac76-2b0b6f31dd62> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Gap hit while correcting knowledge: supersede_decision rejects any target that is not an ArchitecturalDecision (\"not an ArchitecturalDecision in the project graph\"), and no other tool can set a Requirement/Constraint/Lesson to superseded or deprecated. So non-AD knowledge cannot be retired or corrected through the lifecycle — when such a record turns out wrong, the only options are leaving an active contradiction or editing the store out-of-band. Concretely, Requirement f1ccd65b and Constraint 0c2106ab both contradict MOOSE's deliberate no-instance-indexing design and SHOULD be retired, but cannot be. The read path (relevant_context) already hides superseded/deprecated for ALL kinds, so only the WRITE side is missing. Fix: extend supersede_decision (or add a retract/set-status tool) to operate on any knowledge class — link new -supersedes-> old with a linked Rationale and mark the old record superseded, preserving history. Directly relates to Requirement b5b101dd (detect/surface/supersede contradictory entries). Until then, contradictions are surfaced (via the correcting Lesson 89dc91bd) but not retired." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/32c4bffe-17d4-47bd-ac76-2b0b6f31dd62> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "superseded" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/32c4bffe-17d4-47bd-ac76-2b0b6f31dd62> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-18T03:59:43.397895Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/32c4bffe-17d4-47bd-ac76-2b0b6f31dd62> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Extend the supersede/retract lifecycle beyond ArchitecturalDecision" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/350c7f2e-61bd-49e4-b7cd-2fdd3f51f521> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Requirement> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/350c7f2e-61bd-49e4-b7cd-2fdd3f51f521> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "MOOSEDev v3: standalone neurosymbolic coding agent, not an MCP sidecar" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/350c7f2e-61bd-49e4-b7cd-2fdd3f51f521> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/350c7f2e-61bd-49e4-b7cd-2fdd3f51f521> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "The eventual v3 goal: MOOSEDev evolves from an MCP memory sidecar into a full neurosymbolic coding agent in its own right — owning the agent loop, with the symbolic layer (project KG of intent + an AST/code-structure graph as world model + a symbolic planner) as the CONTROLLER and the LLM relegated to a sensor/effector (invariant #1: LLM is a sensor, not the controller). Trajectory: v1 = passive MCP memory sidecar (current); v2 = add AST/code-structure indexing (a structural world-model substrate) plus an active-agency layer; v3 = MOOSEDev IS the coding agent, no longer parasitic on a host agent (Claude Code / Cursor / Codex) for code navigation or control flow. Differentiator vs pure-LLM agents: symbolic, auditable control grounded in typed memory + a verifiable code graph, rather than LLM-as-controller. This is the terminus of the 'active memory participant, not passive tool' direction (AD 145af7e9) — the active-agency layer eventually absorbs the whole loop." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/350c7f2e-61bd-49e4-b7cd-2fdd3f51f521> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/350c7f2e-61bd-49e4-b7cd-2fdd3f51f521> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-23T01:53:29.896196Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/350c7f2e-61bd-49e4-b7cd-2fdd3f51f521> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "MOOSEDev v3: standalone neurosymbolic coding agent, not an MCP sidecar" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/4ab93555-0d8d-4bb5-abf5-ce3241f2be90> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Requirement> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/4ab93555-0d8d-4bb5-abf5-ce3241f2be90> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "In-anger trial: frozen probe registry (16 supersession probes)" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/4ab93555-0d8d-4bb5-abf5-ce3241f2be90> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#concerns> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/SystemComponent/ce49a867-7ebc-41d5-879c-fa59eed3ae65> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/4ab93555-0d8d-4bb5-abf5-ce3241f2be90> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/4ab93555-0d8d-4bb5-abf5-ce3241f2be90> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Frozen pre-registered probe set for the in-anger trial (operationalizes AD 07415633; governed by kill Constraint 75b0cf14). 16 context_recovery 'why-we-moved' probes over SUPERSESSION reversals — the old approach is deleted from the current tree, so the why is NON-LOCAL by construction. Ratified by James and FROZEN 2026-06-24; only ADDED later, never revised. Graded by a blind LLM judge (bench/judge_recovery.py) against PRIMARY-source gold answers, never the in-graph record (anti-circularity).\n\ntrivyn (10, under BENCH_HOME/trivyn-trial/tasks): why_growl_over_reasonable, retire_owl_reasoning_screen, yasqe_over_codemirror, moose_only_alignment, local_embeddings_via_moose, editions_sqlite_pg_split, graphs_schema_direct_traversal, annotations_scan_quads, ontology_persist_by_graph_iri, remove_clustering_from_excerpt.\nmoose (6, under BENCH_HOME/moose-trial/tasks): shape_aware_filter_resolution, role_routed_arctic_fleet, seeded_defn_cosine_confidence, category_singleton_coherence, designator_leaf_category, l3_rank_cap_exemptions.\n\nNOTABLE FINDING: remove_clustering_from_excerpt exposed a CAPTURE GAP — the misleading commit subject ('getting tests building') had poisoned BOTH the drafted gold AND the temporal-captured graph rationale. James supplied the real why (the embedding-based semantic search ignored the core ontologies' STRUCTURE and added INAPPROPRIATE matches — a quality fix); the trivyn-trial graph was corrected (AD 1d36f22e superseded by a31b75d3) so B2 serves truth. This VALIDATED the anti-circularity rule: had the gold been the in-graph record, B2 would have scored 'correct' against a wrong why and the gap would have stayed invisible. 4 trivyn golds (yasqe, editions, graphs_schema, ontology_persist) were commit-silent on the why; James reviewed and accepted the inferred drafts." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/4ab93555-0d8d-4bb5-abf5-ce3241f2be90> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/4ab93555-0d8d-4bb5-abf5-ce3241f2be90> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-24T15:14:34.59467Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/4ab93555-0d8d-4bb5-abf5-ce3241f2be90> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "In-anger trial: frozen probe registry (16 supersession probes)" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/5565038e-3109-4943-883d-1b46591fd592> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Requirement> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/5565038e-3109-4943-883d-1b46591fd592> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Prevent duplicate knowledge instances at capture time" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/5565038e-3109-4943-883d-1b46591fd592> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/5565038e-3109-4943-883d-1b46591fd592> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "graph::record_instance mints a fresh UUID per call (mint_instance_iri) with no existence check, so re-running a capture (e.g. record_important_decision with the same title) creates distinct instances sharing the same hasTitle. Graph integrity currently depends on the calling agent — a violation of invariant #1 (symbolic layer primary). Verified: a SPARQL dedup check (group by hasTitle HAVING count>1 in the project graph) returns 0 today, but only because volume is small. The symbolic layer should own dedup. Composable options: (1) exact idempotent guard — on capture, reuse the existing instance of the same class + normalized title rather than minting; (2) deterministic content-hash IRI (class + normalized title) so identical captures collapse by construction while the provenance graph still records each event separately; (3) embedding-based near-duplicate detection surfaced as a merge suggestion (needs instance-level embeddings — the vector store is T-box only today). Prefer enforcing via MOOSE's assert_instance AssertionValidator hook so every write path is protected, not just this tool. Especially important now that agents auto-capture." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/5565038e-3109-4943-883d-1b46591fd592> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/5565038e-3109-4943-883d-1b46591fd592> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-17T23:27:18.687496Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/5565038e-3109-4943-883d-1b46591fd592> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Prevent duplicate knowledge instances at capture time" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/74423463-3982-4620-b8bd-f72e5987778e> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Requirement> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/74423463-3982-4620-b8bd-f72e5987778e> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Migrate existing A-box instances on breaking ontology change" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/74423463-3982-4620-b8bd-f72e5987778e> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/74423463-3982-4620-b8bd-f72e5987778e> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "The vector-store cache keeps only the T-box (ontology term embeddings) fresh; it does nothing for captured A-box instances. A cache hit therefore does not imply recorded data is still valid. A breaking ontology change (renamed/removed class, namespace shift) orphans existing instances, which store concrete class/property IRIs resolved at capture time. Need an explicit migration triggered on a detected ontology-version change (re-type via a mapping — never hardcode old namespaces). Additive ontology changes (new classes/properties, stable IRIs) need no A-box migration. The fingerprint cache is forward-compatible: an ontology change flips the fingerprint and forces a vector rebuild, which can be the same trigger point for the A-box migration. Tracked as P1 in tasks/todo.md (Ontology-regeneration orphans existing records)." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/74423463-3982-4620-b8bd-f72e5987778e> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/74423463-3982-4620-b8bd-f72e5987778e> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-17T23:14:05.727497Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/74423463-3982-4620-b8bd-f72e5987778e> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Migrate existing A-box instances on breaking ontology change" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/98b589fe-7a58-4fe6-8a2a-7b93ade3f2b3> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Requirement> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/98b589fe-7a58-4fe6-8a2a-7b93ade3f2b3> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Temporal git-walk bootstrap on burrow corpus" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/98b589fe-7a58-4fe6-8a2a-7b93ade3f2b3> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/98b589fe-7a58-4fe6-8a2a-7b93ade3f2b3> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Future-work item (raised by the user). Today the only corpus with real supersession chains is moosedev-temporal (built by the temporal git-walk bootstrap, Lesson d1b44d5e), so the H4 currency/anti-staleness result (Rationale 51338ce8, abe11031, 2e88601d) rests on ONE corpus. Running the same temporal bootstrap on burrow would (a) generalize the temporal bootstrap itself from N=1 to N=2 — directly addressing the honest caveat in d1b44d5e — and (b) produce burrow supersession chains + a real commit-dated timeline, enabling a second, independent currency A/B (currency-blind B1 vs supersede-aware B2) that would test whether the structured-currency-GUARANTEE generalizes beyond moosedev. PREREQS/NOTES: burrow must be a git-walkable repo with a first-parent main history that contains real reversals (verify burrow has commit history, not just the seeded corpus/burrow.json snapshot — burrow was authored as a synthetic corpus, so a temporal timeline may need to be constructed/committed first). Use the deterministic commit-date/author stamping driver (committed 0cb4602) so new.hasTimestamp >= old.hasTimestamp holds. Use a VETTED faster capture agent (codex-spark / gpt-5.4-mini / gpt-5.5 low-effort via the codex backend) per the 'next' note in d1b44d5e — NOT Haiku (it records but drops the recall->supersede sequence, losing supersessions). After bootstrap: validate_against_architecture (expect 0 violations), then add burrow currency reversal-pair tasks and run the B0/B1-md/B1-rag/B2 x oracle/tooluse matrix, grading currency by coverage of current-markers (Lesson 9fc21dc0). Relates to d1b44d5e (temporal bootstrap), bd96a65f (burrow pilot), 8a06ad1d (bench scope: currency is the longitudinal axis), and the model-suite AD 8b48ab85." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/98b589fe-7a58-4fe6-8a2a-7b93ade3f2b3> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/98b589fe-7a58-4fe6-8a2a-7b93ade3f2b3> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-20T03:57:32.093905Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/98b589fe-7a58-4fe6-8a2a-7b93ade3f2b3> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Run the temporal git-walk bootstrap on the burrow corpus to generalize the bootstrap (N=1→2) and unlock a second-corpus currency A/B" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/b2f8240c-70f4-471f-929e-089ef6b52a43> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Requirement> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/b2f8240c-70f4-471f-929e-089ef6b52a43> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Expose supersede + rationale; preserve history" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/b2f8240c-70f4-471f-929e-089ef6b52a43> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/b2f8240c-70f4-471f-929e-089ef6b52a43> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "The architecture ontology ALREADY models decision evolution: supersedes (ObjectProperty, new decision -> the one it replaces), hasRationale (-> the typed Rationale class, the WHY), and hasLifecycleStatus values proposed/accepted/superseded/deprecated; there is even a competency question \"Which architectural decision supersedes a previous one?\". The gap is purely the write surface: graph::record_instance hardcodes object_props to &[] and record_important_decision accepts only literals, so supersedes/hasRationale are never written. Required behavior when a decision changes: (1) mint the new decision; (2) assert new supersedes old; (3) attach a Rationale node capturing WHY it changed (typed, not just prose — invariant #2); (4) transition the OLD decision's hasLifecycleStatus to \"superseded\" WITHOUT deleting it — the prior record stays as immutable historical context (the comprehension-debt \"why\"); the provenance graph already records who/when. Query layer should default to current (accepted) decisions but allow walking the supersedes chain for history. This is the resolution half of the contradiction requirement (b5b101dd): detect conflict -> resolve by supersede + rationale, never silent overwrite. Concrete first step independent of core MOOSE: add object-property support to the capture path + a supersede mode to the tool." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/b2f8240c-70f4-471f-929e-089ef6b52a43> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/b2f8240c-70f4-471f-929e-089ef6b52a43> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-17T23:32:12.032798Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/b2f8240c-70f4-471f-929e-089ef6b52a43> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Expose supersede + rationale in capture; preserve superseded decisions as history" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/b3ba8285-746d-4f3e-a092-b8e4fc324149> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Requirement> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/b3ba8285-746d-4f3e-a092-b8e4fc324149> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "NLQ must answer content-recall and structural queries" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/b3ba8285-746d-4f3e-a092-b8e4fc324149> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/b3ba8285-746d-4f3e-a092-b8e4fc324149> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "NLQ must answer BOTH content-recall questions (\"does X do Y?\", \"why Z?\" — answers living in record prose) and structural/multi-hop queries (\"what supersedes X\", \"rationale for Y\" — answers living in the edges). Today it serves neither well: content-recall hits the single-shot clarification gate because graph-walk is the wrong engine (a65d1bbe), and structural queries have almost no edges to walk (the flat graph, 96456e40). This requirement is what motivates both the query-routing decision (content→retrieval fallback) and the GROWL-enrichment + capture work (materialize/draw the edges). Derived from diagnosis a65d1bbe (which, being a Lesson, the model won't let a decision cite directly via isMotivatedBy — a concrete capture-gap detail)." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/b3ba8285-746d-4f3e-a092-b8e4fc324149> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/b3ba8285-746d-4f3e-a092-b8e4fc324149> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-22T00:10:44.44892Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/b3ba8285-746d-4f3e-a092-b8e4fc324149> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "NLQ must answer content-recall and structural queries" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/b401ef5e-8962-446e-88f1-73ff383888f6> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Requirement> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/b401ef5e-8962-446e-88f1-73ff383888f6> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "get_relevant_context → query → sparql precision/cost ladder" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/b401ef5e-8962-446e-88f1-73ff383888f6> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/b401ef5e-8962-446e-88f1-73ff383888f6> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Keeps the still-valid work item from the superseded requirement: make tool selection reliable — sharpen the get_relevant_context / query / sparql tool descriptions (and CLAUDE.md) so agents escalate from shallow anchor-recall to walk-planned reasoning to exact structural reads. The ladder: get_relevant_context = fast hybrid (BM25F⊕dense) anchor + bounded typed expansion (recall, paraphrase-tolerant); query = walk-planned, synthesized, trace-bearing answers (precision/reasoning); sparql = exact, complete, deterministic reads (dedup, bulk, version-control export). DROPS the superseded requirement's prohibition on A-box vector indexing: get_relevant_context now seeds with a hybrid dense channel (AD b933bd10) under the narrowed Constraint af5ebd6d — dense as a bounded SEED feeding the symbolic typed expansion, walk planning still the precision engine, confidence floor preserving honest-empty-state. A-box reconciliation (dedup/contradiction) stays symbolic + LLM-as-sensor per Requirement b5b101dd. Compose existing MOOSE (invariant #8)." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/b401ef5e-8962-446e-88f1-73ff383888f6> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/b401ef5e-8962-446e-88f1-73ff383888f6> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasRationale> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Rationale/2456f9ef-08c6-4f3a-ab94-dd2213df53a6> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/b401ef5e-8962-446e-88f1-73ff383888f6> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-21T07:26:00.337169Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/b401ef5e-8962-446e-88f1-73ff383888f6> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Encode the get_relevant_context → query → sparql precision/cost ladder in tool-selection guidance (A-box dense seed now permitted)" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/b401ef5e-8962-446e-88f1-73ff383888f6> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#supersedes> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/14a4275c-d688-466e-96b5-9d4b46ea593c> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/b5b101dd-5f5b-4300-b01d-82ca14e9f7e0> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Requirement> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/b5b101dd-5f5b-4300-b01d-82ca14e9f7e0> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Detect and surface contradictory knowledge entries" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/b5b101dd-5f5b-4300-b01d-82ca14e9f7e0> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/b5b101dd-5f5b-4300-b01d-82ca14e9f7e0> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Beyond duplicates, graph integrity requires handling contradictory entries, at three levels. (a) Schema/logical contradiction — e.g. more than one value for a functional/maxCount-1 property, or disjoint-class membership; partly covered today by SHACL via validate_against_architecture, extend shapes as needed. (b) Decision-level conflict — two ArchitecturalDecisions making opposite choices both marked accepted (e.g. Unix socket vs TCP port); needs a typed conflictsWith/supersedes relation plus a lifecycle so a new decision supersedes the old rather than silently coexisting. (c) Factual/semantic contradiction in free-text descriptions — detectable only with the LLM as a sensor (NLI), then represented symbolically as a typed conflict for human/agent adjudication, never silently resolved. Guiding principle (invariants #1 and #6): prefer detect -> surface -> supersede with provenance over silent prevent/overwrite, because a contradiction is often legitimate evolution and the integrity move is to make the change explicit and auditable. Relates to the supersede/retract lifecycle deferred in core MOOSE (Ask 2 scope) and to the duplicate-prevention requirement." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/b5b101dd-5f5b-4300-b01d-82ca14e9f7e0> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/b5b101dd-5f5b-4300-b01d-82ca14e9f7e0> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-17T23:27:20.401583Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/b5b101dd-5f5b-4300-b01d-82ca14e9f7e0> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Detect and surface contradictory knowledge entries" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/d459cac2-09f6-4f7b-b959-0f5337d6c5f4> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Requirement> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/d459cac2-09f6-4f7b-b959-0f5337d6c5f4> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Version-controllable project KG: text serialization canonical, RocksDB cache" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/d459cac2-09f6-4f7b-b959-0f5337d6c5f4> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/d459cac2-09f6-4f7b-b959-0f5337d6c5f4> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Decision (user-confirmed): multi-project memory uses a PER-PROJECT store (not a central named-graph store), specifically so each project's knowledge graph can be put UNDER VERSION CONTROL and SHARED with other maintainers. This adds a requirement the current storage design does not meet: the live store is RocksDB (oxigraph, binary, single-writer — AD 0d81e237), which cannot be committed/diffed/merged. Resolution (text-canonical, DB-as-cache): (1) the committed SOURCE OF TRUTH becomes a deterministic, canonically-sorted TEXT serialization of the project KG (and optionally the provenance graph) — N-Quads or Turtle, e.g. .moosedev/kg.nq — checked into the repo so git diff shows added/changed records (PR-reviewable) and it merges; (2) the RocksDB store + entity index + ontology vectors become a DERIVED, gitignored local cache, rebuilt from the text on load when missing/stale; (3) capture writes through to RocksDB for live transactional use and exports/marks-dirty the canonical text (on demand, on a `moosedev export`, or a git hook). This COMPLEMENTS rather than contradicts 0d81e237 (which rejected N-Quads as the LIVE store for transactional coherence): RocksDB stays the hot path; text is the committed export. Merge-friendliness is largely already satisfied — MOOSEDev uses named UUID IRIs (not blank nodes, which break RDF merges) and additions are append-only, so sorted N-Quads merges cleanly for concurrent additions; only same-subject edits (e.g. a lifecycle-status flip) can conflict and are rare/resolvable. This REVISES the current 'gitignored .moosedev store' stance in CLAUDE.md/README: the cache stays gitignored, but a new committed text artifact becomes canonical. Open sub-questions: exact serialization + canonical sort order; whether provenance is committed; cache-staleness detection (text mtime/hash vs cache stamp); conflict-resolution guidance for maintainers. Benchmark relevance (not a benchmark task): this lets the PUBLIC corpus KGs (moosedev, rust-rfcs) be published for reproducibility while trivyn's stays private. Scope: MOOSEDev product feature to schedule; NOT part of the value-benchmark phases." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/d459cac2-09f6-4f7b-b959-0f5337d6c5f4> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "accepted" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/d459cac2-09f6-4f7b-b959-0f5337d6c5f4> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-18T16:11:07.103398Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/d459cac2-09f6-4f7b-b959-0f5337d6c5f4> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTitle> "Project KG must be version-controllable and shareable: canonical text serialization as source of truth, RocksDB as a derived local cache" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/f1ccd65b-f816-470b-9b59-8c4f85716bb3> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Requirement> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/f1ccd65b-f816-470b-9b59-8c4f85716bb3> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Embedding-rank A-box recall and realign at reconciliation" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/f1ccd65b-f816-470b-9b59-8c4f85716bb3> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasAuthor> "claude-code" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/f1ccd65b-f816-470b-9b59-8c4f85716bb3> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasDescription> "Two linked gaps, both downstream of the recall honesty fix. (1) get_relevant_context ranks recall by lexical label-token match only; the ontology vector store built at startup (build_alignment_index) is used solely by align_concepts. Rank recall by embedding similarity over instance text (title+description) with a relevance floor, reusing that vector store — this yields semantic recall and a principled score to threshold (the 0.45 lexical floor is the interim honesty fix, not the real recall fix). (2) The alignment engine (suggest_parent) places new concepts under T-box classes, but evidence — codex tried alignment once, got no usable result, and recorded a free ArchitecturalDecision instead — shows projects rarely need new classes and constantly need A-box reconciliation: \"is this new decision a duplicate / refinement / contradiction of one already held?\". Reaim the same embedding machinery at instances to feed the supersede/conflict lifecycle; satisfies the dedup and \"Detect and surface contradictory knowledge entries\" requirements. Leaning toward a FIXED core ontology (no per-project T-box overlay) since extensions are rare, which also avoids the embedding-regen and upgrade-merge problems of a mutable T-box. No custom Chat pipeline needed — compose existing MOOSE capabilities (invariant #8). Depends on the MOOSE A-box-similarity gap recorded as a Constraint." <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/f1ccd65b-f816-470b-9b59-8c4f85716bb3> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasLifecycleStatus> "superseded" <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
<https://moosedev.dev/kg/Requirement/f1ccd65b-f816-470b-9b59-8c4f85716bb3> <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#hasTimestamp> "2026-06-18T03:48:45.559518Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> <https://moosedev.dev/kg/project> .
